 Jenner impersonation.<ref name=nbc-out>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nbcnews.com/feature/nbc-out/meet-jan-singing-queen-rupaul-s-drag-race-season-12-n1145551|title=Meet Jan: The singing queen from 'RuPaul's Drag Race' season 12|website=NBC News|language=en|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref> \"Jan Sport\" pays tribute to his athleticism. He formed the pop group Stephanie's Child along with queens Ros\u00e9 and Lagoona Bloo in 2018. Manitone's drag mother is [[Alexis Michelle]].{{cn|date=April 2020}}\n\nManitone appeared as a contestant on both ''[[The Voice (American TV series)|The Voice]]'' and ''[[America's Got Talent]]''.<ref name=nbc-out/>\n\nJan is currently a contestant on the [[RuPaul's Drag Race (season 12)|twelfth season]] of ''[[RuPaul's Drag Race]]''. On the show, she is referred to as just \"Jan\", to avoid trademark issues with the [[JanSport|backpack brand]]. Her casting was announced on January 23, 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.oprahmag.com/entertainment/tv-movies/a28765179/rupauls-drag-race-season-12-cast-premiere-date/|title=See the \"RuPaul's Drag Race\" Season 12 Queens Competing to Take Home the Crown|last=Amanda Mitchell|date=2020-01-23|website=Oprah Magazine|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n===Featured singles===\n====Featured singles====\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:left;\"\n! scope=\"col\"  style=\"width:20em;\" | Title\n! scope=\"col\"  style=\"width:2em;\" | Year\n! scope=\"col\"  style=\"width:6em;\" | Album\n|-\n| scope=\"row\"| \"You Don't Know Me\"<small>(with The Cast of RuPaul's Drag Race Season 12)</small>\n|rowspan=\"2\"| 2020\n|rowspan=\"2\" {{n/a|non-album single}}\n|-\n| scope=\"row\"| \"Madonna: The Unauthorized Rusical\"<small>(with The Cast of RuPaul's Drag Race Season 12)</small>\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{RuPaul's Drag Race}}\n\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American drag queens]]\n[[Category:Boston Conservatory alumni]]\n[[Category:People f