lets and strategic hills, two water and power stations,<ref>[http://www.syriahr.com/2016/11/21/\u0642\u0648\u0627\u062a-\u0633\u0648\u0631\u064a\u0627-\u0627\u0644\u062f\u064a\u0645\u0642\u0631\u0627\u0637\u064a\u0629-\u062a\u062d\u0631\u0632-\u062a\u0642\u062f\u0645\u0627\u064b-\u062c\u062f/ \u0642\u0648\u0627\u062a \u0633\u0648\u0631\u064a\u0627 \u0627\u0644\u062f\u064a\u0645\u0642\u0631\u0627\u0637\u064a\u0629 \u062a\u062d\u0631\u0632 \u062a\u0642\u062f\u0645\u0627\u064b \u062c\u062f\u064a\u062f\u0627\u064b \u0648\u062a\u0631\u0641\u0639 \u0625\u0644\u0649 48 \u0639\u062f\u062f \u0627\u0644\u0642\u0631\u0649 \u0648\u0627\u0644\u0645\u0632\u0627\u0631\u0639 \u0627\u0644\u0645\u0633\u064a\u0637\u0631 \u0639\u0644\u064a\u0647\u0627]</ref><ref name=Hawar110/> Tabqa Airbase,<ref name=\"Tabqa airbase\" /><ref name=Bloomairbase>{{cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2017-03-26/syrian-opposition-calls-on-us-to-spare-civilians-in-raqqa|title=US-backed Forces Capture Syrian Air Base From IS|first=Philip|last=Issa|work=The Associated Press|publisher=Bloomberg L.P.|date=26 March 2017|accessdate=26 March 2017}}</ref> [[Al-Thawrah|Tabqa city]], [[Tabqa Dam]], and [[Baath Dam]]<ref name=ArabiyaTabqa/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/idUSKBN1862E4|title=U.S.-backed Syria militias say Tabqa, dam captured from Islamic State|first=Ellen|last=Francis|date=10 May 2017|publisher=Reuters}}</ref><ref name=baath>{{Cite web|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-mideast-crisis-syria-raqqa-idUSKBN18V0EX|title=U.S.-backed Syrian forces seize dam west of Raqqa from Islamic State: SDF|work=Reuters|date=4 June 2017}}</ref>\n* The SDF comes within 5 km of the Islamic State's capital city of Raqqa, in early February 2017<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.almasdarnews.com/article/video-kurdish-led-forces-5km-isis-capital-raqqa-rapid-offensive/|title=Video: Kurdish-led forces only 5km from the ISIS capital of Raqqa after rapid offensive|first=Paul|last=Antonopoulos|