s=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170117053258/http://aranews.net/2017/01/over-530-isis-jihadis-killed-133-villages-liberated-in-the-second-phase-of-kurdish-led-raqqa-campaign/ |archivedate=2017-01-17}}<br />Third Phase: 377 killed, 8 captured;{{cite web|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/ypg-made-january-and-february-outcomes-clear/|title=Archived copy|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170305114206/http://en.hawarnews.com/ypg-made-january-and-february-outcomes-clear/|archive-date=2017-03-05}}[https://www.almasdarnews.com/article/kurdish-led-forces-continue-rapid-progress-rural-raqqa-isis/]<br />Fourth Phase: 500+ killed, 8 captured;{{cite web |url=http://www.aranews.net/2017/04/at-least-311-isis-jihadists-killed-by-sdf-fire-in-military-campaign-to-liberate-raqqas-northern-countryside/ |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2017-06-18 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170701115656/http://aranews.net/2017/04/at-least-311-isis-jihadists-killed-by-sdf-fire-in-military-campaign-to-liberate-raqqas-northern-countryside/ |archivedate=2017-07-01}}[https://www.almasdarnews.com/article/huge-isis-casualties-rural-raqqa-counter-offensive-ends-disaster/]<br />Fifth Phase: 1,786 killed, 10 captured;[https://anfenglish.com/news/ypg-releases-balance-sheet-of-war-for-june-20776][https://anfenglish.com/rojava/ypg-releases-balance-sheet-of-war-for-the-month-of-august-21900][https://anfenglish.com/rojava/ypg-releases-balance-sheet-of-war-for-the-month-of-august-21900]<br />Total of 3,784+ reported killed and 38 captured}}<br />6,000 killed {{small|(US claim)}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.businessinsider.com/isis-a-pathetic-and-a-lost-cause-mass-surrender-raqqa-2017-10|title=Top US official calls ISIS a 'pathetic and a lost cause' after mass surrender of militants at Raqqa|author=|publisher=|date=18 October 2017|accessdate=19 October 2017}}</ref>\n|casualties3 = 2,385 civilians killed<ref>[http://www.rudaw.net/english/middleeast/syria/20092017 SDF advance in northern Raqqa after surprise attack on ISIS]</ref><ref name=3200killed>[http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=75821 More than 3200 civilians and fighters were killed in 4 months of the grand battle of Al-Raqqah city and declaration of control continue to be delayed due to the undergoing sweep]</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.alaraby.co.uk/english/news/2017/5/25/coalition-strikes-killing-civilians-by-the-hundreds-in-raqqa|title=Coalition strikes 'killing civilians by the hundreds' in Raqqa|publisher=The New Arab|date=25 May 2017}}</ref><br />200,000 civilians displaced<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dailystar.com.lb/News/Middle-East/2016/Nov-10/380597-5000-displaced-since-start-of-raqa-offensive-sdf.ashx|title=5,000 displaced since start of Raqqa offensive: SDF}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://aranews.net/2017/03/over-2000-civilians-flee-raqqa-into-sdf-held-areas/|title=Over 2,000 civilians flee Raqqa into SDF-held areas}}</ref><ref name=\"flee Tabqa\">{{cite web|url=http://www.skynews.com.au/news/world/mideast/2017/04/01/thousands-flee-is-held-tabqa--syria.html|title=Thousands flee IS-held Tabqa, Syria|first=Australian News Channel Pty|last=Ltd|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.aranews.net/2017/04/raqqa-civilian-council-calls-aid-100000-idps-isis-held-areas/|title=Raqqa Civilian Council calls for aid for 100,000 IDPs from ISIS-held areas|publisher=ARA News|date=28 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.alaraby.co.uk/english/news/2017/6/2/200-000-flee-raqqa-ahead-of-assault-by-syrian-forces|title=200,000 flee Raqqa ahead of assault by Syrian forces|publisher=The New Arab|date=2 June 2017}}</ref>\n|campaignbox = {{Campaignbox Syrian Civil War}}{{Campaignbox Rojava Revolution}}\n}}\n\nThe '''Raqqa campaign'''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-mideast-crisis-syria-raqqa-idUSKBN17D1PX|title=U.S.-backed forces push back Islamic State in Raqqa campaign - officials|date=11 April 2017|publisher=|via=Reuters}}</ref> (codenamed '''Operation Wrath of [[Euphrates]]''') was a military operation launched by the [[Syrian Democratic Forces]] (SDF) against the [[Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant]] (ISIL) in the [[Raqqa Governorate]], with the goal of isolating and eventually capturing the Islamic State's capital city, [[Raqqa]]. The SDF also completed their other main goals and [[Battle of Tabqa (2017)|captured]] the [[Tabqa Dam]], the nearby city of [[al-Thawrah]],<ref name=\"last battle\">{{cite web|url=http://www.thearabweekly.com/News-&-Analysis/7908/Syria%E2%80%99s-last-battle?-Big-push-on-ISIS-capital-Raqqa-gathers-momentum|title=Syria's last battle? Big push on ISIS capital Raqqa gathers momentum|first=The Arab Weekly|last=http://www.thearabweekly.com/|publisher=}}</ref> and the [[Baath Dam]] further downstream.<ref name=\"make gains\">{{cite web|url=http://www.voanews.com/a/kurdish-arab-forces-syria-gains-raqqa-province/3646230.html|title=Kurdish-Arab Forces in Syria Make Gains in Raqqa Province|first=Sirwan|last=Kajjo|publisher=}}</ref>\n\nThe offensive was concurrent with the [[Battle of Sirte (2016)|Battle of Sirte]] in [[Libya]], the [[Battle of Mosul (2016\u201317)|Battle of Mosul]] in [[Iraq]], the [[Battle of al-Bab]] in the [[Aleppo Governorate]], the [[Palmyra offensive (2017)|Palmyra offensive]], the [[Deir ez-Zor offensive (January\u2013February 2017)|reignition of fighting]] in [[Siege of Deir ez-Zor (2014\u201317)|Deir ez-Zor's siege]], the [[Central Syria campaign (2017)|Central Syria campaign]], and the [[2017 Mayadin offensive|Mayadin offensive]].\n\n== Background ==\n{{See also|Battle of Raqqa (March 2013)|Tell Abyad offensive|Northern Raqqa offensive (May 2016)}}\nIn late October 2016, the [[United States Secretary of Defense]] [[Ash Carter]] called for an offensive on Raqqa to take place concurrent with the [[Battle of Mosul (2016)|Battle of Mosul]] in [[Iraq]]. He stated that the US was cooperating with its allies in order to launch an \"isolation operation\" around Raqqa. On 26 October, the [[President of Turkey]] [[Recep Tayyip Erdo\u011fan]] called the [[President of the United States]] [[Barack Obama]] and stated that he did not want the [[People's Protection Units]] (YPG) to participate in the planned operation, and instead, planned to involve the [[Turkish Armed Forces]]. The [[United Kingdom]]'s [[Secretary of State for Defence]] [[Michael Fallon]] rejected the idea of non-[[Arab]] forces taking part in the offensive and demanded a purely Arab force.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.voanews.com/a/allies-resist-us-plan-to-attack-raqqa/3570491.html|title=Allies Resist US Plan to Attack Raqqa|work=Voice of America|date=28 October 2016}}</ref>\n\nOn the same day, the commander of the [[Combined Joint Task Force \u2013 Operation Inherent Resolve]] Lt. Gen. [[Stephen J. Townsend]] stressed that the YPG-led [[Syrian Democratic Forces]] was the only armed group capable of capturing Raqqa in the near future. Fewer [[US-led coalition]] troops were to be involved than in the Battle of Mosul.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.voanews.com/a/raqqa-fight-starting-soon-isolation-operation-kurdish-ypg/3567282.html|title=Raqqa Fight Starting 'Soon,' Isolation Operation to Include YPG|work=Voice of America|date=27 October 2016}}</ref> On 3 November, the commander of the [[Seljuk Brigade]] and SDF spokesman Col. [[Talal Silo]] rejected the participation of Turkey in the operation.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-mideast-crisis-syria-raqqa-idUSKBN12Y0V8|title=Syria's U.S.-backed SDF says no to Turkish role in Raqqa operation|work=Reuters|date=3 November 2016}}</ref>\n\nAfter the start of the Battle of Mosul in Iraq, many of the 20,000 ISIL fighters estimated to be living in the city<ref name=\"push deeper\">{{cite web|url=http://samachartoday.com/2016/09/27/forces-push-deeper-into-key-is-held-northern-town/|title=Forces push deeper into key IS-held northern town Samachar Today|work=Samachar Today|date=27 September 2016|access-date=26 February 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170227155947/http://samachartoday.com/2016/09/27/forces-push-deeper-into-key-is-held-northern-town/|archive-date=27 February 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref> fled to Raqqa, boosting the ISIL forces that were already present in their de facto capital city.<ref name=\"mass exodus\">{{cite web|url=http://www.foxnews.com/world/2016/11/03/mass-exodus-as-isis-fighters-families-flee-mosul-for-raqqa.html|title=Mass exodus as ISIS fighters, families flee Mosul for Raqqa|first=Hollie|last=McKay|date=3 November 2016|publisher=}}</ref>\n\n== Announcement ==\nThe SDF officially announced the start of the operation on 6 November 2016, in the city of [[Ayn Issa]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2016/11/06/US-backed-Syrian-forces-begin-Raqqa-offensive.html|title=US-backed Syrian forces begin Raqqa offensive|work=Al-Arabiya|date=6 November 2016}}</ref> The intention was to proceed in two phases, first seizing areas around Raqqa and isolating the city, advancing from three fronts, then taking control of the city itself.<ref name=AlMonitor1>{{cite web|url=http://www.al-monitor.com/pulse/contents/afp/2016/11/syria-conflict-raqa.html|title=US-backed forces launch bid to capture IS Syria 'capital'|work=Al Monitor|date=6 November 2016}}</ref> The SDF general command called for the [[Military intervention against ISIL|international coalition against ISIL]] to support the operation.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ypgrojava.org/Democratic-Forces-of-Syria-launch-Operation-Wrath-of-Euphrates-to-liberate-Raqqa|title=Democratic Forces of Syria launch Operation Wrath of Euphrates to liberate Raqqa|author=General Command of the Democratic Forces of Syria (SDF)|date=6 November 2016}}</ref> [[U.S. Secretary of Defense|Secretary of Defense]] [[Ash Carter]] welcomed the announcement.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.defense.gov/News/News-Releases/News-Release-View/Article/997338/statement-by-secretary-of-defense-ash-carter-on-raqqa|title=Statement by Secretary of Defense Ash Carter on Raqqa|publisher=U.S. Department of Defense|date=6 November 2016}}</ref>\n\n== The offensive ==\n=== Phase One: Isolating Raqqa from its northern hinterland ===\n[[File:Tel al-Samin after SDF conquest (November 2016).png|thumb|left|Tal Saman, former [[Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant|ISIL]] headquarters in the northern Raqqa countryside, after being captured by the [[Syrian Democratic Forces|SDF]]]]\nOn 6 November, the SDF captured six small villages,<ref name=\"batch\"/> including the villages of Wahid, Umm Safa, Wasita, Haran, al-Adriyah and Jurah south and southeast of [[Ayn Issa]].<ref name=Almasdar1>{{cite web|url=https://www.almasdarnews.com/article/kurdish-forces-capture-first-batch-villages-isis-campaign-liberate-raqqa/|title=Kurdish forces capture first batch of villages from ISIS in campaign to liberate Raqqa|publisher=Almasdar News|date=6 November 2016}}</ref> The Islamic State detonated four [[car bomb]]s on the first day of the offensive.<ref name=MEE1>{{cite web|url=http://www.middleeasteye.net/news/morale-high-among-anti-islamic-state-fighters-marching-raqqa-986613335|title=Morale is high among anti-Islamic State fighters marching on Raqqa|publisher=MiddleEastEye|date=6 November 2016}}</ref>\n\nOn 8 November, the SDF reported that they had taken control of 11 villages near Ayn Issa. The SDF also claimed that ISIL used several car bombs against their forces.<ref name=\"aranews.net\">{{cite web|url=http://aranews.net/2016/11/syrian-democratic-forces-report-first-gains-raqqa-operation-liberate-11-villages/|title=Syrian Democratic Forces report first gains in Raqqa operation, capture 11 villages|date=8 November 2016|publisher=[[ARA News]]}}</ref> By 11 November, the SDF had captured over a dozen villages and the strategically significant town of [[Al-Hisbah]], which had served as a local headquarters and command center for ISIL.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.almasdarnews.com/article/syrian-democratic-forces-overrun-isis-bastion-north-raqqa/|title=Syrian Democratic Forces overrun ISIS bastion north of Raqqa|first=Chris|last=Tomson|date=11 November 2016|publisher=al-Masdar News|accessdate=12 November 2016}}</ref> On the next day, the SDF continued to advance against ISIL in the area around Tal Saman and Khnez, bringing the number of captured farms and villages to 26.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=54433|title=Continued clashes in Raqqa countryside|work=SOHR|date=12 November 2016}}</ref>\n\nOn 14 November, the SDF reported the completion of the First Phase of the operations, stating that 500&nbsp;km<sup>2</sup> has been captured: 34 villages, 31 hamlets and seven strategic hills, along with 167 Islamic State casualties.<ref name=\"reveals\"/> The SDF had also begun to besiege Tal Saman, the largest village and ISIL headquarters north of Raqqa,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=54646|title=Continued clashes and SDF advance in 33 villages|work=SOHR|date=14 November 2016}}</ref> while ISIL launched a counter-attack near Salok in the eastern countryside of Raqqa Governorate in order to force the SDF to split its forces and open a new front.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=54628|title=IS attacks SDF in Raqqa countryside|work=SOHR|date=14 November 2016}}</ref> On the next day, the SDF advanced into Tal Saman, resulting in a fierce battle with its ISIL defenders,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.almasdarnews.com/article/kurdish-forces-capture-another-village-push-towards-raqqa-city/|title=Kurdish forces capture another village in push towards Raqqa city|publisher=al-Masdar News|first=Chris|last=Tomson|date=16 November 2016|accessdate=17 November 2016}}</ref> and captured 10 more villages and farms.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=54698|title=An explosion in Tal Abyad town and clashes in the vicinity of Tal al-Samn|work=SOHR|date=15 November 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=54751|title=YPG sdf us forces New advancement in about 10 areas in the countryside of Raqqa within the operation of isolating the city from its countryside|work=SOHR|date=15 November 2016}}</ref> By 19 November, the SDF had fully captured Tal Saman and had driven ISIL completely from the surrounding countryside.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=55090|title=Controlling Tal al-Samn area north of Raqqa raises the number of areas controlled by The Syria Democratic Forces of \"Euphrates Wrath\" to 47|work=SOHR|date=19 November 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/sdf-fighters-completely-liberate-tal-saman/|title=SDF fighters completely liberate Tal Saman|publisher=[[Hawar News Agency]]|date=19 November 2016|access-date=20 November 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161121042855/http://en.hawarnews.com/sdf-fighters-completely-liberate-tal-saman/|archive-date=21 November 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref> With this, the first phase of the offensive was considered completed.<ref name=atimes>{{cite web|url=http://www.atimes.com/raqqa-will-mark-islamic-states-downfall/|title=Raqqa will mark Islamic State's downfall|work=Asia Times|date=20 November 2016}}</ref>\n\n=== Stalemate and preparation for the second phase ===\n[[File:US airstrike in northern Raqqa countryside (December 2016).png|thumb|left|A [[United States Air Force]] airstrike on an [[Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant|ISIL]] position to the north of [[Raqqa]]]]\nThe second phase of the offensive aimed to enforce a full blockade of the city of Raqqa.<ref name=atimes/> On 21 November, the SDF captured two more villages,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=55263|title=The Syria Democratic Forces raise the number of villages and farms controlled to 48, Coalition bombards north of Raqqa|work=SOHR|date=21 November 2016}}</ref> while ISIL launched a counter-attack near Tal Saman.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=55272|title=School students demonstrate against imposing Kurdish books in Hasakah|work=SOHR|date=21 November 2016}}</ref> Over the next days, the SDF attempted to further advance, such as at al-Qalita,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=55362|title=Continued clashes between IS and SDF in Raqqa|work=SOHR|date=23 November 2016}}</ref> but was unable to break through ISIL's defense line south of Tal Saman.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.almasdarnews.com/article/breaking-us-soldier-dies-due-isis-booby-trap-northern-syria/|title=Breaking: US soldier dies due to ISIS booby trap in northern Syria|publisher=al-Masdar News|first=Chris|last=Tomson|date=24 November 2016|accessdate=25 November 2016}}</ref> On 24 November, a US serviceman died from wounds he suffered after stepping on an improvised explosive device near the town of Ayn Issa, to the north of Raqqa.{{citation needed|date=February 2020}}\n\nOn 25 November, ISIL received reinforcements from Iraq, among them explosive experts and defected Iraqi Army personnel.<ref>{{cite web|title=200 ISIS members arrive to Syria's Raqqa: rights group|url=http://www.iraqinews.com/arab-world-news/200-isis-members-arrive-syrias-raqqa-rights-group/}}</ref> On the next day, ISIL launched a counter-attack, retaking parts of Qaltah village and a nearby water pump station, while the SDF managed to advance in the village's vicinity.<ref name=\"Qaltah\">{{cite web|url=http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=55651|title=Violent clashes in the vicinity of Tal Sawwanah area and in the northern countryside of Raqqa|work=SOHR|date=26 November 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://syria.liveuamap.com/en/2016/27-november-is-regained-control-of-water-pumpstation-near|title=IS regained control of water pump/station near Kaltah in north Raqqa countryside following clashes with SDF yesterday|work=Syria Live Map|date=27 November 2016}}</ref> Boubaker Al-Hakim, an ISIL commander who was linked to the [[Charlie Hebdo shooting]], was reported to have been killed in an American airstrike in Raqqa on 26 November.<ref name=\"facilitators\">{{cite web|url=http://www.longwarjournal.org/archives/2016/12/pentagon-2-paris-attack-facilitators-killed-in-us-airstrike-in-raqqa-syria.php|title=Pentagon: 2 Paris attack facilitators killed in US airstrike in Raqqa, Syria|first=Thomas|last=Joscelyn|work=Long War Journal|date=13 December 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.business-standard.com/article/pti-stories/us-airstrike-killed-militant-linked-to-charlie-hebdo-attack-116121000030_1.html|title=US airstrike killed militant linked to Charlie Hebdo attack|work=Business Standard|date=10 December 2016}}</ref> Iraqi military however later stated in April 2017 that he might still be alive.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/idUSKBN17H0F4|title=Islamic State militant linked to Charlie Hebdo attack could still be alive: Iraq|work=Reuters|date=15 April 2017}}</ref>\n\nOn 27 November, the SDF announced the offensive's second phase was due to start,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/jihan-ahmad-second-phase-of-the-raqqa-campaign-due-to-start/|title=Jihan Ahmad: Second phase of the Raqqa campaign due to start|publisher=[[Hawar News Agency]]|date=27 November 2016|access-date=27 November 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161128133001/http://en.hawarnews.com/jihan-ahmad-second-phase-of-the-raqqa-campaign-due-to-start/|archive-date=28 November 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref> though this was then delayed. At least five SDF fighters were killed in renewed clashes north of Raqqa on 29 November.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://aranews.net/2016/11/five-kurdish-fighters-killed-isis-fire-north-raqqa/|title=Five Kurdish fighters killed by ISIS fire north Raqqa|publisher=[[ARA News]]|date=30 November 2016}}</ref> Meanwhile, ISIL suffered from the defection of two senior commanders, who fled from Raqqa to join [[Al-Nusra Front|Jabhat Fateh al-Sham]] in [[Idlib]].<ref name=\"flee\">{{cite web|url=http://www.voanews.com/a/two-top-islamic-state-commanders-flee-raqqa/3627238.html|title=2 Top IS Commanders Reportedly Flee Raqqa|work=VOA News|first=Sirwan|last=Kajjo|date=20 November 2016}}</ref> On 4 December, a coalition drone strike in Raqqa killed two ISIL leaders who had helped facilitate the [[November 2015 Paris attacks]] and another who was involved in a foiled [[suicide attack]] in Belgium in 2015.<ref name=\"facilitators\" /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.foxnews.com/world/2016/12/13/paris-attack-planners-among-3-isis-fighters-killed-in-drone-strike-pentagon-says.html|title=Paris attack planners among 3 ISIS fighters killed in drone strike, Pentagon says|date=4 December 2016}}</ref> Three days later, co-Chair of the [[Democratic Union Party (Syria)|Democratic Union Party]] (PYD) [[Salih Muslim]] said that the first phase to surround Raqqa was almost over, while a new Arab brigade consisting of more than 1,000 men and women from the Raqqa area had joined the SDF as part of the second phase which was slated to be launched on 10 December.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://aranews.net/2016/12/over-1000-new-fighters-join-syrian-democratic-forces-in-fight-for-raqqa/|title=Over 1,000 new fighters join Syrian Democratic Forces in fight for Raqqa|publisher=[[ARA News]]|date=10 December 2016}}</ref> More than 1,500 Arab fighters who were trained and equipped by the anti-ISIL coalition joined the SDF for the second phase on its launch day.<ref name=\"Secondphase\">{{cite web|url=http://aranews.net/2016/12/syrian-democratic-forces-launch-second-phase-raqqa-operation/|title=Syrian Democratic Forces launch second phase of Raqqa Operation|publisher=[[ARA News]]|date=10 December 2016|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161213053518/http://aranews.net/2016/12/syrian-democratic-forces-launch-second-phase-raqqa-operation/|archivedate=13 December 2016}}</ref>\n\n=== Phase Two: Isolating Raqqa from its western countryside ===\n==== Initial advances ====\n[[File:SDF infantry in northern Raqqa countryside (December 2016).png|thumb|left|[[Syrian Democratic Forces|SDF]] fighters advance northwest of [[Raqqa]] after the start of the offensive's second phase.]]\nThe SDF launched the second phase on 10 December, with the aim of capturing the northwestern and western countryside of Raqqa and ultimately reaching and securing the [[Tabqa Dam]]. The same day, it was announced that Arab SDF groups, consisting of the [[Syria's Tomorrow Movement#Military wing|Elite Forces]], [[Jabhat Thuwar al-Raqqa]] and the newly formed [[Syrian Democratic Forces military councils#Deir Ezzor|Deir Ezzor Military Council]] would be taking part. During the first day, the SDF began to advance south of the [[Tishrin Dam]] and captured al-Kiradi village.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=56675|title=Coalition warplanes target the northern countryside again, and the regime forces shell al-Vgeh in the countryside of Daraa after advancement of the factions|work=SOHR|date=10 December 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://rudaw.net/english/middleeast/syria/101220162|title=SDF: Phase 2 of Raqqa campaign begins, sights set on al-Tabqa dam|work=Rudaw|date=10 December 2016}}</ref> The United States announced that it would send 200 more troops to assist the SDF.<ref name=\"500more\">{{cite web|url=http://www.aljazeera.com/news/2016/12/american-troops-raqqa-offensive-161210073733228.html|title=US to deploy 200 more troops for Raqqa offensive|work=Al Jazeera|date=10 December 2016}}</ref> The next day, the SDF captured seven more villages from ISIL.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/wrath-of-euphrates-liberates-6-villages/|title=Wrath of Euphrates liberates 6 villages|publisher=[[Hawar News Agency]]|date=11 December 2016|access-date=11 December 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161213043409/http://en.hawarnews.com/wrath-of-euphrates-liberates-6-villages/|archive-date=13 December 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref name=\"200killed\" /> On 12 December, the SDF captured four villages as well as many hamlets south of Tishrin Dam.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/two-villages-liberated-in-al-raqqa/|title=Two villages liberated in al-Raqqa|publisher=[[Hawar News Agency]]|date=12 December 2016|access-date=12 December 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161212105143/http://en.hawarnews.com/two-villages-liberated-in-al-raqqa/|archive-date=12 December 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/ajaj-and-safakhir-villages-freed/|title=Ajaj and Safakhir villages freed|publisher=[[Hawar News Agency]]|date=12 December 2016|access-date=12 December 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161212135517/http://en.hawarnews.com/ajaj-and-safakhir-villages-freed/|archive-date=12 December 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref name=\"200killed\">{{cite web|url=http://aranews.net/2016/12/kurdish-arab-alliance-captures-new-areas-raqqa-tells-isis-jihadists-surrender-die/|title=Kurdish-Arab alliance captures new areas in Raqqa, tells ISIS jihadists: \"Surrender or Die\"|publisher=[[ARA News]]|date=13 December 2016}}</ref> The SDF captured five villages during the next two days.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=56912|title=SDF advances in 2 villages over IS in Raqqa countryside|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=56956|title=Casualties and injuries in Deir Ezzor city and Syria Democratic Forces advance in the countryside of Raqqa|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=57013|title=Clashes in Deir Ezzor city and new advancement for the Syria Democratic Forces at the northern countryside of Raqqa|publisher=}}</ref> On 15 December, the SDF captured three villages, taking the total number of villages captured by them in the second phase to 20.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=57039|title=SDF advances in 20 areas in Raqqa countryside|publisher=}}</ref>\n\nOver the next four days, the SDF captured 20 more villages and finally reaching [[Lake Assad]], thereby cutting off and besieging 54 ISIL-held villages to the west. In response to these territorial losses, ISIL began to carry out more suicide attacks against both the SDF as well as civilian targets within SDF-controlled areas in an attempt to hinder the offensive.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.almasdarnews.com/article/syrian-democratic-forces-reach-euphrates-besiege-isis-held-area/|title=Syrian Democratic Forces reach Euphrates, besiege ISIS-held area|work=[[al-Masdar News]]|first=Ivan|last=Yakovlev|date=19 December 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=57158|title=Clashes continue in Raqqa countryside between IS and SDF|publisher=|date=2016-12-17}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://aranews.net/2016/12/syrian-democratic-forces-capture-new-areas-west-raqqa-amid-isis-retreat/|title=Syrian Democratic Forces capture new areas west Raqqa amid ISIS retreat|publisher=[[ARA News]]|date=18 December 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/idUSKBN1480ZE?il=0|title=Kurd-led forces press Islamic State near Syria's Raqqa|work=Reuters|date=19 December 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=57366|title=SDF advance in 40 villages in Raqqa countryside|publisher=|date=2016-12-20}}</ref> On 19 December, ISIL launched a counter-attack to regain four villages in the northwestern countryside,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://syria.liveuamap.com/en/2016/20-december-isil-launched-counteroffensive-west-to-raqqa|title=ISIL launched counter-offensive west to Raqqa and regained several villages: Sayqul(\u0635\u0627\u064a\u0642\u0648\u0644), Khirbat Al Jahsha(\u062e\u0631\u0628\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u062c\u062d\u0634\u0629), Al Majibina(\u0627\u0644\u0645\u062c\u064a\u0628\u0646\u0629), Khirbat Al Baqra(\u062e\u0631\u0628\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0642\u0631\u0629)|work=Syria Live Map|date=19 December 2016}}</ref> but the attack was repelled after a few hours.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/isis-attack-thwarted-9-mercenaries-killed/|title=ISIS attack thwarted, 9 mercenaries killed|publisher=[[Hawar News Agency]]|date=19 December 2016|access-date=21 December 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161221234408/http://en.hawarnews.com/isis-attack-thwarted-9-mercenaries-killed/|archive-date=21 December 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref> The following night, ISIL forces retreated largely unopposed from the besieged 54 villages, leaving them to be captured by the SDF.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://southfront.org/kurdish-ypg-forces-liberate-54-villages-from-isis-in-province-of-raqqah-report/|title=Kurdish YPG Forces Liberate 54 Villages From ISIS In Province Of Raqqa|work=South Front|date=20 December 2016}}</ref><ref name=SFJabar/> The SDF declared that they had captured 97 villages overall during the second phase, and had begun to advance against [[Qal'at Ja'bar]].<ref name=97vilages>{{cite web|url=http://aranews.net/2016/12/us-backed-syrian-democratic-forces-expel-isis-from-97-villages-west-raqqa/|title=US-backed Syrian Democratic Forces expel ISIS from 97 villages west Raqqa|publisher=[[ARA News]]|date=21 December 2016}}</ref>\n\n==== Battle of Jabar ====\n[[File:Killed ISIL fighters near Mahmudli.png|thumb|left|Dead [[Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant|ISIL]] fighters near Mahmudli]]\nOn 21 December, the SDF seized five villages near Qal'at Ja'bar, including [[Al-Jarniyah Subdistrict#Towns and villages|Jabar]],<ref name=SFJabar>{{cite web|url=https://southfront.org/ypg-forces-seize-jobar-deploy-closer-to-al-tabqa-dam/|title=YPG FORCES SEIZE JABAR, DEPLOY CLOSER TO AL-TABQA DAM|work=South Front|date=21 December 2016}}</ref> which served as the main weaponry storage and supply centre for ISIL in the northwestern countryside.<ref name=\"Jabar\">{{cite web|url=http://aranews.net/2016/12/kurdish-led-sdf-forces-expel-isis-from-key-town-west-raqqa-kill-over-50-jihadists/|title=Kurdish-led SDF forces expel ISIS from key town west Raqqa, kill over 50 jihadists|publisher=[[ARA News]]|first=Ahmed|last=Shiwesh|date=27 December 2016|accessdate=27 December 2016}}</ref> The coalition then began to move toward [[Raqqa Subdistrict#Towns and villages|Suwaydiya Saghirah]] and [[Raqqa Subdistrict#Towns and villages|Suwaydiya Kabir]], the last villages before Tabqa Dam.<ref name=SFJabar /><ref>{{cite web|url=https://southfront.org/kurdish-ypg-seizes-3-more-villages-in-raqqa-province-advancing-towards-tabqa-damn/|title=KURDISH YPG SEIZES 3 MORE VILLAGES IN RAQQA PROVINCE, ADVANCING TOWARDS TABQA DAMN|work=South Front|date=21 December 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=57461|title=Warplanes raid on Deir Ezzor and its western countryside and clashes continue in the western countryside of Raqqa|publisher=|date=2016-12-22}}</ref> Even though an ISIL counter-attack managed to retake Jabar village soon after,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://syria.liveuamap.com/en/2016/22-december-sdf-kurds-have-captured-jabah-bir-shallal-and|title=SDF Kurds have captured Jabah, Bir Shallal and Ghadban, but were pushed back by IS at Jabar in West Raqqa governate|work=Sytia Live Map|date=22 December 2016}}</ref> the SDF attacked again on 23 December, and once again took control of it, while also capturing another village.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://southfront.org/kurdish-ypg-forces-capture-suwaydiya-saghirah-in-syrias-raqqah-province-map-video/|title=Kurdish YPG forces capture Suwaydiya Saghirah in Syria's Raqqa province (map, video)|work=South Front|date=23 December 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://syria.liveuamap.com/en/2016/23-december-sdf-captured-jedi-jabar-villages-and-control|title=SDF captured Jedi, Jabar villages and control Suwaydiya Saghirah. West Raqqa|work=Syria Live Map|date=23 December 2016}}</ref> This prompted ISIL to launch yet another counter-attack later that day, which was accompanied by several suicide car bombs.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/10910-2/|title=Wrath of Euphrates: 16 ISIS militants killed in heavy clashes|publisher=[[Hawar News Agency]]|date=23 December 2016|access-date=23 December 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161223154036/http://en.hawarnews.com/10910-2/|archive-date=23 December 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=57571|title=IS detonates 3 suicide cars in Raqqa countryside|work=SOHR|date=23 December 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/raqqa-campaign-seven-bomb-laden-vehicles-destroyed/|title=Raqqa Campaign: Seven bomb-laden vehicles destroyed|publisher=[[Hawar News Agency]]|date=23 December 2016|access-date=23 December 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161224095226/http://en.hawarnews.com/raqqa-campaign-seven-bomb-laden-vehicles-destroyed/|archive-date=24 December 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref> As a result, heavy clashes took place between them and SDF fighters in several villages along the frontline that lasted until the early morning of 24 December. The ISIL forces were eventually forced to withdraw after the SDF first shelled and then stormed their positions, whereupon the latter took control of most of Jabar as well as two more villages,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=57665|title=The Syria Democratic Forces advance in the northern banks of the Euphrates River|work=SOHR|date=24 December 2016}}</ref><ref name=16militants>{{cite web|url=http://aranews.net/2016/12/at-least-16-isis-militants-killed-by-sdf-fire-near-raqqa/|title=At least 16 ISIS militants killed by SDF fire near Raqqa|publisher=[[ARA News]]|date=24 December 2016|accessdate=24 December 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://anfenglish.com/news/two-more-villages-liberated-in-raqqa-following-heavy-clashes|title=Two more villages liberated in Raqqa following heavy clashes|work=ANF News|date=24 December 2016}}</ref> though some ISIL holdouts persisted in Jabar.<ref name=\"Jabar\" />\n\nISIL was pushed out of the neighboring, strategic village of Eastern Jabar on the next day, bringing the SDF within {{convert|5|km|mi}} of Tabqa Dam,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://rudaw.net/english/middleeast/syria/25122016|title=SDF 5km from strategic Tabqa dam west of Raqqa|work=Rudaw|date=25 December 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=57753|title=The Syria Democratic Forces and US Special Forces are 5 km away from the Euphrates Dam, kill 25 members of the \"Islamic State\" at least|work=SOHR|date=25 December 2016}}</ref> and by 26 December, the SDF had finally fully secured the main Jabar village, with the last ISIL defenders being expelled after heavy fighting.<ref name=\"Jabar\" /> An ISIL counterattack on the village later that day failed,<ref name=\"al-Kuwaiti2\" /><ref>{{cite web|url=https://anfenglish.com/news/38-isis-members-killed-amid-severe-clashes-in-jabar-and-hadaj-villages|title=38 ISIS members killed amid severe clashes in Jabar and Hadaj villages|work=ANF News|date=27 December 2016}}</ref> with a US airstrike killing [[Abu Jandal al-Kuwaiti]] as he commanded the assault. Al-Kuwaiti, also known as Abdulmuhsin al-Zaghelan al-Tarish, was a high-ranking ISIL commander leading the defense of the whole Raqqa region against the SDF.<ref name=\"al-Kuwaiti2\" /><ref name=\"al-Kuwaiti\" /> Meanwhile, the [[Amaq News Agency]] declared that Iman Na'im Tandil (''nom de guerre'': Abu 'Umar Al-Hindi), one of the few [[Indian people|Indian]] ISIL fighters active in Syria, had also been killed during the fighting near Jabar. The Islamic State's official media wing later also officially paid tribute to Iman.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.almasdarnews.com/article/indian-national-killed-syria-fighting-isis/|title=Indian national killed in Syria while fighting for ISIS|work=[[al-Masdar News]]|date=28 December 2016}}</ref>\n\n==== Battle for Jabar's surroundings ====\n[[File:YPG BMP near Mahmudli.png|thumb|right|A [[People's Protection Units|YPG]] [[BMP development|BMP]], loaded on a truck, being transported to the frontline near Mahmudli on 4 January]]\n\n===== First week =====\nOn 27 December, ISIL launched an attack on the village of Secol in the northern countryside, reportedly breaching the local SDF defences.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.almasdarnews.com/article/isis-attacks-kurdish-positions-south-kobani/|title=ISIS attacks Kurdish positions south of Kobani|work=[[al-Masdar News]]|first=Paul|last=Antonopoulos|date=27 December 2016}}</ref> On the next day, the SDF reportedly captured Hadaj village after two days of heavy fighting, while another ISIL counter-attack against Jabar was repelled.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/a-village-liberated-and-38-mercenaries-killed/|title=A village liberated and 38 mercenaries killed|publisher=[[Hawar News Agency]]|date=28 December 2016|access-date=28 December 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161229100622/http://en.hawarnews.com/a-village-liberated-and-38-mercenaries-killed/|archive-date=29 December 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref> Mahmud al-Isawi, a senior ISIL manager of finances for the group's leaders who also worked in propaganda and intelligence-gathering, was killed on 31 December in a US-led coalition airstrike on Raqqa.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dailystar.com.lb/News/Middle-East/2017/Jan-06/388201-coalition-strike-kills-senior-isis-leader-in-syria-us.ashx|title=Coalition strike kills senior ISIS leader in Syria: US|publisher=The Daily Star|date=6 January 2017}}</ref> After three days of heavy fighting, the SDF captured all or most of Mahmudli, the largest town of the [[Al-Jarniyah Subdistrict]], on 1 January 2017. ISIL counterattacked later in an attempt to regain the town.<ref>{{cite web|last1=J.O|title=Wrath of Euphrates advances 6 km towards Til Samin|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/wrath-of-euphrates-advances-6-km-towards-til-samin/|publisher=[[Hawar News Agency]]|date=1 January 2017|accessdate=1 January 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170102171340/http://en.hawarnews.com/wrath-of-euphrates-advances-6-km-towards-til-samin/|archive-date=2 January 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=58181|title=Syria Democratic Forces advance in the countryside of al-Tabaqa within \"Euphrates Wrath\" operation|publisher=|date=January 2017}}</ref> The SDF leadership said that in the clashes since the launch of the second phase they had captured 110 villages, killed 277 ISIL fighters, and captured 13.<ref name=1500km2>{{cite web|url=http://aranews.net/2017/01/kurdish-led-sdf-announces-liberation-110-villages-death-277-isis-militants-fresh-operations-near-raqqa/|title=Kurdish-led SDF announces liberation of 110 villages, death of 277 ISIS militants in fresh operations near Raqqa|publisher=[[ARA News]]|date=1 January 2017|accessdate=2 January 2017}}</ref>\n\nAlso, on January 1, 2017, the SDF resumed its offensive on the northern front, advancing 6&nbsp;km south of Tell Saman against ISIL positions.<ref name=Hawar110>{{cite web|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/wrath-of-euphrates-progressing-110-villages-liberated-till-now/|title=Wrath of Euphrates progressing, 110 villages liberated till now|publisher=[[Hawar News Agency]]|date=1 January 2017|accessdate=1 January 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170102082327/http://en.hawarnews.com/wrath-of-euphrates-progressing-110-villages-liberated-till-now/|archive-date=2 January 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://anfenglish.com/news/another-strategic-step-in-the-operation-wrath-of-euphrates|title=Another strategic step in the Operation Wrath of Euphrates|work=ANF News|date=1 January 2017|accessdate=1 January 2017}}</ref> The SDF captured nine more villages in this area within the next three days.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/sdf-fighters-liberate-three-more-raqqa-villages/|title=SDF fighters liberate three more Raqqa villages|publisher=[[Hawar News Agency]]|date=3 January 2017|accessdate=3 January 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170104090726/http://en.hawarnews.com/sdf-fighters-liberate-three-more-raqqa-villages/|archive-date=4 January 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://syria.liveuamap.com/en/2017/2-january-report-on-ayn-issa-front-sdf-captured-nediye-village|title=Report: On Ayn Issa front SDF captured Nediye village from ISIL|publisher=Syria Live Map|date=3 January 2017|accessdate=3 January 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://syria.liveuamap.com/en/2017/3-january-on-ayn-issa-front-sdf-recaptured-mayan-village|title=On Ayn Issa front SDF recaptured Mayan village from ISIL|publisher=Syria Live Map|date=3 January 2017|accessdate=3 January 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://aranews.net/2017/01/syrian-democratic-forces-seize-more-ground-west-raqqa-push-to-isis-capital/|title=Syrian Democratic Forces seize more ground west Raqqa, push to ISIS capital|publisher=[[ARA News]]|first=Ahmed|last=Shiwesh|date=4 January 2017|accessdate=4 January 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://syria.liveuamap.com/en/2017/4-january-ain-issa-front-sdf-captured-villages-erbo-dehlan|title=Ain Issa front: SDF captured villages Erbo, Dehlan, Arir, Swwillam, Khirbi Shekh Jiddi|publisher=Syria Live Map|date=4 January 2017|accessdate=5 January 2017}}</ref> Meanwhile, with the SDF edging closer to Raqqa, ISIL further restricted Internet access and increased surveillance over Internet users in Raqqa. There were harsh punishments for accessing anti-ISIL websites, with a new special unit within the ISIL's security office searching for offenders. Several online activists in Raqqa were captured and tortured or executed.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.voanews.com/a/islamic-state-tightens-internet-restrictions-raqqa/3661816.html|title=IS Tightens Internet Restrictions in Raqqa|publisher=[[Voice of America]]|first=Sirwan|last=Kajjo|date=3 January 2017|accessdate=4 January 2017}}</ref>\n\n===== Second week =====\nAnother two villages and hamlets were captured by the SDF on 5 January 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/two-villages-and-two-hamlets-liberated/|title=Two villages and two hamlets liberated|publisher=[[Hawar News Agency]]|date=5 January 2017|accessdate=6 January 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170512155133/http://en.hawarnews.com/two-villages-and-two-hamlets-liberated/|archive-date=12 May 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n[[File:SDF at Jabar Castle 3.png|thumb|left|SDF fighters examine [[Qal'at Ja'bar]]. ISIL had built tunnels and weapons depots into the medieval castle.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.voanews.com/a/us-backed-kurdish-forces-capture-historic-castle-form-is-near-raqqa/3671014.html|title=US-backed Kurdish Forces Capture Historic Castle From IS Near Raqqa|publisher=[[Voice of America]]|author=|date=10 January 2017|accessdate=23 January 2017}}</ref>]]\n\nThe SDF captured Qal'at Ja'bar (Ja'bar Castle) from ISIL on 6 January.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.voanews.com/a/us-backed-forces-in-syria-target-strategic-is-held-dam/3666068.html|title=US-backed Forces in Syria Target Strategic IS-held Dam|first=Sirwan|last=Kajjo|publisher=[[Voice of America]]|date=6 January 2017|accessdate=6 January 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.yahoo.com/news/kurdish-arab-forces-seize-strategic-syria-citadel-175514147.html|title=Kurdish-Arab forces seize strategic Syria citadel from IS|work=Agnce France-Presse|publisher=Yahoo! News|date=6 January 2017|accessdate=6 January 2017}}</ref> The same day, ISIL was reported to have moved its 150 prisoners from [[List of Syrian Air Force bases|Tabqa]] city due to the offensive.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.business-standard.com/article/news-ians/is-moves-prisoners-as-forces-advance-on-raqqa-117010600686_1.html|title=IS moves prisoners as forces advance on Raqqa|publisher=Business Standard|date=6 January 2017|accessdate=6 January 2017|newspaper=Business Standard India}}</ref> The SDF later captured eight villages and five hamlets at the Ayn Issa front.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/eight-villages-five-hamlets-liberated-in-raqqa/|title=Eight villages, five hamlets liberated in Raqqa|publisher=[[Hawar News Agency]]|date=6 January 2017|accessdate=6 January 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170107170441/http://en.hawarnews.com/eight-villages-five-hamlets-liberated-in-raqqa/|archive-date=7 January 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref> On 7 January, the SDF captured five villages including the strategic Suwaydiya Gharbi<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=58601|title=Helicopters bomb Morek and continuous clashes in the countryside Ain Issa and the Syria Democratic Forces advance in the area|publisher=|date=2017-01-07}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/isis-strategic-stronghold-was-liberated/|title=ISIS strategic stronghold was liberated|publisher=[[Hawar News Agency]]|date=6 January 2017|accessdate=6 January 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170109020831/http://en.hawarnews.com/isis-strategic-stronghold-was-liberated/|archive-date=9 January 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref> and Suwaydiya Saghirah, reaching the outskirts of Tabqa Dam.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=58595|title=The Syria Democratic Forces and US Special forces control a village north of al-Tabaqa and reach the outskirts of the strategic Dam of Euphrates|publisher=|date=2017-01-07}}</ref> ISIL recaptured Suwaydiya Saghirah by the next day after a counterattack, while a local leader of the group was killed in clashes.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=58659|title=Violent clashes in several areas near the Euphrates dam in the northern countryside of Raqqa|publisher=|date=2017-01-08}}</ref> Meanwhile, ISIL was reported to have withdrawn 150 of its fighters towards Raqqa city.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=58664|title=Although the arrival of Turkish reinforcements to al-Bab and the \"Euphrates Wrath\" to the outskirts of Euphrates Dam\u2026 the \"Islamic State\" pulls more than 150 of its members towards the \"Euphrates State\"|publisher=|date=2017-01-08}}</ref>\n\nOn 8 January 2017, US special forces raided the village of Al-Kubar, between Raqqa and Deir ez-Zor, killing at least 25 ISIL militants in the two-hour operation.<ref name=\"Al-Kubar raid\">{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2017/01/09/us-special-forces-carry-ground-raid-against-isil/|title=US special forces carry out secret ground raid against Isil in Syria, 'killing at least 25 jihadists'|publisher=|newspaper=The Telegraph|date=2017-01-09|last1=Ensor|first1=Josie}}</ref> It was believed that the goal of the US may have been to rescue hostages from an ISIL secret prison in the village. After the raid, ISIL forces cut off access to the village.<ref name=\"Al-Kubar raid\" />\n\nOn 9 January, the SDF captured another village, along with three hamlets.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/sdf-fighters-liberate-one-village-three-hamlets-in-raqqa-campaign/|title=SDF fighters liberate one village, three hamlets in Raqqa campaign|publisher=[[Hawar News Agency]]|date=9 January 2017|accessdate=10 January 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170112021040/http://en.hawarnews.com/sdf-fighters-liberate-one-village-three-hamlets-in-raqqa-campaign/|archive-date=12 January 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n===== Third week =====\nOn 10 January, ISIL launched a large-scale counter-attack at the Jabar frontline and reportedly recaptured several sites;<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=58800|title=The \"Islamic State\" renews the counterattacks at the northern banks of Euphrates River|publisher=SOHR|date=10 January 2017|accessdate=11 January 2017}}</ref> with pro-[[Free Syrian Army]] sources claiming Qal'at Ja'bar and the village of Jabar were among these.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.almasdarnews.com/article/isis-fights-back-us-backed-fighters-northern-syria-captures-historical-castle/|title=Isis fights back US-backed fighters in northern Syria, captures historical castle|publisher=[[al-Masdar News]]|first=Zen|last=Adra|date=10 January 2017|accessdate=11 January 2017}}</ref> ISIL consequently released photos of dead SDF fighters, while claiming that over 70 of them had been killed in the counter-attack.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.almasdarnews.com/article/graphic-18-isis-claims-killed-70-kurdish-fighters-west-raqqa/|title=[Graphic 18+] ISIS claims to have killed 70+ Kurdish fighters in west Raqqa|publisher=[[al-Masdar News]]|first=Leith|last=Fadel|date=10 January 2017|accessdate=11 January 2017}}</ref> However, the SDF was reported to still be in control of Jabar village and Qalat Jabar a few days later.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.middleeasteye.net/news/raqqa-sdf-islamic-state-taqba-dam-1207817818|title=Raqqa offensive: Flood fears as SDF forces near Islamic State-held dam|publisher=[[Middle East Eye]]|date=12 January 2017|accessdate=12 January 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rudaw.net/english/middleeast/syria/040220171|title=Third phase of Raqqa campaign announced|publisher=Rudaw|date=4 February 2017|accessdate=14 February 2017}}</ref>\n\nAn ISIL attack on Jib Shair village, trying to resist SDF advances from the north, was repelled on the next day, after which the SDF advanced and captured six hamlets around it.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/isis-attack-repelled-6-hamlets-liberated/|title=ISIS attack repelled, 6 hamlets liberated|publisher=[[Hawar News Agency]]|date=11 January 2017|accessdate=11 January 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170113103747/http://en.hawarnews.com/isis-attack-repelled-6-hamlets-liberated/|archive-date=13 January 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref> The SDF later announced that their forces advancing from the Ayn Issa front and on the Qadiriya front linked up in Kurmanju village after capturing several villages over the past few days,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://rudaw.net/english/middleeast/syria/110120171|title=Two SDF fronts meet northwest of Raqqa, continue push for city|publisher=Rudaw|date=11 January 2017|accessdate=12 January 2017}}</ref> besieging a large [[Pocket (military)|pocket]] of about 45 villages and 20 hamlets.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hawarnews.com/%d8%a7%d9%84%d8%aa%d9%82%d8%a7%d8%a1-%d8%a7%d9%84%d9%85%d8%ad%d9%88%d8%b1%d9%8a%d9%86-%d9%8a%d9%85%d9%87%d9%91%d8%af-%d9%84%d8%aa%d8%ad%d8%b1%d9%8a%d8%b1-%d8%a7%d9%84%d8%b7%d8%a8%d9%82%d8%a9/|title=\u0627\u0644\u062a\u0642\u0627\u0621 \u0627\u0644\u0645\u062d\u0648\u0631\u064a\u0646 \u064a\u0645\u0647\u0651\u062f \u0644\u062a\u062d\u0631\u064a\u0631 \u0627\u0644\u0637\u0628\u0642\u0629|publisher=[[Hawar News Agency]]|date=12 January 2017|accessdate=13 January 2017|language=Arabic|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170114205845/http://www.hawarnews.com/%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AA%D9%82%D8%A7%D8%A1-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D8%AD%D9%88%D8%B1%D9%8A%D9%86-%D9%8A%D9%85%D9%87%D9%91%D8%AF-%D9%84%D8%AA%D8%AD%D8%B1%D9%8A%D8%B1-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B7%D8%A8%D9%82%D8%A9/|archive-date=14 January 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref> All of them were captured by the next day, resulting in the alliance gaining about {{convert|460|km\u00b2}} of land.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/45-villages-20-hamlets-liberated-in-raqqa-campaign/|title=45 villages, 20 hamlets liberated in Raqqa campaign|publisher=[[Hawar News Agency]]|date=13 January 2017|accessdate=13 January 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170116025445/http://en.hawarnews.com/45-villages-20-hamlets-liberated-in-raqqa-campaign/|archive-date=16 January 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref> Another village was captured by the SDF on 13 January.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/sdf-fighters-liberate-odyan-village-in-raqqa-campaign/|title=SDF fighters liberate Odyan village in Raqqa campaign|publisher=[[Hawar News Agency]]|date=14 January 2017|accessdate=14 January 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170116025446/http://en.hawarnews.com/sdf-fighters-liberate-odyan-village-in-raqqa-campaign/|archive-date=16 January 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=58995|title=Clashes in several areas in the countryside of Raqqa and aerial bombing on the countryside of Hama|publisher=}}</ref> On 15 January, the SDF progressed to Suwaydiya Kabir village,<ref>[http://syria.liveuamap.com/en/2017/15-january-sdf-progressing-to-big-suaydiya-village-near-tabqa SDF progressing to Big Suaydiya village near Tabqa Dam] Syria Live Map. 15 January 2017</ref> while ISIL launched a large-scale counter-attack against Mahmudli and a nearby village, resulting in clashes within these settlements.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=59106|title=The \"Islamic State\" organization is trying to regain areas they lost within the \"Euphrates Wrath\" operations|publisher=SOHR|date=15 January 2017|accessdate=15 January 2017}}</ref> The attack was repelled after several hours of fighting.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/isis-attack-thwarted-in-al-raqqa/|title=ISIS attack thwarted in al-Raqqa|publisher=[[Hawar News Agency]]|date=15 January 2017|accessdate=15 January 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170115100157/http://en.hawarnews.com/isis-attack-thwarted-in-al-raqqa/|archive-date=15 January 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref> The SDF captured three villages during the day,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=59123|title=Syria Democratic Forces advance in the countryside of Raqqa and continuous clashes in several areas|publisher=SOHR|date=15 January 2017|accessdate=15 January 2017}}</ref> while Suwaydiya Saghirah was also reported to be under its control again.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.syriahr.com/2017/01/15/%D9%82%D8%B5%D9%81-%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%89-%D8%B1%D9%8A%D9%81-%D8%AD%D9%84%D8%A8-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B4%D9%85%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%8A-%D9%88%D8%A7%D9%86%D9%81%D8%AC%D8%A7%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%86-%D9%81%D9%8A-%D9%82%D8%B1/|title=\u0642\u0635\u0641 \u062c\u0648\u064a \u064a\u0633\u062a\u0647\u062f\u0641 \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0627\u0628 \u0648\u0627\u0634\u062a\u0628\u0627\u0643\u0627\u062a \u0639\u0646\u062f \u0627\u0644\u0636\u0641\u0627\u0641 \u0627\u0644\u0634\u0645\u0627\u0644\u064a\u0629 \u0644\u0646\u0647\u0631 \u0627\u0644\u0641\u0631\u0627\u062a|publisher=SOHR|language=Arabic|date=15 January 2017|accessdate=17 January 2017}}</ref>\n\n===== Fourth week =====\nOn 17 January 2017, 28 Arab tribes from Raqqa announced their support for the offensive and encouraged locals to join the SDF.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://en.hawarnews.com/raqqa-tribes-declare-support-for-sdf/|title=Raqqa tribes declare support for SDF - ANHA|access-date=2017-01-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170121171806/http://en.hawarnews.com/raqqa-tribes-declare-support-for-sdf/|archive-date=2017-01-21|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/AfarinMamosta/status/821391559350423553/photo/1|title=Afarin Mamosta on Twitter|publisher=}}</ref>\n\nThe SDF attacked Suwaydiya Kabir on the next day, leading to heavy clashes in the village.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=59250|title=Violent clashes in the northern countryside of al-Tabaqa and shells target al-Fu'aa|publisher=SOHR|date=17 January 2017|accessdate=17 January 2017}}</ref> Meanwhile, it was announced that about 2,500 local fighters had joined the offensive since it began.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rudaw.net/english/middleeast/syria/17012017|title=Kurdish-led SDF repel aggressive ISIS attack|publisher=Rudaw|date=17 January 2017|accessdate=20 January 2017}}</ref> On 19 January, ISIL launched a counter-attack against Suwaydiya Saghirah, supported by mortars and heavy machine guns, killing or wounding several YPG fighters.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://aranews.net/2017/01/isis-attacks-ypg-security-centre-west-raqqa-scores-of-kurdish-fighters-killed/|archive-url=https://wayback.archive-it.org/all/20171010064806/http://aranews.net/2017/01/isis-attacks-ypg-security-centre-west-raqqa-three-kurdish-fighters-killed/|url-status=dead|archive-date=10 October 2017|title=ISIS attacks YPG security centre west Raqqa, scores of Kurdish fighters killed|publisher=[[ARA News]]|first=Siber|last=Haci|date=20 January 2017|accessdate=20 January 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.almasdarnews.com/article/isis-attacks-ypg-security-center-near-raqqa-many-casualties-reported/|title=ISIS attacks YPG security center near Raqqa, many casualties reported|publisher=[[al-Masdar News]]|first=Paul|last=Antonopoulos|date=19 January 2017|accessdate=20 January 2017}}</ref> Despite this, the SDF made further progress on the next day, capturing a village and advancing against many other ISIL-held villages.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=59412|title=The Syria Democratic Forces achieve a new advancement in the countryside of Raqqa and shelling renewed on the Eastern Ghouta|publisher=SOHR|date=20 January 2017|accessdate=20 January 2017}}</ref> The SDF again attacked Suwaydiya Kabir on 20 January, reaching the outskirts of the village, and captured it on 22 January after heavy clashes, with the support of U.S. special forces.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://aranews.net/2017/01/sdf-forces-expel-isis-from-strategic-town-near-raqqa-advance-towards-tabqa-dam/|title=SDF forces expel ISIS from strategic town near Raqqa, advance towards Tabqa Dam|work=ARA News|date=23 January 2017|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170125203851/http://aranews.net/2017/01/sdf-forces-expel-isis-from-strategic-town-near-raqqa-advance-towards-tabqa-dam/|archivedate=25 January 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=59600|title=The Syria Democratic Forces and US Special Forces are making a significant advancement towards the Euphrates Dam and near it, and seek to secure their way towards it|work=SOHR|date=22 January 2017}}</ref>\n\n==== Tabqa Dam raid and further SDF advances in the north ====\n[[File:The Tabqa Dam.png|thumb|right|The [[Tabqa Dam]] in 2014]]\nIn late January 2017, it was reported that a number of ISIL militants were hiding inside the structure of the [[Tabqa Dam]], including senior militant leaders who used to be \"very important prisoners\" wanted by the US and several other countries, in order to deter a possible US-led coalition strike on them.{{citation needed|date=February 2020}}\n\n{{anchor|Al-Tabqa Dam Raid}}\nOn 23 January, the SDF began to advance on the Tabqa Dam, spurring ISIL to open its turbines to raise the [[Euphrates]] River's water levels. This was seen as an attempt to hinder the progress of the Kurdish-led forces and a scare tactic,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://syriadirect.org/news/%E2%80%98if-the-euphrates-river-rises-any-more-it-will-submerge-huge-swathes-of-agricultural-land%E2%80%99-islamic-state-opens-turbines-of-syria%E2%80%99s-largest-dam/|title='If the Euphrates River rises any more, it will submerge huge swathes of agricultural land': Islamic State opens turbines of Syria's largest dam|author1=Mohammad Abdulssattar Ibrahim|author2=Tariq Adely|work=SYRIA:direct|date=23 January 2017}}</ref> and caused the water level of the Euphrates to rise to its highest level in 20 years, leading to record flooding downstream.<ref name=\"A Bay of Pigs in the making\">{{cite web|url=https://www.limacharlienews.com/op-ed/trumps-middle-eastern-war-a-bay-of-pigs-in-the-making/|title=Trump's Middle Eastern War, A Bay of Pigs in the making|first=John|last=Sjoholm|publisher=Lima Charlie|date=8 February 2017|accessdate=8 March 2017}}</ref> Coinciding with this, pro-SDF sources reported that US special forces and SDF units had launched a raid against [[Al-Thawrah]] across the river.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://southfront.org/us-special-forces-ypg-units-conduct-saboteur-raid-against-isis-in-tabqa/|title=US Special Forces & YPG Units Conduct Saboteur Raid Against ISIS In Tabqa|work=South Front|date=23 January 2017}}</ref> By 24 January, the SDF managed to capture parts of the town, and they began to work towards the Tabqa Dam's control rooms, at the southern part of the dam, in an attempt to stop the massive outflow of water released by ISIL. However, the entrance to the dam's control rooms was too well defended, and with the continued threat of disastrous flooding downstream, SDF and the US forces withdrew from both the Tabqa Dam and the town of Al-Thawrah, after which ISIL closed the dam's turbines again.<ref name=\"A Bay of Pigs in the making\" />\n\nOver the next three days, ISIL repeatedly launched fierce counter-attacks against SDF positions in the western and northern countryside.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=59746|title=7 SDF fighters were killed in battles at the western and northern countryside of Raqqa|publisher=SOHR|date=24 January 2017|accessdate=26 January 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=59764|title=Casualties in violent counter attacks in the western countryside of Raqqa|publisher=SOHR|date=25 January 2017|accessdate=26 January 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=59857|title=Clashes continue in Raqqa and Aerial bombardment targets Der-Ezzor|publisher=SOHR|date=26 January 2017|accessdate=26 January 2017}}</ref> ISIL managed to retake ground in the area around the dam,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=59776|title=IS advances in Tabaqa countryside|publisher=SOHR|date=25 January 2017|accessdate=26 January 2017}}</ref> but the attack was later repelled.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/sdf-fighters-seize-ammunition-amid-foiling-attacks/|title=SDF fighters seize ammunition amid foiling attacks|publisher=[[Hawar News Agency]]|date=25 January 2017|accessdate=26 January 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170816020932/http://en.hawarnews.com/sdf-fighters-seize-ammunition-amid-foiling-attacks/|archive-date=16 August 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n=== Preparation for the third phase ===\n[[File:SDF Guardian Armored Personnel Carrier 1.png|thumb|right|An SDF IAG Guardian [[armoured personnel carrier]] in February 2017, one of several APCs that were supplied by the United States to the SDF]]\nOn 31 January 2017, the SDF received a number of [[armoured personnel carrier]]s supplied by the US. The SDF spokesman stated that preparations for a new phase of the operation were continuing and the operation would begin in \"a few days\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.middleeasteye.net/news/kurd-led-syrian-militia-claims-trump-government-sent-armoured-vehicles-1743395167|title=Kurd-led Syrian militia says Trump sent it armoured vehicles|work=Middle East Eye|date=31 January 2017}}</ref> Meanwhile, the leader of the SDF-aligned [[Syria's Tomorrow Movement]] and its [[Syria's Tomorrow Movement#Elite Forces|paramilitary wing]], [[Ahmad Jarba]], announced that 3,000 Arab fighters under his command were training with US special forces to be deployed in the battle for Raqqa against ISIL.<ref name=\"Arab fighters\" />\n\nOn the night of 2\u20133 February, intense CJTF\u2013OIR airstrikes targeted several bridges in or near Raqqa city, destroying them as well as the local water pipelines, leaving the city without drinking water. Meanwhile, the SDF advanced against the village of Qaltah in the northern countryside,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=60272|title=Intense raids target bridges in Raqqa and information about cutting off the water of the \"Islamic State\" organization's stronghold in Syria|publisher=SOHR|date=3 February 2017|accessdate=4 February 2017}}</ref> which the coalition had already unsuccessfully attacked in November.<ref name=\"Qaltah\" /> ISIL maintenance crews managed to fix the pipelines during 3 February, restoring Raqqa's water supply.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://en.zamanalwsl.net/news/22947.html|title=Raqqa water supply restored after air strike|publisher=Zaman al Wasl|date=3 February 2017|accessdate=4 February 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=60300|title=Coalition warplanes target areas of Raqqa Countryside|author=D.H.|publisher=[[Hawar News Agency]]|date=3 February 2017|accessdate=4 February 2017}}</ref> On 3 February, 251 Arab fighters in Hasaka completed their training and joined the SDF.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/251-fighters-join-the-sdf-ranks-after-training/|title=251 fighters join the SDF ranks after training|work=Hawar News Agency|date=3 February 2017|access-date=5 February 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170816021150/http://en.hawarnews.com/251-fighters-join-the-sdf-ranks-after-training/|archive-date=16 August 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n=== Phase Three: Isolating Raqqa from its eastern countryside ===\n==== Pressing south ====\n[[File:YPG and YPJ machine gun Raqqa (February 2017).jpg|thumb|left|[[People's Protection Units|YPG]] and [[Women's Protection Units|YPJ]] fighters in combat]]\nOn 4 February, the SDF announced the offensive's third phase, aiming at capturing Raqqa's eastern countryside, and to separate Raqqa city from ISIL forces in Deir ez-Zor, though operations in the west and north would continue simultaneously.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://en.hawarnews.com/wrath-of-euphrates-have-advanced-11-km/|title=Wrath of Euphrates declares 3rd stage of al-Raqqa liberation|publisher=[[Hawar News Agency]]|date=4 February 2017|accessdate=4 February 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170207215911/http://en.hawarnews.com/wrath-of-euphrates-have-advanced-11-km/|archive-date=7 February 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref> The SDF captured a village and three hamlets to the northeast of Raqqa later that day, with clashes being reported at al-Qaltah and Bir Said.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rudaw.net/mobile/english/middleeast/syria/05022017|title=SDF make advance northeast of Raqqa, airstrikes destroy bridges south of the city|publisher=Rudaw|date=4 February 2017|accessdate=5 February 2017}}</ref> On the next day, the Kurdish-led forces captured another two villages along with a hamlet and two farms, and besieged Bir Said,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/wrath-of-euphrates-advancing-19-km-2-villages-and-a-hamlet-liberated/|title=Wrath of Euphrates advancing 19 km, 2 villages and a hamlet liberated|publisher=[[Hawar News Agency]]|date=5 February 2017|accessdate=5 February 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170614130853/http://en.hawarnews.com/wrath-of-euphrates-advancing-19-km-2-villages-and-a-hamlet-liberated/|archive-date=14 June 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=60351|title=Fighting operations of \"Euphrates Wrath\" continue in the northeastern countryside of Raqqa and more advancement for the Syria Democratic Forces|publisher=}}</ref> while especially intense airstrikes hit several ISIL targets in Al-Thawrah.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.middleeasteye.net/news/us-led-coalition-planes-blast-held-town-near-euphrates-dam-syria-475210681|title=US coalition jets blast IS-held Syrian town near Euphrates dam|publisher=[[Middle East Eye]]|date=5 February 2017|accessdate=7 February 2017}}</ref> Bir Said, along with another village, was eventually captured by the SDF on 6 February.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/wrath-of-euphrates-a-village-liberated-dozens-of-isis-killed/|title=Wrath of Euphrates: a village liberated, dozens of ISIS killed|publisher=[[Hawar News Agency]]|date=6 February 2017|accessdate=6 February 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170811005459/http://en.hawarnews.com/wrath-of-euphrates-a-village-liberated-dozens-of-isis-killed/|archive-date=11 August 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.syriahr.com/2017/02/06/%d9%86%d8%ad%d9%88-10-%d9%82%d8%aa%d9%84%d9%89-%d8%ae%d9%84%d8%a7%d9%84-%d8%aa%d9%82%d8%af%d9%85-%d9%82%d9%88%d8%a7%d8%aa-%d8%b3%d9%88%d8%b1%d9%8a%d8%a7-%d8%a7%d9%84%d8%af%d9%8a%d9%85%d9%82%d8%b1/|title=\u0646\u062d\u0648 10 \u0642\u062a\u0644\u0649 \u062e\u0644\u0627\u0644 \u062a\u0642\u062f\u0645 \u0642\u0648\u0627\u062a \u0633\u0648\u0631\u064a\u0627 \u0627\u0644\u062f\u064a\u0645\u0642\u0631\u0627\u0637\u064a\u0629 \u0641\u064a \u0631\u064a\u0641 \u0627\u0644\u0631\u0642\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u0634\u0645\u0627\u0644\u064a \u0627\u0644\u0634\u0631\u0642\u064a |publisher=SOHR|date=6 February 2017|accessdate=6 February 2017|language=Arabic}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/mishrafa-village-liberated-after-violent-clashes/|title=Mishrafa village liberated after violent clashes|publisher=[[Hawar News Agency]]|author=J.O.|date=7 February 2017|accessdate=7 February 2017}}</ref> In addition to these villages, the SDF also captured another five villages on two fronts.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/strong-clashes-in-makmen-and-khanez-fronts/|title=Strong clashes in Makmen and Khanez fronts|publisher=[[Hawar News Agency]]|author=D.H.|date=7 February 2017|accessdate=7 February 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170811010014/http://en.hawarnews.com/strong-clashes-in-makmen-and-khanez-fronts/|archive-date=11 August 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref> The SDF made further progress, capturing three more villages on 7 February.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://stepagency-sy.net/archives/130969|title=\u0645\u0644\u062e\u0635 \u0627\u0644\u0631\u0642\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u064a\u0648\u0645\u064a 7-2-2017 |publisher=Step News Agency|date=7 February 2017|accessdate=7 February 2017|language=Arabic}}</ref> In early February 2017, US-led coalition airstrikes destroyed much of the Deir ez-Zor-Raqqa highway, reducing it to a single-file gravel road in some spots, with the SDF patrolling other areas with minefields, in order to prevent ISIL from reinforcing Raqqa city.<ref name=\"A Bay of Pigs in the making\" /> By this point, almost all of the five bridges leading to Raqqa had been destroyed either by the US-led coalition or by ISIL, with the only exceptions being the Tabqa Dam and the Baath Dam, both west of Raqqa city.<ref name=\"accelerating\">{{cite web|url=http://www.washingtoninstitute.org/policy-analysis/view/the-campaign-to-retake-raqqa-is-accelerating|title=The Campaign to Retake Raqqa Is Accelerating|publisher=}}</ref>\n\nAs these advances continued, ISIL responded by launching several unsuccessful counter-attacks against Suwaydiya Kabir and other strategic territories captured by the SDF.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=60456 |title=Clashes continue in Raqqa countryside between SDF and IS|publisher=SOHR|date=7 February 2017|accessdate=6 February 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/isis-attacks-foiled-on-northeast-of-al-tabqa-dam/|title=ISIS attacks foiled on northeast of al-Tabqa Dam|author=J.O.|publisher=[[Hawar News Agency]]|date=9 February 2017|accessdate=9 February 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170811005828/http://en.hawarnews.com/isis-attacks-foiled-on-northeast-of-al-tabqa-dam/|archive-date=11 August 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref> On 8 and 9 February, the SDF advanced at the northern and northeastern frontline, capturing several villages and besieging Mizella, a major strategic ISIL stronghold in the northern countryside. The advance put them within {{convert|11|km|mi}} of Raqqa.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/al-raqqa-is-encircled-from-3-axes-by-wrath-of-euphrates/|title=Al-Raqqa is encircled from 3 axes by Wrath of Euphrates|author=J.O.|publisher=[[Hawar News Agency]]|date=9 February 2017|accessdate=9 February 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170810210316/http://en.hawarnews.com/al-raqqa-is-encircled-from-3-axes-by-wrath-of-euphrates/|archive-date=10 August 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://en.zamanalwsl.net/news/23124.html|title=SDF forces make new gains north of Raqqa as ISIS retreats: spokeswoman |publisher=Zaman al-Wasl|date=8 February 2017|accessdate=9 February 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/wrath-of-euphrates-is-11km-away-from-al-raqqa/|title=Wrath of Euphrates is 11km away from al-Raqqa|author=D.H.|publisher=[[Hawar News Agency]]|date=8 February 2017|accessdate=9 February 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170211035313/http://en.hawarnews.com/wrath-of-euphrates-is-11km-away-from-al-raqqa/|archive-date=11 February 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/raqqa-campaign-sninh-village-liberated/|title=Raqqa campaign: Sninh village liberated|publisher=[[Hawar News Agency]]|date=9 February 2017|accessdate=9 February 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170211155239/http://en.hawarnews.com/raqqa-campaign-sninh-village-liberated/|archive-date=11 February 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://aranews.org/2017/02/%d9%82%d8%b3%d8%af-%d8%aa%d8%b3%d9%8a%d8%b7%d8%b1-%d8%b9%d9%84%d9%89-%d9%82%d8%b1%d9%8a%d8%a9-%d8%ac%d8%af%d9%8a%d8%af%d8%a9-%d8%b4%d8%b1%d9%82-%d8%a7%d9%84%d8%b1%d9%82%d8%a9/|title=\"\u0642\u0633\u062f\" \u062a\u0633\u064a\u0637\u0631 \u0639\u0644\u0649 \u0642\u0631\u064a\u0629 \u062c\u062f\u064a\u062f\u0629 \u0634\u0631\u0642 \u0627\u0644\u0631\u0642\u0629|publisher=ARA News|date=9 February 2017|accessdate=9 February 2017|language=Arabic}}</ref> The SDF captured Mizella the next day.<ref name=\"ground\" /><ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.syriahr.com/2017/02/10/%d9%82%d9%88%d8%a7%d8%aa-%d8%b3%d9%88%d8%b1%d9%8a%d8%a7-%d8%a7%d9%84%d8%af%d9%8a%d9%85%d9%82%d8%b1%d8%a7%d8%b7%d9%8a%d8%a9-%d8%aa%d8%aa%d9%82%d8%af%d9%85-%d8%b6%d9%85%d9%86-%d8%a7%d9%84%d9%85%d8%b1/|title= \u0642\u0648\u0627\u062a \u0633\u0648\u0631\u064a\u0627 \u0627\u0644\u062f\u064a\u0645\u0642\u0631\u0627\u0637\u064a\u0629 \u062a\u062a\u0642\u062f\u0645 \u0636\u0645\u0646 \u0627\u0644\u0645\u0631\u062d\u0644\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u062b\u0627\u0644\u062b\u0629 \u0645\u0646 \u0639\u0645\u0644\u064a\u0629 \"\u063a\u0636\u0628 \u0627\u0644\u0641\u0631\u0627\u062a\"|publisher=Syrian Observatory for Human Rights|date=10 February 2017 |accessdate=11 February 2017 |language=Arabic}}</ref> The two fronts of the alliance converged on 11 February as it also captured two villages and wheat silos to the north of Raqqa during the day;<ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/mulihan-and-badraniye-villages-liberation/|title=Mulihan and Badraniye villages liberation - ANHA|access-date=2017-02-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170212091401/http://en.hawarnews.com/mulihan-and-badraniye-villages-liberation/|archive-date=2017-02-12|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/raqqa-campaign-khaniz-and-makman-fronts-meet/|title=Raqqa campaign: Khaniz and Makman fronts meet|publisher=[[Hawar News Agency]]|date=11 February 2017|accessdate=11 February 2017|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170213192642/http://en.hawarnews.com/raqqa-campaign-khaniz-and-makman-fronts-meet/|archivedate=13 February 2017}}</ref> the next day, the SDF attempted to cross the [[Balikh River]] northeast of Raqqa, leading to heavy fighting with local ISIL defenders.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=60721|title=Airstrikes targets Raqqa countryside with attempts to reduce the advancement distance towards Raqqa city|publisher=SOHR|date=12 February 2017 |accessdate=12 February 2017}}</ref> On 12 February, a large-scale counter-attack by ISIL reportedly succeeded in retaking Suwaydiya Kabir and four other nearby villages.<ref name=\"violent\">{{cite web |url=http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=60791|title=Violent attacks by the \"Islamic State\" organization at the Euphrates banks in the northern countryside of al-Tabaqa result in its advance at the expense of Syria Democratic Forces|publisher=SOHR|date=13 February 2017|accessdate=13 February 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"counter\">{{cite web |url=https://www.almasdarnews.com/article/isis-launches-massive-counter-offensive-western-raqqa/|title=ISIS launches massive counter-offensive in western Raqqa|first=Leith|last=Fadel |publisher=[[al-Masdar News]]|date=13 February 2017|accessdate=13 February 2017}}</ref> However, pro-YPG sources denied these reports.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://southfront.org/isis-attacks-us-backed-forces-regains-village-west-of-raqqah/|title=ISIS attacks US-backed forces, regains village west of Raqqah - Reports|publisher=South Front|date=13 February 2017 |accessdate=13 February 2017}}</ref> Another counterattack was carried out by ISIL to the northeast of Raqqa where the SDF had advanced to, leading to heavy clashes between both sides.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=60833|title=The \"Islamic State\" organization carries out a counter attack northeast Al-Raqqah city to keep forces of \"Euphrates Wrath\" away of its stronghold in Syria|publisher=SOHR|date=13 February 2017|accessdate=14 February 2017}}</ref> Clashes continued over the next few days.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=60990|title=The \"Islamic State\" organization attacks sites of the Syria Democratic Forces in the countryside of Al-Hasakah and fighting continues in the countryside of Al-Raqqah |publisher=SOHR|date=16 February 2017 |accessdate=17 February 2017}}</ref>\n\n==== Capturing the eastern countryside ====\n[[File:Euphrates bridge in Deir ez-Zor Governorate during Raqqa offensive (2017).png|thumb|right|A destroyed bridge over the [[Euphrates]] in [[Deir ez-Zor Governorate]]. As a result of the [[Combined Joint Task Force \u2013 Operation Inherent Resolve|CJTF\u2013OIR]] bombing campaign, as well as ISIL detonations, most bridges across the river were destroyed.]]\nOn 17 February 2017, the SDF announced the launch of the second stage of the third phase, aimed at capturing the eastern countryside of Raqqa near [[Deir ez-Zor]], with the [[Syrian Democratic Forces military councils#Deir Ezzor|Deir Ezzor Military Council]] leading the operation.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/second-step-of-operation-wrath-of-euphrates-launched-in-third-phase/|title=Second step of Operation Wrath of Euphrates launched in third phase|publisher=ANHA|date=17 February 2017|accessdate=17 February 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170218065305/http://en.hawarnews.com/second-step-of-operation-wrath-of-euphrates-launched-in-third-phase/|archive-date=18 February 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref> On the same day the SDF captured two villages from ISIL to the north of Deir ez-Zor and came within {{convert|6|km|mi}} of the northeast of Raqqa,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.almasdarnews.com/article/kurdish-forces-overrun-two-isis-held-villages-north-deir-ezzor/|title=Kurdish forces overrun two ISIS-held villages north of Deir Ezzor |publisher=Al-Masdar News|date=17 February 2017|accessdate=17 February 2017}}</ref> while the [[Russian Air Force]] conducted airstrikes on ISIL forces in Raqqa city for the second time since its entry into the war.<ref name=\"Russia\" /> The next day, the SDF captured another village to the southwest of the Makman front (north of Deir ez-Zor) as well as another near Raqqa.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/joyce-village-liberated-a-bomb-laden-vehicle-destroyed/|title=Joyce village liberated, a bomb-laden vehicle destroyed|publisher=[[Hawar News Agency]]|date=18 February 2017|accessdate=18 February 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170219102137/http://en.hawarnews.com/joyce-village-liberated-a-bomb-laden-vehicle-destroyed/|archive-date=19 February 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/operation-wrath-of-euphates-fighters-liberate-siwehan-village/|title=Operation Wrath of Euphates fighters liberate \u015eiw\u00eahan village|publisher=[[Hawar News Agency]]|date=18 February 2017|accessdate=18 February 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170219101105/http://en.hawarnews.com/operation-wrath-of-euphates-fighters-liberate-siwehan-village/|archive-date=19 February 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref> On 18 February, the SDF stormed a prison a few kilometres northeast of Raqqa, freeing some of the inmates.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.almasdarnews.com/article/kurdish-forces-liberate-prison-outskirts-raqqa-city/|title=Kurdish forces liberate prison on the outskirts of Raqqa city|last=Tomson|first=Chris|date=2017-02-18|newspaper=[[al-Masdar News]]|access-date=2017-02-19|language=en-US}}</ref> They later captured three villages in Deir ez-Zor's northern countryside.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.almasdarnews.com/article/us-airforce-propels-the-syrian-democratic-forces-to-capture-three-villages-from-isis/|title=US Airforce propels the Syrian Democratic Forces to capture three villages from ISIS|last=Tomson|first=Chris|date=2017-02-18|newspaper=[[Al-Masdar News]] |access-date=2017-02-19}}</ref> On the next day, the SDF captured five villages to the east of Raqqa.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://southfront.org/us-backed-kurdish-forces-seize-5-more-villages-from-isis/|title=US-backed forces seize 5 more villages from ISIS|date=2017-02-19|newspaper= South Front|access-date=2017-02-19}}</ref> On 20 February, they captured four villages on the Makmen front, including the strategic village of Sebah al-X\u00ear as well as a [[base station]] of [[Syriatel]], thus cutting off the road between Makman and Raqqa and besieging three ISIL-held villages. Furthermore, the SDF took control of a significant bridge over the [[Balikh River]] on the western front.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/wrath-of-euphrates2-villages-were-liberated-20-km-advanced-forward/|title=Wrath of Euphrates:2 villages were liberated, 20 km advanced forward|date=2017-02-20|newspaper=[[Hawar News Agency]]|access-date=2017-02-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170221010201/http://en.hawarnews.com/wrath-of-euphrates2-villages-were-liberated-20-km-advanced-forward/|archive-date=2017-02-21|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/makman-al-raqqa-road-was-cut-and-a-new-village-liberated/|title=Makman-al-Raqqa road was cut and a new village liberated.|date=2017-02-20|newspaper=[[Hawar News Agency]]|access-date=2017-02-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170221010032/http://en.hawarnews.com/makman-al-raqqa-road-was-cut-and-a-new-village-liberated/|archive-date=2017-02-21|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/operation-wrath-of-euphrates-fighters-liberate-base-station/|title=Operation Wrath of Euphrates: Fighters liberate base station|date=2017-02-20|newspaper=[[Hawar News Agency]]|access-date=2017-02-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170221010116/http://en.hawarnews.com/operation-wrath-of-euphrates-fighters-liberate-base-station/|archive-date=2017-02-21|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/operation-wrath-of-euphates-terfawi-village-liberated/|title=Operation Wrath of Euphates: Terfaw\u00ee village liberated|date=2017-02-20|newspaper=[[Hawar News Agency]]|access-date=2017-02-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170221005731/http://en.hawarnews.com/operation-wrath-of-euphates-terfawi-village-liberated/|archive-date=2017-02-21|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=61184|title=Violent clashes in Al-Raqqah countryside lead to new advancement for Syria Democratic Forces|date=20 February 2017|newspaper=SOHR|access-date=28 February 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=61259|title=Warplanes carried out a massacre in the stronghold of the \"Islamic State\" organization and the Syria Democratic Forces continue advancing in the eastern countryside of Al-Raqqah|date=20 February 2017|newspaper=SOHR|access-date=28 February 2017}}</ref>\n\nOn 21 February, the SDF captured two villages on the Makman front and another one near Raqqa.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/bir-adman-village-liberated/|title=B\u00eer Adman village liberated|date=2017-02-20|newspaper=[[Hawar News Agency]]|access-date=2017-02-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170614144100/http://en.hawarnews.com/bir-adman-village-liberated/|archive-date=2017-06-14|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://en.hawarnews.com/operation-wrath-of-euphrates-quwaytar-village-liberated/|title=Operation Wrath of Euphrates: Quwaytar village liberated |date=2017-02-21|newspaper=[[Hawar News Agency]]|access-date=2017-02-21}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://en.hawarnews.com/abu-wahi-village-liberated-in-raqqa-campaign/|title=Abu Wahi village liberated in Raqqa campaign |date=2017-02-21 |newspaper=[[Hawar News Agency]]|access-date=2017-02-21}}</ref> ISIL later again assaulted Suwaydiya Kabir, attacking it from three fronts, leading to heavy fighting around it.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/heavy-clashes-in-big-siwediya-village-2/|title=Heavy clashes in Big Siw\u00eadiya village|date=2017-02-20|newspaper=ANHA|access-date=2017-02-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170614132359/http://en.hawarnews.com/heavy-clashes-in-big-siwediya-village-2/|archive-date=2017-06-14|url-status=dead}}</ref> The SDF continued advancing in the eastern countryside of Raqqa on 22 February, capturing three villages, and merging the two fronts at Makman and Bir Hebe. A YPJ commander declared that the SDF had cut the road to Raqqa and Deir ez-Zor.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/wrath-of-euphrates-progresses-the-two-wings-would-meet/|title=Wrath of Euphrates progresses, the two wings would meet|date=2017-02-22|newspaper=[[Hawar News Agency]]|access-date=2017-02-22}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/wrath-of-euphrates-two-other-villages-liberated/|title=Wrath of Euphrates: two other villages liberated|date=2017-02-22|newspaper=[[Hawar News Agency]]|access-date=2017-02-22}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/ypj-commander-our-forces-cut-the-road-to-raqqa-and-deir-ez-zor/|title=YPJ commander: Our forces cut the road to Raqqa and Deir ez-Zor|date=2017-02-22|newspaper=[[Hawar News Agency]]|access-date=2017-02-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170614171408/http://en.hawarnews.com/ypj-commander-our-forces-cut-the-road-to-raqqa-and-deir-ez-zor/|archive-date=2017-06-14|url-status=dead}}</ref> The SDF stated that it had entered [[Deir ez-Zor Governorate]] for the first time in the offensive.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.aljazeera.com/news/2017/02/backed-alliance-enters-syria-deir-al-zor-province-170222045418598.html|title=US-backed alliance enters Deir Az Zor province|date=2017-02-22|newspaper= Al-Jazeera|access-date=2017-02-22}}</ref> On the next day, they captured six villages and sixteen hamlets.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/three-more-villages-liberated-in-the-raqqa-campaign/|title=Three more villages liberated in the Raqqa campaign|date=2017-02-23|newspaper=[[Hawar News Agency]]|access-date=2017-02-23}}</ref>\n\n==== Opening of a new front ====\nOn 24 February, the SDF captured four villages in the Makman front and another three in a fourth front to the northeast of Deir ez-Zor.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/operation-wrath-of-euphrates-four-villages-liberated/|title=Operation Wrath of Euphrates: four villages liberated|date=2017-02-24|newspaper=[[Hawar News Agency]]|access-date=2017-02-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170816010513/http://en.hawarnews.com/operation-wrath-of-euphrates-four-villages-liberated/|archive-date=2017-08-16|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/sdf-fighters-liberate-3-more-villages-in-wrath-of-euphrates/|title=SDF fighters liberate 3 more villages in Wrath of Euphrates|date=2017-02-24|newspaper=[[Hawar News Agency]]|access-date=2017-02-24}}</ref> They captured the strategic [[Abu Khashab]] village later that day.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=61534|title=The Syria Democratic Forces advance in the outskirts of Deir Ezzor province to close the road between them and the stronghold of the \"Islamic State\" organization in Al-Raqqah|date=2017-02-24|newspaper= SOHR |access-date=2017-02-24}}</ref> On 25 February, they captured another three villages on the fourth front.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/the-4th-axis-advances-28-km-3-villages-were-liberated/|title=The 4th axis advances 28 Km, 3 villages were liberated|date=2017-02-25|newspaper=[[Hawar News Agency]]|access-date=2017-02-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170614182906/http://en.hawarnews.com/the-4th-axis-advances-28-km-3-villages-were-liberated/|archive-date=2017-06-14|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref name=\"auto\">{{cite news|url=https://www.almasdarnews.com/article/coalition-airstrikes-endanger-tabqa-dam-northern-syria/|title=Coalition airstrikes endanger Tabqa dam in northern Syria|date=26 February 2017|first=Zen|last=Adra|newspaper=[[al-Masdar News]]|access-date=28 February 2017}}</ref>\n\nOn 26 February, a US airstrike near Tabqa Dam destroyed a former government facility which was being used as a headquarters by ISIL. The airstrike's proximity to the dam's structure led to fears that the dam could potentially be destabilized or destroyed during the fighting.<ref name=\"auto\"/> Later that day, it was reported that the SDF had captured the village of Al-Kubar, on the northern bank of the Euphrates in the Deir ez-Zor countryside, further tightening the siege on Raqqa.<ref name=\"thousands of Kurdish troops\">{{cite web|url=https://www.almasdarnews.com/article/thousands-kurdish-troops-arrive-iraq-spearhead-deir-ezzor-offensive/|title=Thousands of Kurdish troops arrive from Iraq to spearhead Deir Ezzor offensive|first=Chris|last=Tomson|date=27 February 2017|publisher=}}</ref> On 28 February, it was reported that the US-led coalition had completely destroyed the Tabqa Airbase in an airstrike.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.almasdarnews.com/article/us-led-coalition-airstrikes-completely-destroy-al-tabqa-airbase-raqqa/|title=US-led coalition airstrikes completely destroy Al-Tabqa airbase in Raqqa|date=28 February 2017|first=Paul|last=Antonopoulos|newspaper=[[al-Masdar News]]|access-date=28 February 2017}}</ref>\n\nOn 27 February, the plan that the Pentagon submitted to US President [[Donald Trump]] to significantly speed up the fight against ISIL included a significant increase in US participation in the Raqqa campaign, with the possibility of the US increasing its ground presence on the Raqqa front to 4,000\u20135,000 troops.<ref name=\"speed up fight\">{{cite web|url=https://www.cnbc.com/2017/02/27/pentagon-delivers-plan-to-speed-up-fight-against-islamic-state.html|title=Pentagon delivers plan to speed up fight against ISIS, possibly boosting US troops in Syria|first=Jeff|last=Daniels|date=27 February 2017|publisher=}}</ref>\n\n==== Advance to the Raqqa-Deir Ezzor highway ====\n[[File:YPG-SDF fighters near the Euphrates east of Raqqa.png|left|thumb|YPG/SDF fighters on the bank of the [[Euphrates]] east of Raqqa]]\nThe offensive resumed on 5 March, with the SDF capturing at least seven villages and 15 hamlets to the northeast of the Euphrates River, east of Raqqa. The offensive had previously been paused due to bad weather, according to the SDF.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/operation-wrath-of-euphrates-six-villages-liberated/|title=Operation Wrath of Euphrates: Six villages liberated|date=5 March 2017|newspaper=Hawar News|accessdate=5 March 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170306130911/http://en.hawarnews.com/operation-wrath-of-euphrates-six-villages-liberated/|archive-date=6 March 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.voanews.com/a/us-backed-syrian-forces-resume-offensive-to-recapture-raqqa/3751039.html|title=US-backed Syrian Forces Resume Offensive to Recapture Raqqa|date=6 March 2017|newspaper=Voice of America|accessdate=6 March 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"15 hamlets\">{{cite web|url=https://www.almasdarnews.com/article/kurdish-forces-capture-15-hamlets-desert-area-east-raqqa/|title=Kurdish forces capture 15 hamlets in desert area east of Raqqa|first=Chris|last=Tomson|date=6 March 2017|publisher=}}</ref> The area captured by the SDF on that day was about 19 square kilometers, and about 32 ISIL militants were killed in the clashes.<ref name=\"continue rapid progress\">{{cite web|url=https://www.almasdarnews.com/article/kurdish-led-forces-continue-rapid-progress-rural-raqqa-isis/|title=Kurdish-led forces continue rapid progress in rural Raqqa against ISIS|first=Paul|last=Antonopoulos|date=6 March 2017|publisher=}}</ref> After further advances on 6 March, the SDF cut the highway between Raqqa and Deir ez-Zor, which was the last road out of the city,<ref name=VOAroadcut>{{cite news|url=http://www.voanews.com/a/us-backed-syrian-force-cuts-last-main-road-/3751189.html|title=US-backed Syrian Forces Cut Key Road Linking Raqqa, Deir Ezzor|first=Sirwan|last=Kajjo|date=6 March 2017|newspaper=Voice of America|accessdate=6 March 2017}}</ref><ref name=Reuterscut>{{cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-mideast-crisis-syria-raqqa-idUSKBN16D0YE|title=U.S.-backed Syrian force cuts last road out of IS stronghold|first=Tom|last=Perry|date=6 March 2017|newspaper=Reuters|accessdate=6 March 2017}}</ref> and reached the Euphrates River.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.yahoo.com/news/iraq-says-forces-retake-government-hq-bridgehead-mosul-070731475.html|title=Iraqi forces retake government HQ, museum in Mosul|author1=Tony Gamal-Gabriel|author2=Ammar Khan|work=Agence-France Presse|publisher=Yahoo! News|date=7 March 2017|accessdate=7 March 2017}}</ref> The SDF captured six villages, the Al-Kubar Military Base (a [[Operation Orchard|former nuclear facility]]), and the [[Zalabiye]] Bridge, during the day.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://aranews.net/2017/03/syrian-democratic-forces-seize-more-ground-eastern-raqqa-amidst-isis-decline/|title=Syrian Democratic Forces seize more ground eastern Raqqa amidst ISIS decline|first=Mir|last=Yaqoub|publisher=ARA News|date=7 March 2017|accessdate=7 March 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.almasdarnews.com/article/kurdish-forces-seize-military-base-isis-amid-massive-offensive-deir-ezzor/|title=Kurdish forces seize military base from ISIS amid massive offensive in Deir Ezzor|first=Chris|last=Tomson|date=6 March 2017|publisher=Al-Masdar News|accessdate=7 March 2017}}</ref> On 8 March, the SDF took control of the strategic West Menxer hill in the eastern countryside,<ref>{{cite news|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/strategic-hill-liberated-in-operation-wrath-of-euphrates/|title=Strategic hill liberated in Operation Wrath of Euphrates|date=8 March 2017|work=[[Hawar News Agency]]|access-date=8 March 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170309062538/http://en.hawarnews.com/strategic-hill-liberated-in-operation-wrath-of-euphrates/|archive-date=9 March 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref> while elements of the US [[11th Marine Expeditionary Unit]] were deployed to northern Syria, bringing with them an artillery battery of [[M777 howitzer]]s to support the attack on Raqqa.<ref name=\"marines\" /> Meanwhile, about 150 ISIL militants from Hama and Deir ez-Zor managed to reinforce Raqqa, by crossing the Euphrates, despite the partial siege that had been imposed by the SDF on the city.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=62464|title=About 150 militants in IS reach Raqqa city after a strict siege by SDF|date=8 March 2017|work=SOHR|access-date=8 March 2017}}</ref>\n\nOn 9 March, SDF captured the strategic East Menxer hill and captured three villages on two different fronts. Two villages, including Kubar, were captured on the front to the far east of Raqqa, and one near Raqqa.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/strategic-east-menxer-hill-liberated-in-raqqa-campaign/|title=Strategic East Menxer Hill liberated in Raqqa campaign|date=9 March 2017|work=[[Hawar News Agency]]|access-date=9 March 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170312005558/http://en.hawarnews.com/strategic-east-menxer-hill-liberated-in-raqqa-campaign/|archive-date=12 March 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/two-villages-liberated-in-operation-wrath-of-euphrates/|title=Two villages liberated in Operation Wrath of Euphrates|date=9 March 2017|work=[[Hawar News Agency]]|access-date=9 March 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170312005603/http://en.hawarnews.com/two-villages-liberated-in-operation-wrath-of-euphrates/|archive-date=12 March 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/operation-wrath-of-euphrates-jezera-village-liberated/|title=Operation Wrath of Euphrates: Jezera village liberated|date=9 March 2017|work=[[Hawar News Agency]]|access-date=9 March 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170312005256/http://en.hawarnews.com/operation-wrath-of-euphrates-jezera-village-liberated/|archive-date=12 March 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref> 244 Arab fighters from the Raqqa countryside also joined the SDF during the day, for the protection of the people in the region.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/244-arab-youths-graduate-and-join-sdf-ranks/|title=244 Arab youths graduate and join SDF ranks|date=9 March 2017|work=[[Hawar News Agency]]|access-date=26 March 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170326225752/http://en.hawarnews.com/244-arab-youths-graduate-and-join-sdf-ranks/|archive-date=26 March 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref> On the next day, the SDF advancing from the [[Abu Khashab]] front captured three villages, including two near Kubar.<ref name=\"2 villages near Kubar\">{{cite news|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/operation-wrath-of-euphrates-liberates-two-villages/|title=Operation Wrath of Euphrates liberates two villages|date=10 March 2017|work=[[Hawar News Agency]]|access-date=10 March 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170312060323/http://en.hawarnews.com/operation-wrath-of-euphrates-liberates-two-villages/|archive-date=12 March 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref name=\"auto1\">{{cite news|url=http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=62488|title=The Syria Democratic Forces advance in 2 villages in the eastern countryside of Al-Raqqah|date=10 March 2017|publisher=SOHR|access-date=10 March 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"auto1\"/><ref name=\"slice through\">{{cite web|url=https://www.almasdarnews.com/article/kurdish-militants-slice-islamic-state-heartland-near-raqqa/|title=Kurdish militants slice through the Islamic State heartland near Raqqa|first=Chris|last=Tomson|date=10 March 2017|publisher=}}</ref> On 12 March, the SDF captured Khas Ujayl village, to the southeast of Raqqa, on the Abu Khashab front,<ref>{{cite news|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/wrath-of-euphrates-kas-ajeyl-village-liberated/|title=Wrath of Euphrates: Kas Ajeyl village liberated|date=12 March 2017|work=[[Hawar News Agency]]|access-date=12 March 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170313124142/http://en.hawarnews.com/wrath-of-euphrates-kas-ajeyl-village-liberated/|archive-date=13 March 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=62715|title=Continued clashes in the eastern countryside of al-Raqqah city within the \"Euphrates Wrath\" operations|date=12 March 2017|work=SOHR|access-date=15 March 2017}}</ref> while ISIL continued to launch repeated counterattacks in the area, in an attempt to check the SDF advances.<ref name=\"reinforcements enter\">{{cite news|url=http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=62732|title=Violent clashes in the vicinity of the towns of Al-Fu'ah and Kafriya in the countryside of Idlib and the \"Islamic State\" organization continues its attempt to recover what it lost east of Al-Raqqah|date=13 March 2017|work=SOHR|access-date=9 March 2017}}</ref> Meanwhile, 230 ISIL fighters entered Raqqa to reinforce the city.<ref name=\"reinforcements enter\"/><ref name=\"hundreds pour in\">{{cite web|url=https://www.almasdarnews.com/article/hundreds-isis-fighters-pour-raqqa-kurdish-forces-advance/|title=Hundreds of ISIS fighters pour into Raqqa as Kurdish forces advance|first=Izat|last=Charkatli|date=11 March 2017|publisher=}}</ref>\n\nOn 14 March, the SDF captured the Khass Hibal village, as well as the Al-Kulayb grain silos, along the Raqqa-Deir Ezzor highway.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://southfront.org/us-backed-kurdish-led-forces-advance-against-isis-along-euphrates-east-of-raqqah/|title=US-backed Kurdish-led forces advance against ISIS along Euphrates east of Raqqah|publisher=South Front|date=14 March 2017|accessdate=15 March 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.almasdarnews.com/article/kurdish-forces-brink-cutting-isils-main-supply-line-raqqa-deir-ezzor/|title=Kurdish forces on the brink of cutting ISIL's main supply line from Raqqa to Deir Ezzor|first=Leith|last=Fadel|date=14 March 2017|publisher=Al-Masdar News|accessdate=15 March 2017}}</ref> An SDF spokeswoman stated that Raqqa had been isolated. The advance of the SDF put them in control of the land region used by ISIL to connect to their territories in the east, stretching from al-Kubar to the northern bank of the Euphrates and measuring {{convert|30|km|mi}}.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.al-monitor.com/pulse/originals/2017/03/syria-democratic-forces-isolate-isis.html|title=Wrath of Euphrates spokeswoman: Raqqa is now isolated|publisher=Al-monitor|date=15 March 2017|accessdate=16 March 2017}}</ref> The SDF captured the Hamad Asaf silos and al-Qulayb village the next day.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/wrath-of-euphrates-making-5-km-progress-hamad-asaf-silos-liberated/|title=Wrath of Euphrates: making 5 km progress, Hamad Asaf silos liberated|publisher=Hawar News|date=16 March 2017|accessdate=16 March 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170316204836/http://en.hawarnews.com/wrath-of-euphrates-making-5-km-progress-hamad-asaf-silos-liberated/|archive-date=16 March 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref> Hamad Assaf was also reportedly captured.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://southfront.org/us-backed-syrian-democratic-forces-captured-two-villages-east-raqqah/|title=US-backed Syrian Democratic Forces captured two villages east of Raqqah|publisher=South Front|date=16 March 2017|accessdate=16 March 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.almasdarnews.com/article/kurdish-forces-renew-push-towards-raqqa-city-two-villages-liberated-isis/|title=Kurdish forces renew push towards Raqqa city, two villages liberated from ISIS|first=Chris|last=Tomson|publisher=Al-Masdar News|date=16 March 2017|accessdate=16 March 2017}}</ref> On 17 March, a YPG commander stated that the SDF planned to storm Raqqa city in April 2017, and that the YPG would be participating in the attack, despite the fierce opposition from the Turkish government. However, [[The Pentagon|Pentagon]] Spokesman Jeff Davis denied that any decision had been made regarding when and how an assault on Raqqa city would be carried out.<ref name=\"Raqqa attack to start in April\">{{cite web|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-mideast-crisis-syria-ypg-exclusive-idUSKBN16O218|title=Exclusive: Syrian Kurdish YPG says Raqqa attack to start in early April|date=17 March 2017|publisher=|via=Reuters}}</ref> Meanwhile, clashes continued to take place around Khas Ujayl.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/violent-clashes-around-khas-ageyl-village/|title=Violent clashes around Khas Ageyl village|publisher=Hawar News|date=18 March 2017|accessdate=19 March 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170320053408/http://en.hawarnews.com/violent-clashes-around-khas-ageyl-village/|archive-date=20 March 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=63086|title=Clashes continue between IS and SDF in Raqqa and Hasakah|publisher=SOHR|date=18 March 2017|accessdate=19 March 2017}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Al-Karama during Raqqa offensive (early 2017).png|right|thumb|The town of [[Al-Karamah, Raqqa Governorate|al-Karama]], after the SDF had captured it from ISIL]]\nHeavy clashes took place in the town of [[Al-Karamah, Raqqa Governorate|al-Karama]], to the east of Raqqa, on 19 March.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/a-big-part-of-al-karama-town-is-liberated/|title=A big part of al-Karama town is liberated|publisher=Hawar News|date=19 March 2017|accessdate=19 March 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170614080749/http://en.hawarnews.com/a-big-part-of-al-karama-town-is-liberated/|archive-date=14 June 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=63150|title=Airstrikes on al-Raqqa's countryside cause more casualties and clashes continue in the east|publisher=SOHR|date=19 March 2017|accessdate=20 March 2017}}</ref> On the next day, SDF captured al-Karama, along with Jarqa village as well as a train station and water pumping station nearby.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=63207|title= The \"Euphrates Wrath\" operations continue in the eastern countryside of the capital and SDF advance more|publisher=SOHR|date=20 March 2017|accessdate=20 March 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hawarnews.com/%d8%aa%d8%ad%d8%b1%d9%8a%d8%b1-%d9%82%d8%b1%d9%8a%d8%a9-%d8%ac%d8%b1%d9%82%d8%a7-%d8%a7%d9%84%d8%aa%d8%a7%d8%a8%d8%b9%d8%a9-%d9%84%d8%a8%d9%84%d8%af%d8%a9-%d8%a7%d9%84%d9%83%d8%b1%d8%a7%d9%85%d8%a9/|title=\u062a\u062d\u0631\u064a\u0631 \u0642\u0631\u064a\u0629 \u062c\u0631\u0642\u0627 \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0627\u0628\u0639\u0629 \u0644\u0628\u0644\u062f\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u0643\u0631\u0627\u0645\u0629 \u0645\u0646 \u0645\u0631\u062a\u0632\u0642\u0629 \u062f\u0627\u0639\u0634|publisher=Hawar News|date=20 March 2017|accessdate=20 March 2017|language=Arabic|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170321082655/http://www.hawarnews.com/%d8%aa%d8%ad%d8%b1%d9%8a%d8%b1-%d9%82%d8%b1%d9%8a%d8%a9-%d8%ac%d8%b1%d9%82%d8%a7-%d8%a7%d9%84%d8%aa%d8%a7%d8%a8%d8%b9%d8%a9-%d9%84%d8%a8%d9%84%d8%af%d8%a9-%d8%a7%d9%84%d9%83%d8%b1%d8%a7%d9%85%d8%a9/|archive-date=21 March 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/wrath-of-euphrates-a-train-station-liberated/|title=Wrath of Euphrates: a train station liberated|publisher=Hawar News|date=20 March 2017|accessdate=20 March 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170321082612/http://en.hawarnews.com/wrath-of-euphrates-a-train-station-liberated/|archive-date=21 March 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hawarnews.com/%d8%aa%d8%ad%d8%b1%d9%8a%d8%b1-%d9%85%d8%ad%d8%b7%d8%a9-%d8%b6%d8%ae-%d9%85%d9%8a%d8%a7%d9%87-%d8%a7%d9%84%d9%85%d8%ad%d9%85%d8%af%d9%8a%d8%a9/|title=\u062a\u062d\u0631\u064a\u0631 \u0645\u062d\u0637\u0629 \u0636\u062e \u0645\u064a\u0627\u0647 \u0627\u0644\u0645\u062d\u0645\u062f\u064a\u0629|publisher=Hawar News|date=20 March 2017|accessdate=20 March 2017|language=Arabic|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170321082411/http://www.hawarnews.com/%D8%AA%D8%AD%D8%B1%D9%8A%D8%B1-%D9%85%D8%AD%D8%B7%D8%A9-%D8%B6%D8%AE-%D9%85%D9%8A%D8%A7%D9%87-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D8%AD%D9%85%D8%AF%D9%8A%D8%A9/|archive-date=21 March 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://southfront.org/us-backed-kurdish-forces-seized-karamah-town-east-of-raqqah/|title=US-backed Kurdish forces seized Karamah town east of Raqqah|publisher=South Front|date=20 March 2017|accessdate=20 March 2017}}</ref> On 21 March, it was reported again that the SDF had captured Hamad Assaf in the eastern countryside from the Abu Khashab front.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/peration-wrath-of-euphrates-hemed-asaf-liberated/|title=Operation Wrath of Euphrates: Hemed Asaf liberated|publisher=Hawar News|date=22 March 2017|accessdate=22 March 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170615123410/http://en.hawarnews.com/peration-wrath-of-euphrates-hemed-asaf-liberated/|archive-date=15 June 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref name=HamadAssaf>{{cite web|url=http://www.syriahr.com/2017/03/22/%d8%a7%d9%86%d9%81%d8%ac%d8%a7%d8%b1-%d9%85%d9%81%d8%ae%d8%ae%d8%a9-%d8%a8%d8%b1%d9%8a%d9%81-%d8%a7%d9%84%d8%ad%d8%b3%d9%83%d8%a9-%d9%88%d8%aa%d9%88%d8%a7%d8%b5%d9%84-%d8%a7%d9%84%d9%85%d8%b9%d8%a7/|title= \u0627\u0646\u0641\u062c\u0627\u0631 \u0645\u0641\u062e\u062e\u0629 \u0628\u0631\u064a\u0641 \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0633\u0643\u0629 \u0648\u062a\u0648\u0627\u0635\u0644 \u0627\u0644\u0645\u0639\u0627\u0631\u0643 \u0628\u0631\u064a\u0641 \u0627\u0644\u0631\u0642\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u0634\u0631\u0642\u064a |publisher=SOHR|date=22 March 2017|accessdate=22 March 2017|language=Arabic}}</ref> Another village was captured on 22 March from the Abu Khashab front.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/operation-wrath-of-euphrates-cedidit-mexyet-liberated/|title=Operation Wrath of Euphrates: Ced\u00eedit Mexyet liberated|publisher=Hawar News|date=22 March 2017|accessdate=22 March 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170323233502/http://en.hawarnews.com/operation-wrath-of-euphrates-cedidit-mexyet-liberated/|archive-date=23 March 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref name=HamadAssaf/> Meanwhile, [[Syrian Observatory for Human Rights]] (SOHR) and [[Raqqa is Being Slaughtered Silently]] (RIBSS) stated that coalition airstrikes hit a school being used as a shelter for displaced people in a village to the west of Raqqa on 20 March. SOHR stated that 33 civilians were killed in the airstrikes while RIBSS stated that it was unknown what happened to 50 families who were there.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-39350475|title=IS conflict: Strike on Raqqa school 'kills displaced civilians'|publisher=BBC|date=22 March 2017|accessdate=22 March 2017}}</ref> The SDF continued advancing in the eastern Raqqa countryside on 23 March, capturing two more villages on the Abu Khashab front, allowing them to capture a small ISIL [[Pocket (military)|pocket]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/sdf-liberates-misharfit-al-shihnat-village/|title=SDF liberates Misharfit al-Shihnat village|publisher=Hawar News|date=23 March 2017|accessdate=23 March 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170324083957/http://en.hawarnews.com/sdf-liberates-misharfit-al-shihnat-village/|archive-date=24 March 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/al-xasansiye-village-liberated-progress-continues/|title=Al-Xasansiye village liberated, progress continues|publisher=Hawar News|date=24 March 2017|accessdate=24 March 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170325201552/http://en.hawarnews.com/al-xasansiye-village-liberated-progress-continues/|archive-date=25 March 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=63361|title=Syria Democratic Forces advance and control new villages in the eastern countryside of Al-Raqqah|publisher=SOHR|date=24 March 2017|accessdate=24 March 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"developing advance\">{{cite web|url=https://southfront.org/us-backed-forecs-developing-advance-east-of-raqqah/|title=US-Backed Forecs Developing Advance East Of Raqqah|date=24 March 2017|publisher=}}</ref> On 24 March, the SDF took control of two more villages in the eastern countryside of Raqqa.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/farsat-abdulismail-village-liberated-in-wrath-of-euphrates/|title=Farsat Abd\u00fblismail village liberated in Wrath of Euphrates|date=24 March 2017|accessdate=24 March 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170325201451/http://en.hawarnews.com/farsat-abdulismail-village-liberated-in-wrath-of-euphrates/|archive-date=25 March 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.syriahr.com/2017/03/24/%d9%85%d8%b9%d8%a7%d8%b1%d9%83-%d8%ba%d8%b6%d8%a8-%d8%a7%d9%84%d9%81%d8%b1%d8%a7%d8%aa-%d8%aa%d8%aa%d9%88%d8%a7%d8%b5%d9%84-%d9%88%d9%82%d9%88%d8%a7%d8%aa-%d8%b3%d9%88%d8%b1%d9%8a%d8%a7-%d8%a7/|title=\u0645\u0639\u0627\u0631\u0643 \"\u063a\u0636\u0628 \u0627\u0644\u0641\u0631\u0627\u062a\" \u062a\u062a\u0648\u0627\u0635\u0644 \u0648\u0642\u0648\u0627\u062a \u0633\u0648\u0631\u064a\u0627 \u0627\u0644\u062f\u064a\u0645\u0642\u0631\u0627\u0637\u064a\u0629 \u062a\u062a\u0642\u062f\u0645 \u0639\u0644\u0649 \u0636\u0641\u0627\u0641 \u0627\u0644\u0641\u0631\u0627\u062a \u0627\u0644\u0634\u0645\u0627\u0644\u064a\u0629|publisher=SOHR|date=24 March 2017|accessdate=24 March 2017|language=Arabic}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://southfront.org/kurdish-forces-supported-by-us-led-coalition-capture-more-villages-from-isis/|title=Kurdish forces supported by US-led coalition capture more villages from ISIS|date=24 March 2017|accessdate=26 March 2017}}</ref>\n\n=== Battle for al-Tabqa countryside and other advances ===\n{{See also|Battle of Tabqa (2017)#Assault on Tabqa Dam and Tabqa Airbase}}\n[[File:SDF fighters near Tabqa Dam.png|left|thumb|SDF fighters near [[Tabqa Dam]] on 27 March]]\nOn 22 March, the SDF began an assault to capture the Tabqa Dam, [[al-Thawrah]] (Tabqa) city, and its airbase. Five hundred SDF fighters and five hundred US Special Forces from CJTF\u2013OIR were airlifted by helicopters of the United States military, across the Euphrates River and [[Lake Assad]], and were dropped on the Shurfa Peninsula to the west of Al-Thawrah. The attack was supported by artillery support from United States Marines, as well as air support.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://edition.cnn.com/2017/03/22/politics/syria-tabqa-dam/|title=US joins first air assault 'behind enemy lines' against ISIS in Syria|author1=Barbara Starr|author2=Zachary Cohen|author3=Ryan Browne|publisher=CNN|date=22 March 2017|accessdate=22 March 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rudaw.net/english/middleeast/syria/22032017|title=Coalition airdrops SDF and US forces into Tabqa for joint operation|work=Rudaw|author=|date=22 March 2017|accessdate=22 March 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.stratfor.com/sample/situation-report/syria-syrian-democratic-forces-cross-euphrates-west-raqqa|title=Syria: Syrian Democratic Forces Cross Euphrates West Of Raqqa|work=[[STRATFOR]]|date=22 March 2017|accessdate=22 March 2017|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170323132449/https://www.stratfor.com/sample/situation-report/syria-syrian-democratic-forces-cross-euphrates-west-raqqa|archivedate=23 March 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.defenseone.com/news/2017/03/the-d-brief-march-22-2017/136370/|title=Escalation in Raqqa; Inside the Trump-Saudi meeting; Lockheed to move F-16 assembly line; What's wrong with the military personnel system?; and just a bit more\u2026|work=Defense One|publisher=Atlantic Media|date=22 March 2017|accessdate=22 March 2017}}</ref> SDF and US forces also landed on the Jazirat al-'Ayd Island (or Peninsula) to the west of Tabqa Dam, capturing it as well.<ref name=\"special forces\">{{cite news|url=http://www.thetimes.co.uk/edition/world/special-forces-join-airborne-assault-on-isis-dam-stronghold-65b8xh0lj|title=Special forces join airborne assault on Isis dam stronghold|publisher=|newspaper=The Times|date=2017-03-24}}</ref> Four villages southwest of Tabqa were captured in the attack, including Abu Hurayrah, al-Mushayirafah, al-Krain, and al-Jameen. The SDF advanced towards the town of Al-Thawrah, where fliers were dropped, asking residents to stay indoors and avoid clashing against ISIL for now. These fliers were also dropped on Raqqa city.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.limacharlienews.com/mena/us-forces-tabqa-dam/|title=US forces seek to take critical Tabqa dam before ISIS uses it as a weapon of terror|first=John|last=Sjoholm|publisher=Lima Charlie News|date=22 March 2017|accessdate=22 March 2017}}</ref> An anti-ISIL coalition spokesman announced that the advance had cut off the highway linking the Aleppo, Deir ez-Zor, and Raqqa Governorates. He added that around 75-80% of the attacking force consisted of Arab fighters, with the rest being Kurds. The SDF stated that the advance was also meant to block any advance on Raqqa by the [[Syrian Arab Army]] from the west.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/idUSKBN16T1KM|title=U.S.-led coalition airdrops forces in Raqqa province|author1=Ellen Francis|author2= Tom Perry|publisher=Reuters|date=22 March 2017|accessdate=22 March 2017}}</ref>\n[[File:Tabqa refugees (2017).png|right|thumb|Refugees from [[al-Thawrah]] (Tabqa) city, who had fled from the fighting between the SDF and ISIL]]\nOn the same day, SDF and US forces stormed the Tabqa Dam, triggering \"intense\" clashes with ISIL forces. US officials stated that it may take several weeks to capture Tabqa Dam, Al-Thawrah city, and the surrounding countryside from ISIL.<ref name=\"airlifts\">{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/03/22/world/middleeast/us-airlift-raqqa-syria.html|title=U.S. Airlifts Hundreds of Militia Fighters in Attack to Cut Off Raqqa, Syria|first1=Michael R.|last1=Gordon|first2=Anne|last2=Barnard|date=22 March 2017|publisher=|newspaper=The New York Times}}</ref><ref name=\"strategic Syrian Dam\">{{cite web|url=http://www.thedrive.com/the-war-zone/8540/us-backed-forces-take-strategic-syrian-dam-to-block-isis-from-escaping-raqqa|title=US Backed Forces Take Strategic Syrian Dam To Block ISIS From Escaping Raqqa|first=Tyler|last=Rogoway|publisher=}}</ref> Airstrikes by the coalition on Tabqa city were reported to have killed about 25 civilians.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.alaraby.co.uk/english/news/2017/3/22/the-atrocities-against-civilians-that-coincided-with-londons-attack|title=The atrocities against civilians that coincided with London's attack|publisher=The New Arab|date=23 March 2017|accessdate=23 March 2017}}</ref> On 23 March, some early reports circulated that the SDF had captured Tabqa Dam from ISIL, after clashing with ISIL forces for a few hours.<ref name=\"ISIL loses Tabqa Dam\">{{cite web|url=http://www.difesaesicurezza.com/difesa-e-sicurezza/siria-isis-perde-la-diga-di-tabqa-strategica-per-la-sua-sopravvivenza/|title=Siria: Isis perde la diga di Tabqa, strategica per la sua sopravvivenza - Difesa e Sicurezza|date=23 March 2017|publisher=}}</ref><ref name=\"Tabqa Dam\">{{cite web|url=https://www.almasdarnews.com/article/sdf-captures-tabqa-dam-from-isis-in-spectacular-behind-enemy-lines-operation/|title=SDF capture Tabqa Dam from ISIS in spectacular behind enemy lines operation|first=Paul|last=Antonopoulos|date=23 March 2017|publisher=}}</ref><ref name=\"Peshmerga\" /> However, these reports were unconfirmed by other sources, with neither the SDF or [[CENTCOM]] confirming the capture of Tabqa Dam, and [[Rudaw]] reported that the SDF was still preparing to capture it.<ref name=\"ISIL loses Tabqa Dam\" /><ref name=unconfirmed>{{cite news|url=https://southfront.org/us-special-forces-capture-tabqa-dam-in-raqqah-province-unconfirmed/|title=US Special Forces, SDF capture Tabqa Dam in Raqqah province - Unconfirmed|publisher=South Front|date=23 March 2017|accessdate=23 March 2017}}</ref><ref name=unconfirmed1>{{cite news|url=http://www.rudaw.net/english/middleeast/syria/23032017|title=SDF prepares to take Tabqa dam after successful airdrop mission|publisher=Rudaw|date=23 March 2017|accessdate=23 March 2017}}</ref> SDF spokesman Talal Silo stated during the day that they were still advancing on the dam and the city and expected to attack the dam soon.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.usnews.com/news/world/articles/2017-03-23/us-backed-syrian-force-expects-to-attack-tabqa-soon|title=U.S.-Backed Syrian Force Expects to Attack Tabqa Soon|work=Reuters|publisher=U.S. News & World Report|date=23 March 2017|accessdate=24 March 2017}}</ref> Later on the same day, it was reported that ISIL was redeploying a large number of fighters from the Deir ez-Zor Province to Al-Thawrah and Raqqa city, in order to reinforce those fronts.<ref name=\"ISIL redeploys to Raqqa\">{{cite web|url=https://southfront.org/isis-reportedly-redeploys-forces-from-deir-ezzor-to-raqqah/|title=ISIS Reportedly Redeploys Forces From Deir Ezzor To Raqqah|date=23 March 2017|publisher=}}</ref> ISIL's Amaq News Agency later denied later that the SDF had captured the dam.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.almasdarnews.com/article/isis-denies-kurdish-led-forces-captured-tabqa-dam/|title=ISIS denies that Kurdish-led forces captured Tabqa Dam|first=Paul|last=Antonopoulos|publisher=Reuters|date=24 March 2017|accessdate=24 March 2017}}</ref>\n\nOn 24 March, SDF spokeswoman Jihan Sheikh Ahmed announced that they had reached the Tabqa Dam, and were fighting ISIL at its entrance.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-mideast-crisis-syria-dam-idUSKBN16V1QW|title=Syrian militia reaches Tabqa dam: SDF official|publisher=Reuters|date=24 March 2017|accessdate=24 March 2017}}</ref> The assault on the dam was spearheaded by SDF fighters who were backed by United States Special Operation Forces. According to early reports, the SDF and its allies had taken its outer perimeter, with the battle ongoing for its middle.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.limacharlienews.com/mena/tabqa-dam-mar24/|title=DEVELOPING: Joint US offensive to take back Tabqa Dam from ISIS sees gains|publisher=Lima Charlie News|date=24 March 2017|accessdate=24 March 2017}}</ref> On the same day, it was also reported that the SDF had captured 8 villages to the southwest of Al-Thawrah.<ref name=\"8 villages\">{{cite web|url=http://www.anfenglish.com/news/sdf-fighters-enter-the-eastern-neighborhoods-of-raqqa|title=ANF - Ajansa N\u00fb\u00e7eyan a Firat\u00ea|access-date=2017-03-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170326052830/http://www.anfenglish.com/news/sdf-fighters-enter-the-eastern-neighborhoods-of-raqqa|archive-date=2017-03-26|url-status=dead}}</ref> On the same day, the SDF advanced on Al-Tabqa Airbase, setting off clashes in the vicinity.<ref name=\"close in on airbase\">{{cite web|url=https://www.almasdarnews.com/article/kurdish-forces-close-isis-controlled-tabqa-airbase-amid-blitz-offensive-raqqa/|title=Kurdish forces close in on ISIS controlled Tabqa Airbase amid blitz offensive in Raqqa|first=Chris|last=Tomson|date=25 March 2017|publisher=}}</ref> Amaq meanwhile claimed SDF had withdrawn from the dam.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.almasdarnews.com/article/kurdish-forces-close-isis-controlled-tabqa-airbase-amid-blitz-offensive-raqqa/|title=Kurdish forces close in on ISIS controlled Tabqa Airbase amid blitz offensive in Raqqa|publisher=Al-Masdar News|date=25 March 2017|accessdate=25 March 2017}}</ref>\n\nOn 26 March, the SDF captured 2 villages to the east of Al-Thawrah. It was also reported that ISIL was shelling the surroundings of Tabqa Dam with heavy weaponry.<ref name=\"2 more villages east of Tabqa\">{{cite web|url=http://www.anfenglish.com/news/sdf-fighters-liberate-two-more-villages-east-of-tabqa|title=ANF - Ajansa N\u00fb\u00e7eyan a Firat\u00ea|access-date=2017-03-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170327075802/http://www.anfenglish.com/news/sdf-fighters-liberate-two-more-villages-east-of-tabqa|archive-date=2017-03-27|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/al-acel-al-sharqi-and-al-gharbi-were-liberated/|title=Al-Acel al-Sharqi and al-Gharbi were liberated - ANHA|access-date=2017-03-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170326230223/http://en.hawarnews.com/al-acel-al-sharqi-and-al-gharbi-were-liberated/|archive-date=2017-03-26|url-status=dead}}</ref> On the same day, ISIL claimed that Tabqa Dam was on the verge of collapse and that all the floodgates were closed. The dam was reported to have become inoperable, which ISIL claimed was due to Coalition bombing and artillery strikes, though the SOHR stated that the actual reasons were unknown, adding that ISIL still held its main building and turbines.<ref name=\"collapse\">{{cite web|url=https://www.almasdarnews.com/article/breaking-isis-claims-tabqa-dam-on-verge-of-collapse/|title=BREAKING: ISIS claims Tabqa Dam on verge of collapse|first=Paul|last=Antonopoulos|date=26 March 2017|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=63515|title=The strategic Euphrates Dam stops working and the \"Islamic State\" organization still controls its main buildings and turbines|publisher=SOHR|date=26 March 2017|accessdate=26 March 2017}}</ref> SDF however denied that it had been hit, while RIBSS (Raqqa is Silently Being Slaughtered) stated that ISIL was informing fleeing civilians that the dam was safe.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-39399803|title=IS conflict: Raqqa warning over 'risk to Tabqa dam'|publisher=BBC|date=26 March 2017|accessdate=26 March 2017}}</ref> Additionally, the US-led Coalition stated that the Tabqa Dam was structurally sound, and that the dam had not been targeted by any airstrikes. They also stated that the SDF controlled an emergency spillway at the northern part of the dam, which could be used in the event of an emergency.<ref name=\"not in danger\">{{cite web|url=http://www.miamiherald.com/news/nation-world/article140867338.html|title=The Latest: US claims Tabqa dam is not in danger of bursting|publisher=}}</ref> On the same day, SDF spokesman Talal Silo announced that SDF had stormed the Tabqa military airport, and had taken sixty to seventy percent of it.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/idUSKBN16X0V0|title=U.S-backed forces storm IS-held Tabqa military airport in northern Syria: spokesman|publisher=Reuters|date=26 March 2017|accessdate=26 March 2017}}</ref> They later announced that they had completely captured the Al-Tabqa Airbase, following a 24-hour battle.<ref name=\"Tabqa airbase\">{{cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/idUSKBN16X0V0|title=U.S.-backed forces capture Islamic State-held airport near Euphrates dam|author1=Angus McDowall|author2=Suleiman Al-Khalidi|publisher=Reuters|date=26 March 2017|accessdate=26 March 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"Tabqa airbase liberated\">{{cite news|url=https://www.almasdarnews.com/article/breaking-kurdish-forces-liberate-tabqa-airbase-raqqa-province/|title=BREAKING: Kurdish forces liberate Tabqa Airbase in Raqqa province|first=Chris|last=Tomson|publisher=Al-Masdar News|date=26 March 2017|accessdate=26 March 2017}}</ref><ref name=Bloomairbase/> ISIL forces stationed at Al-Tabqa Airbase were reported to have withdrawn northward, to Al-Thawrah city. Additionally, the SDF captured 2 villages near the airbase during the advance.<ref name=\"Tabqa airbase liberated\" /><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.upi.com/Top_News/World-News/2017/03/27/Syrian-militia-captures-Tabqa-airbase-from-Islamic-State/6641490612667/|title=Syrian militia captures Tabqa airbase from Islamic State|author=Andrew V. Pestano|publisher=[[United Press International]]|date=27 March 2017|accessdate=27 March 2017}}</ref>\n\n[[File:SDF boat crosses Lake Assad.png|left|thumb|A boat carrying SDF fighters across [[Lake Assad]] on 9 April 2017]]\nLate on 26 March, it was reported that the SDF had taken full control of Tabqa Dam, and that repairs on the dam by Coalition engineers had begun.<ref name=\"mission complete\">{{cite web|url=https://www.limacharlienews.com/mena/victory-joint-us-specops-take-tabqa-dam/|title=VICTORY - Mission Tabqa Dam Complete, joint US SpecOps retake vital dam from ISIS - Lima Charlie News|date=26 March 2017|publisher=}}</ref><ref name=\"takes Tabqa Dam\">{{cite web|url=http://www.yenisafak.com/en/dunya/pyd-takes-tabqa-dam-in-northern-syria-local-sources-2634310|title=PYD takes Tabqa Dam in northern Syria: local sources|first=Yeni|last=\u015eafak|publisher=}}</ref> A day later however SDF announced they were temporarily pausing their offensive for the dam.<ref name=\"stop assault\">{{cite web|url=https://www.almasdarnews.com/article/tabqa-dam-update-kurdish-led-forces-stop-assault-isis-allow-engineers-work/|title=Tabqa Dam update: Kurdish-led forces to stop assault against ISIS to allow engineers to work|first=Paul|last=Antonopoulos|date=27 March 2017|publisher=}}</ref><ref name=AJpause>{{cite news|url=http://www.aljazeera.com/news/2017/03/backed-syria-forces-pause-operations-tabqa-dam-170327112107511.html|title=U.S.-backed forces capture IS-held airport near Euphrates dam|publisher=Al-Jazeera|date=27 March 2017|accessdate=27 March 2017}}</ref><ref name=Reuterspause>{{cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/idUSL5N1H42CH|title=U.S.-backed Syrian militias say have paused military operations near Tabqa dam|first=Ellen|last=Francis|publisher=Reuters|date=27 March 2017|accessdate=27 March 2017}}</ref> Later in the day, a spokeswoman of the SDF announced that engineers who had been permitted to check the dam and its operations did not find it was damaged or malfunctioning.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/idUSKBN16Y1JG|title=Syria dam not damaged: SDF Raqqa campaign spokeswoman|first=Angus|last=McDowall|publisher=Reuters|date=27 March 2017|accessdate=27 March 2017}}</ref> SDF also captured 2 villages to the west of Raqqa on the same day.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.nrttv.com/EN/Details.aspx?Jimare=13472|title=SDF liberates two villages from ISIS west of Raqqa|publisher=NRT|date=27 March 2017|accessdate=27 March 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.voanews.com/a/us-backed-fighters-to-pause-military-action-near-syria-dam/3783289.html|title=US-backed Fighters to Pause Military Action Near Syria Dam|publisher=Voice of America|date=27 March 2017|accessdate=27 March 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/two-villages-liberated-west-of-al-raqqa/|title=Two villages liberated west of al-Raqqa|publisher=Hawar News|date=27 March 2017|accessdate=27 March 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170328195745/http://en.hawarnews.com/two-villages-liberated-west-of-al-raqqa/|archive-date=28 March 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref> It resumed the offensive against ISIL at the Tabqa Dam on 28 March.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.aljazeera.com/news/2017/03/backed-syria-forces-resume-fighting-tabqa-dam-170327173005420.html|title=US-backed Syria forces resume fighting near Tabqa dam|publisher=Al-Jazeera|date=28 March 2017|accessdate=28 March 2017}}</ref> Syrian engineers worked on the dam during a pause in the fighting to open spillways and ease the pressure on the dam. Its southern reaches were reported to be under ISIL control. ISIL claimed that the maintenance team was killed in airstrikes by the anti-ISIL coalition while the SOHR stated that it had learned that the engineer administering the dam had been killed in airstrikes along with a technician. It also stated that the group had sent 900 fighters from Raqqa to fight against the SDF advance.<ref name=\"guns silent\">{{cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/idUSKBN16Z23U|title=Guns silent as engineers work to ease pressure on Syrian dam|publisher=Reuters|date=28 March 2017|accessdate=28 March 2017|first=Rodi|last=Said}}</ref>\n\nOn 29 March, the SDF cut the road between Al-Thawrah (Tabqa) city and Raqqa. The SDF stated that ISIL had shelled the Tabqa Dam during the day, causing repair work to be temporarily paused.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-mideast-crisis-syria-raqqa-idUSKBN17019O|title=Engineers repair Syria's Tabqa dam spillways after shelling|first=Rodi|last=Said|publisher=Reuters|date=29 March 2017|accessdate=29 March 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=63701|title=Clashes renewed in the vicinity of al-Tabaqa airbase and the Syria Democratic Forces monitor the road of eastern countryside of Aleppo \u2013 al-Tabaqa \u2013 Al-Raqqah|publisher=SOHR|date=29 March 2017|accessdate=29 March 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://southfront.org/sdf-units-capture-importnant-road-near-isis-controlled-town-tabqa-raqqah-province/|title=SDF units capture important road near ISIS-controlled town in Raqqah province|publisher=South Front|date=29 March 2017|accessdate=29 March 2017}}</ref> On 31 March, the SDF attacked the town of al-Safsafah, to the east of al-Thawrah, in an attempt to besiege the city.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.almasdarnews.com/article/kurdish-forces-closing-isil-bastion-west-al-raqqa/|title=Kurdish forces closing on ISIL bastion in west Al-Raqqa|first=Leith|last=Fadel|date=31 March 2017|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=63856|title=US Special Forces and the Syria Democratic Forces continue their operation to complete the siege on al-Tabaqa city|publisher=SOHR|date=31 March 2017|accessdate=31 March 2017}}</ref> On the same day, the Ajeel tribe of Raqqa announced its support for the SDF's Raqqa campaign and sent 150 fighters.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hawarnews.com/%D8%B9%D8%B4%D9%8A%D8%B1%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B9%D8%AC%D9%8A%D9%84-%D8%A8%D8%B4%D9%8A%D9%88%D8%AE%D9%87%D8%A7-%D9%88%D8%B4%D8%A8%D8%A7%D9%86%D9%87%D8%A7-%D8%AA%D8%B3%D8%A7%D9%86%D8%AF-%D9%82%D9%88/|title=\u0639\u0634\u064a\u0631\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u0639\u062c\u064a\u0644 \u0628\u0634\u064a\u0648\u062e\u0647\u0627 \u0648\u0634\u0628\u0627\u0646\u0647\u0627 \u062a\u0633\u0627\u0646\u062f \u0642\u0648\u0627\u062a \u0633\u0648\u0631\u064a\u0627 \u0627\u0644\u062f\u064a\u0645\u0642\u0631\u0627\u0637\u064a\u0629 - ANHA|access-date=2017-04-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170426151904/http://www.hawarnews.com/%d8%b9%d8%b4%d9%8a%d8%b1%d8%a9-%d8%a7%d9%84%d8%b9%d8%ac%d9%8a%d9%84-%d8%a8%d8%b4%d9%8a%d9%88%d8%ae%d9%87%d8%a7-%d9%88%d8%b4%d8%a8%d8%a7%d9%86%d9%87%d8%a7-%d8%aa%d8%b3%d8%a7%d9%86%d8%af-%d9%82%d9%88/|archive-date=2017-04-26|url-status=dead}}</ref> The SDF announced during the day that over 220 new recruits had joined the offensive.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://southfront.org/syrian-democratic-force-storming-al-sfsafeh-town-east-of-al-tabqah/|title= Syrian Democratic Force storming Al-Sfsafeh town|publisher=South Front|date=1 April 2017|accessdate=1 April 2017}}</ref> Meanwhile, leaflets were dropped on the city calling on ISIL to surrender.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=63876|title= Leaflets call members of the \"Islamic State organization in al-Tabaqa to \"surrender\" and the clashes renewed east of the city|publisher=SOHR|date=31 March 2017|accessdate=1 April 2017}}</ref> Clashes continued in the countryside of Tabqa on next day as both sides attempted to advance.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=63944|title= Continuous violent clash between the Syria Democratic Forces and the \"Islamic State\" organization in the countryside of al-Tabaqa|publisher=SOHR|date=1 April 2017|accessdate=1 April 2017}}</ref>\n\n[[File:IRPGF fighters in Tabqa 3.jpg|thumb|right|[[International Revolutionary People's Guerrilla Forces|IRPGF]] fighters crossing [[Lake Assad]] by boat]]\nThe SDF and some activists stated on 2 April that it had repelled a major ISIL counterattack to the northeast of Tabqa city, near the Tabqa Dam and near the Tabqa airbase. They also continued to advance in villages to the east of Tabqa city.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-mideast-crisis-syria-tabqa-idUSKBN1740JS |title= U.S.-backed forces repel Islamic State attack near Syrian dam|author=Suleiman Al-Khalidi|publisher=Reuters|date=2 April 2017|accessdate=2 April 2017}}</ref> On the same day, it was reported that SDF had completely besieged Al-Thawrah (Tabqa) city, with Kurdish activists stating that 2 SDF units linked up to the east of the city.<ref name=\"Tabqa besieged\">{{cite web|url=https://www.alaraby.co.uk/english/news/2017/4/2/syrian-kurdish-arab-force-surround-is-last-stronghold-before-raqqa|title=Syrian Kurdish-Arab force 'surround' IS' last stronghold before Raqqa|first=The New|last=Arab|publisher=}}</ref><ref name=\"Tabqa city encircled\">{{cite web|url=https://www.almasdarnews.com/article/breaking-kurdish-forces-encircle-tabqa-city-isis-collapses-ourskirts-raqqa/|title=BREAKING: Kurdish forces encircle Tabqa city as ISIS collapses on outskirts of Raqqa|first=Chris|last=Tomson|date=2 April 2017|publisher=}}</ref> SOHR, however, stated that they were still trying to besiege the city.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.syriahr.com/2017/04/03/%d9%87%d8%ac%d9%88%d9%85%d8%a7%d8%aa-%d9%8a%d9%88%d9%85%d9%8a%d8%a9-%d9%85%d8%b3%d8%aa%d9%85%d8%b1%d8%a9-%d9%85%d9%86-%d9%82%d8%a8%d9%84-%d8%aa%d9%86%d8%b8%d9%8a%d9%85-%d8%a7%d9%84%d8%af%d9%88%d9%84/|title= \u0647\u062c\u0648\u0645\u0627\u062a \u064a\u0648\u0645\u064a\u0629 \u0645\u0633\u062a\u0645\u0631\u0629 \u0645\u0646 \u0642\u0628\u0644 \u062a\u0646\u0638\u064a\u0645 \"\u0627\u0644\u062f\u0648\u0644\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u0625\u0633\u0644\u0627\u0645\u064a\u0629\" \u0639\u0644\u0649 \u0645\u0637\u0627\u0631 \u0627\u0644\u0637\u0628\u0642\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0633\u0643\u0631\u064a \u0648\u0642\u0635\u0641 \u0645\u062f\u0641\u0639\u064a \u0639\u0644\u0649 \u0631\u064a\u0641 \u062f\u0645\u0634\u0642 \u0627\u0644\u063a\u0631\u0628\u064a|publisher=SOHR|date=2 April 2017|accessdate=2 April 2017|language=Arabic}}</ref> SDF fighters continued battling for Safsafah and Ibad, on the next day, to fully encircle Tabqa.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://syriadirect.org/news/flooding-reported-in-raqqa-city-amidst-struggle-for-euphrates-dam/|title= Flooding reported in Raqqa city as US-backed forces fight for Euphrates Dam|publisher=Syria Direct|date=3 April 2017|accessdate=3 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.almasdarnews.com/article/us-backed-forces-clash-isis-outside-tabqa-video-photos/|title= US-backed forces clash with ISIS outside Tabqa [Video + Photos]|first=Zen|last=Adra|publisher=Al-Masdar News|date=3 April 2017|accessdate=3 April 2017}}</ref> On 3 April, it was reported that ISIL was possibly in the process of moving its capital from Raqqa city to [[Mayadin]], in the Deir ez-Zor Governorate. This followed months of gradual relocation of resources and senior ISIL leaders from Raqqa to Mayadin.<ref name=\"Raqqa to Mayadin\">{{cite web|url=http://moderndiplomacy.eu/index.php?option=com_k2&view=item&id=2420:is-isis-moving-its-capital-from-raqqa-to-mayadin-in-deir-ez-zor&Itemid=154|title=Is ISIS Moving its Capital from Raqqa to Mayadin in Deir ez-Zor?|first=Anne Speckhard|last=Ph.D|publisher=}}</ref> SDF entered and besieged Safsafah on 5 April, thus also besieging Tabqa city while claiming that it had also taken control of a major part of Safsafah.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://southfront.org/syrian-democratic-forces-seize-al-sufsafeh-encircle-isis-stronghold-of-tabqa-videos/|title= Syrian Democratic Force seize al-Sufsafeh, encircle ISIS stronghold of Tabqa|publisher=South Front|date=5 April 2017|accessdate=5 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=64170|title= After 15 days of the airdrop missions west of it\u2026 the Syria Democratic Forces and US Special Forces besiege al-Tabaqa city|publisher=SOHR|date=5 April 2017|accessdate=5 April 2017}}</ref> The village was captured by the next day, resulting in SDF completely encircling Tabqa city.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://syriadirect.org/news/islamic-state-fighters-\u2018fully-encircled\u2019-in-tabqa-city-euphrates-dam/|title= Islamic State fighters 'fully encircled' in Tabqa city, Euphrates Dam|publisher=Syria Direct|date=6 April 2017|accessdate=6 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.middleeasteye.net/news/us-backed-fighters-surround-held-syria-town-monitor-914880225|title= US-backed fighters surround IS-held Syria town: monitor|work=Agence-France Presse|publisher=Middle East Eye|date=6 April 2017|accessdate=6 April 2017}}</ref>\n\nOn 6 April 2017, US Special Forces carried out a raid near the city of [[Mayadin]], in the Deir ez-Zor Governorate, killing Abdul Rahman al-Uzbeki, a high-ranking ISIL commander who was believed to have masterminded the [[2017 Istanbul nightclub shooting|2017 Istanbul New Year terror attack]].<ref name=\"daring US raid\" />\n\nThe SDF captured Ibad village, to the east of Safsafah, on 9 April, further expanding their control in eastern countryside of Tabqa, while more than 25 ISIL fighters were killed in the clashes.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=64550|title= The Syria Democratic Forces and US Special Forces control the second village in the eastern countryside of al-Tabaqa and kill more than 25 members of the \"Islamic State\" organization|publisher=SOHR|date=9 April 2017|accessdate=10 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://anfenglish.com/news/sdf-liberate-ibad-village-east-of-tabqa-19402|title= SDF liberate Ibad village east of Tabqa|publisher=ANF News|date=9 April 2017|accessdate=10 April 2017}}</ref> ISIL also launched unsuccessful counterattacks on Safsafah,<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.almasdarnews.com/article/us-backed-fighters-foil-isis-attack-east-tabqa/|title=US-backed fighters foil ISIS attack east of Tabqa|first=Zen|last=Adra|publisher=Al-Masdar News|date=9 April 2017|accessdate=10 April 2017}}</ref> while also attacking Al-Tabqa Airbase.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=64558|title= The violent clashes renewed near al-Tabaqa airbase in a new offensive by the \"Islamic State\" organization|publisher=SOHR|date=9 April 2017|accessdate=10 April 2017}}</ref> The SDF captured another village near Tabqa on the next day.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/al-raqqas-ayed-al-kabeer-village-liberated/|title=Al-Raqqa's 'Ayed al-Kabeer village liberated|publisher=ANHA|date=10 April 2017|accessdate=14 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170413182240/http://en.hawarnews.com/al-raqqas-ayed-al-kabeer-village-liberated/|archive-date=13 April 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://southfront.org/us-backed-forces-attemptting-to-enter-isis-held-town-of-tabqah-in-raqqah-province/|title= US-backed forces attempting to enter ISIS-held town of Tabqah in Raqqah province|publisher=SouthFront|date=11 April 2017|accessdate=14 April 2017}}</ref>\n\nOn 11 April, the US-led Coalition reported that the SDF had captured 60% of Tabqa Dam, and that they were \"very close\" to liberating the dam.<ref name=\"Tabqa Dam nearly liberated\">{{cite web|url=http://www.rudaw.net/english/middleeast/syria/10042017|title=SDF close to liberating Tabqa dam, will move into Raqqa after, says coalition rep|publisher=}}</ref><ref name=\"push back\">{{cite web|url=https://www.usnews.com/news/world/articles/2017-04-11/us-backed-forces-push-back-islamic-state-in-raqqa-campaign-officials|title=U.S.-Backed Forces Push Back Islamic State in Raqqa Campaign - Officials|publisher=}}</ref> On 13 April, the United States military stated that CJTF\u2013OIR had bombed a SDF fighting position near Tabqa as it was misidentified as belonging to ISIL. It added that the airstrikes resulted in deaths of 18 SDF fighters.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/04/13/world/middleeast/syrian-fighters-airstrike-american-military.html|title= 18 Syrian Fighters Allied With U.S. Are Killed in Coalition Airstrike|work=The New York Times|date=13 April 2017|accessdate=14 April 2017}}</ref>\n\n=== Phase Four: Offensive directly north of Raqqa city; Assault on Tabqa city ===\n{{See also|Battle of Tabqa (2017)#Battle for Tabqa city}}\n[[File:Tabqa offensive (2017).svg|upright=1.5|right|thumb|Map of the progress of the [[Battle of Tabqa (2017)|Battle of Tabqa]]]]\nOn 13 April, the SDF announced the launch of the fourth phase of the campaign. The new phase would involve capturing the entire area directly north of Raqqa city, including the Jalab valley, as well as further strengthening the siege of Raqqa city.<ref name=\"Stage 4\">{{cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/idUSKBN17F11I|title=U.S.-backed forces launch new attacks on Islamic State in Syria: statement|author1=John Davison|author2=Rodi Said|publisher=Reuters|date=13 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.laht.com/article.asp?ArticleId=2434608&CategoryId=12395|title=Syrian Militia Announces 4th Phase of Offensive against IS in al-Raqqa|publisher=Latin American Herald Tribune|date=13 April 2017}}</ref> The advancements may involve capturing the southern countryside of Raqqa as well, since the SDF stated that they plan to fully isolate the city before launching an attack on it.<ref name=\"valley north of Raqqa\">{{cite web|url=http://www.foxnews.com/world/2017/04/13/us-backed-syrian-forces-set-sights-on-valley-north-raqqa.html|title=US-backed Syrian forces set sights on valley north of Raqqa|date=13 April 2017|publisher=}}</ref><ref name=\"Stage 4\" /> A plan to attack Raqqa city itself was also scheduled to for April 2017, but it was postponed due to the Battle of Tabqa.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://komnews.org/syrian-democratic-forces-launch-latest-phase-raqqa-operation/|title=Syrian Democratic Forces launch latest phase of Raqqa operation|work=Kom News|date=13 April 2017|access-date=13 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170516162930/https://komnews.org/syrian-democratic-forces-launch-latest-phase-raqqa-operation/|archive-date=16 May 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref> SDF was reported to have captured a village in the northern countryside of Raqqa on the same day.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=64754|title=About 15 fighters were killed in clashes and explosion of an explosive belt in the countryside of Al-Raqqah and the \"Islamic State\" organization intensifies its counter attacks and booby trapped vehicles on locations of \"Euphrates Wrath\" operation|work=SOHR|date=13 April 2017}}</ref>\n\nSOHR stated early on 15 April that the SDF had advanced to the edge of Tabqa, and was within hundreds of meters of the city.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://english.aawsat.com/asharq-al-awsat-english/news-middle-east/observatory-sdf-doorstep-syrias-tabqa|title=Observatory: SDF on Doorstep of Syria's Tabqa|publisher=Asharq al-Awsat|date=15 April 2017|access-date=15 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171009225944/https://english.aawsat.com/asharq-al-awsat-english/news-middle-east/observatory-sdf-doorstep-syrias-tabqa|archive-date=9 October 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref> Later, SDF captured the village of Ayad al-Saghir near Tabqa and stormed the city itself, capturing the Alexandria suburb and bringing about 15% of the city under their control.<ref>{{cite web|title=\u0642\u0648\u0627\u062a \u0633\u0648\u0631\u064a\u0627 \u0627\u0644\u062f\u064a\u0645\u0642\u0631\u0627\u0637\u064a\u0629 \u062a\u062f\u062e\u0644 \u0636\u0648\u0627\u062d\u064a \u0645\u062f\u064a\u0646\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u0637\u0628\u0642\u0629 \u0628\u0639\u062f 24 \u064a\u0648\u0645\u0627\u064b \u0645\u0646 \u0627\u0646\u062a\u0642\u0627\u0644 \u0627\u0644\u0645\u0639\u0627\u0631\u0643 \u0625\u0644\u0649 \u0636\u0641\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u0641\u0631\u0627\u062a \u0627\u0644\u062c\u0646\u0648\u0628\u064a\u0629 \u0639\u0642\u0628 \u0639\u0645\u0644\u064a\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u0625\u0646\u0632\u0627\u0644|url=http://www.syriahr.com/2017/04/15/%d9%82%d9%88%d8%a7%d8%aa-%d8%b3%d9%88%d8%b1%d9%8a%d8%a7-%d8%a7%d9%84%d8%af%d9%8a%d9%85%d9%82%d8%b1%d8%a7%d8%b7%d9%8a%d8%a9-%d8%aa%d8%af%d8%ae%d9%84-%d8%b6%d9%88%d8%a7%d8%ad%d9%8a-%d9%85%d8%af%d9%8a/|publisher=SOHR|date=15 April 2017|language=Arabic}}</ref><ref name=\"Kurdish troops seize entire neighborhood\">{{cite web|url=https://www.almasdarnews.com/article/isis-big-trouble-kurdish-troops-seize-entire-neighborhood-tabqa-city/|title=ISIS in big trouble as Kurdish troops seize entire neighborhood in Tabqa city|first=Chris|last=Tomson|date=15 April 2017|publisher=}}</ref><ref name=\"enter Tabqa city\">{{cite web|url=http://aranews.net/2017/04/sdf-forces-enter-taqba-city-16-isis-fighters-killed/|title=SDF forces enter Taqba city, 16 ISIS fighters killed - ARA News|date=16 April 2017|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170517053616/http://aranews.net/2017/04/sdf-forces-enter-taqba-city-16-isis-fighters-killed/|archivedate=17 May 2017}}</ref> They also cleared the Mushayrifah village near Tabqa, killing 27 ISIL fighters.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://anfenglish.com/news/27-isis-members-killed-in-misharfa-village-near-tabqa-19513|title=27 ISIS members killed in Misharfa village near Tabqa|publisher=ANF News|date=15 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.almasdarnews.com/article/breaking-kurdish-forces-storm-isis-bastion-western-raqqa/|title=BREAKING: Kurdish forces storm ISIS bastion in western Raqqa|publisher=Al-Masdar News|date=15 April 2017}}</ref>\n\n[[File:IRPGF fighters in Tabqa 1.jpg|left|thumb|A [[International Revolutionary People's Guerrilla Forces|IRPGF]] fighter during the [[Battle of Tabqa (2017)|Battle for]] [[Al-Thawrah|Tabqa city]]]]\nOn 17 April, the SDF captured three villages in the northern countryside of Raqqa, and four hamlets.<ref name=\"3 villages en route\">{{cite web|url=https://www.almasdarnews.com/article/kurdish-troops-capture-three-villages-isis-en-route-raqqa-city/|title=Kurdish troops capture three villages from ISIS en route to Raqqa city|first=Chris|last=Tomson|date=17 April 2017|publisher=|accessdate=23 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=64971|title=Syria Democratic Forces advance in the 4th phase of their military operation|date=17 April 2017|publisher=SOHR}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/3-villages-and-4-hamlets-liberated/|title=3 villages and 4 hamlets liberated|date=17 April 2017|publisher=ANHA|access-date=17 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170517210156/http://en.hawarnews.com/3-villages-and-4-hamlets-liberated/|archive-date=17 May 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref> On the same day, the [[Syrian Democratic Forces military councils#Manbij|Manbij Military Council]] announced that 200 of its fighters would participate in the battle for Tabqa, with a total of 350.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/shams-al-shamal-fighters-participating-in-wrath-of-euphrates/|title=Shams al-Shamal fighters participating in Wrath of Euphrates - ANHA|website=en.hawarnews.com|accessdate=10 July 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170823023244/http://en.hawarnews.com/shams-al-shamal-fighters-participating-in-wrath-of-euphrates/|archive-date=23 August 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref name=\"manbij council\" /> SDF advanced in Tabqa city again on 17 and 18 April, also capturing an ISIL radio station.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/a-rapid-progress-towards-al-tabqa-center-made/|title=A rapid progress towards al-Tabqa center made|date=18 April 2017|publisher=ANHA}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.almasdarnews.com/article/isis-fighters-trapped-western-raqqa-kurdish-forces-seize-new-sites-inside-tabqa/|title=ISIS fighters trapped in western Raqqa as Kurdish forces seize new sites inside Tabqa|date=18 April 2017|first=Chris|last=Tomson|publisher=Al-Masdar News}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://aranews.net/2017/04/us-backed-sdf-forces-take-isis-radio-station-tabqa/|title=US-backed SDF forces take over ISIS radio station in Tabqa|date=19 April 2017|author=Wladimir van Wilgenburg|publisher=ARA News}}</ref> On 19 April, SDF captured 4 villages near Raqqa as well as other areas.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/al-hatash-village-liberated/|title=Al-Hatash village liberated|date=19 April 2017|publisher=ANHA}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://southfront.org/syrian-democratic-forces-advancing-in-al-izaa-area-in-tabqa-photos-videos/|title=Syrian Democratic Forces advancing in al-Iza'a area in Tabqa|date=19 April 2017|publisher=South Front}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=65046|title=The Syria Democratic Forces advance in several villages within the 4th stage of operations of \"Euphrates Wrath\"|date=19 April 2017|publisher=SOHR}}</ref> On 20 April, they captured at least six villages to north of Raqqa.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.syriahr.com/2017/04/20/%d9%85%d8%b9%d8%a7%d8%b1%d9%83-%d9%85%d8%b3%d8%aa%d9%85%d8%b1%d8%a9-%d8%a8%d8%b9%d9%86%d9%81-%d8%b6%d9%85%d9%86-%d8%a7%d8%b3%d8%aa%d9%85%d8%b1%d8%a7%d8%b1-%d8%a7%d9%84%d9%85%d8%b1%d8%ad%d9%84%d8%a9/|title=\u0645\u0639\u0627\u0631\u0643 \u0645\u0633\u062a\u0645\u0631\u0629 \u0628\u0639\u0646\u0641 \u0636\u0645\u0646 \u0627\u0633\u062a\u0645\u0631\u0627\u0631 \u0627\u0644\u0645\u0631\u062d\u0644\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u0631\u0627\u0628\u0639\u0629 \u0645\u0646 \u0639\u0645\u0644\u064a\u0627\u062a \"\u063a\u0636\u0628 \u0627\u0644\u0641\u0631\u0627\u062a\" \u0641\u064a \u0631\u064a\u0641 \u0627\u0644\u0631\u0642\u0629|date=20 April 2017|publisher=SOHR|language=Arabic}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=65115|title=The Syria Democratic Forces achieved a new advancement in the northern countryside of Al-Raqqah and warplanes raid on the countryside of Idlib|date=20 April 2017|publisher=SOHR}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.almasdarnews.com/article/10000-civilians-flee-tabqa-clashes-kurdish-units-capture-two-nearby-villages/|title=10,000 civilians flee Tabqa battle as Kurdish units capture villages north of Raqqa|first=Chris|last=Tomson|date=20 April 2017|publisher=Al-Masdar News}}</ref> More villages and areas were captured by the SDF north of Raqqa on 21 and 22 April, including Hazima and Mazrat Tishrin.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.almasdarnews.com/article/kurdish-pincer-offensive-cuts-off-bunch-isis-held-villages-north-raqqa/|title=Kurdish pincer offensive cuts off bunch of ISIS-held villages north of Raqqa|first=Chris|last=Tomson|date=21 April 2017|publisher=Al-Masdar News}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=65202|title=SDF seek to besiege ISIS in villages in the northern countryside of al-Raqqa |date=21 April 2017|publisher=SOHR}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.syriahr.com/2017/04/22/%d8%a3%d9%83%d8%ab%d8%b1-%d9%85%d9%86-30-%d9%82%d8%aa%d9%8a%d9%84-%d9%85%d9%86-%d8%aa%d9%86%d8%b8%d9%8a%d9%85-%d8%a7%d9%84%d8%af%d9%88%d9%84%d8%a9-%d8%a7%d9%84%d8%a5%d8%b3%d9%84%d8%a7%d9%85%d9%8a/|title=\u0623\u0643\u062b\u0631 \u0645\u0646 30 \u0642\u062a\u064a\u0644 \u0645\u0646 \u062a\u0646\u0638\u064a\u0645 \"\u0627\u0644\u062f\u0648\u0644\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u0625\u0633\u0644\u0627\u0645\u064a\u0629\" \u062e\u0644\u0627\u0644 \u0645\u0639\u0627\u0631\u0643 \u0634\u0645\u0627\u0644 \u0627\u0644\u0631\u0642\u0629 \u0648\u0642\u0648\u0627\u062a \u0633\u0648\u0631\u064a\u0627 \u0627\u0644\u062f\u064a\u0645\u0642\u0631\u0627\u0637\u064a\u0629 \u062a\u0642\u0644\u0635 \u0627\u0644\u0645\u0633\u0627\u0641\u0629 \u0644\u0623\u0642\u0644 \u0645\u0646 6 \u0643\u0644\u0645 \u0628\u064a\u0646 \u0645\u062d\u0648\u0631\u064a \u062a\u0642\u062f\u0645\u0647\u0627|date=22 April 2017|publisher=SOHR|language=Arabic}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/wrath-of-euphrates-two-towns-liberated-49-mercenaries-killed/|title=Wrath of Euphrates: two towns liberated, 49 mercenaries killed|date=22 April 2017|publisher=Hawar News|access-date=23 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170518170231/http://en.hawarnews.com/wrath-of-euphrates-two-towns-liberated-49-mercenaries-killed/|archive-date=18 May 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref> Meanwhile, it was reported that ISIL had essentially moved its capital to [[Mayadin]], in the Deir ez-Zor Governorate, and that ISIL had centered its forces in the Deir ez-Zor Governorate, thus transforming Mayadin into a \"secondary capital city\" for ISIL.<ref name=\"ISIL moves its capital\">{{cite web|url=http://www.foxnews.com/world/2017/04/21/isis-moves-its-capital-in-syria.html|title=ISIS moves its capital in Syria|first=Lucas|last=Tomlinson|date=21 April 2017|publisher=|accessdate=23 April 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"daring US raid\">{{cite web|url=https://www.almasdarnews.com/article/daring-us-airborne-raid-kills-military-advisor-isis-leader/|title=Daring US airborne raid kills military advisor of ISIS leader|first=Chris|last=Tomson|date=21 April 2017|publisher=|accessdate=23 April 2017}}</ref> On 24 April, the SDF captured the ISIL pocket to the north of Raqqa city, allowing them to gain control of 13 villages.<ref name=\"13 villages\" />\n\nBy 25 April, the SDF captured the Wahab district of Tabqa city, during a large advance in its southern and western flanks, which increased SDF control of the city to 40%. The SDF also destroyed an ISIL cell in Jazirat al-Ayd, allowing them to completely secure the island.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.almasdarnews.com/article/isis-loses-huge-numbers-tabqa-city-kurdish-forces-capture-second-neighborhood/|title=ISIS loses huge numbers in Tabqa city as Kurdish forces capture second neighborhood|first=Chris|last=Tomson|date=25 April 2017|publisher=Al-Masdar News|accessdate=25 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=65346|title=After 34 days of moving the clashes to Euphrates' west bank\u2026 SDF advance and enter outskirts of al-Tabaqa city|date=25 April 2017|publisher=SOHR|accessdate=25 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hawarnews.com/%d8%aa%d9%86%d8%b8%d9%8a%d9%81-%d8%af%d9%88%d8%a7%d8%b1-%d8%a7%d9%84%d8%b9%d9%84%d9%81-%d9%88%d8%ac%d8%b2%d9%8a%d8%b1%d8%a9-%d8%a7%d9%84%d9%85%d8%ad%d9%85%d9%8a%d8%a9-%d9%85%d9%86-%d8%a7%d9%84%d9%85/|title=\u062a\u0646\u0638\u064a\u0641 \u062f\u0648\u0627\u0631 \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0641 \u0648\u062c\u0632\u064a\u0631\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u0645\u062d\u0645\u064a\u0629 \u0645\u0646 \u0627\u0644\u0645\u0631\u062a\u0632\u0642\u0629|date=25 April 2017|publisher=ANHA |accessdate=25 April 2017|language=Arabic}}</ref> Meanwhile, the two SDF fronts north of Raqqa were reported to have joined up, following the capture of a number of villages in a former ISIL pocket.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://anfenglish.com/news/sdf-fighters-advancing-on-two-fronts-meet-19692|title=SDF fighters advancing on two fronts meet|date=25 April 2017|publisher=ANF News|accessdate=25 April 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"13 villages\">{{cite web|url=https://www.almasdarnews.com/article/kurdish-blitz-offensive-wrestles-control-13-villages-isis-northern-raqqa/|title=Kurdish blitz offensive wrestles control of 13 villages from ISIS in northern Raqqa|date=24 April 2017|publisher=Al-Masdar News|accessdate=25 April 2017}}</ref> The SDF also announced that it had captured the northern part of Julab Valley.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://aranews.net/2017/04/at-least-311-isis-jihadists-killed-by-sdf-fire-in-military-campaign-to-liberate-raqqas-northern-countryside/|title=At least 311 ISIS jihadists killed by SDF fire in military campaign to liberate Raqqa's northern countryside|date=25 April 2017|publisher=ARA News|accessdate=25 April 2017}}</ref> They announced on 28 April that they had captured the Nababila and Zahra districts of Tabqa city.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.usnews.com/news/world/articles/2017-04-28/us-backed-forces-push-against-is-in-slowed-raqqa-campaign|title=U.S.-Backed Forces Push Against IS in Slowed Raqqa Campaign|date=28 April 2017|work=Reuters|publisher=U.S. News|accessdate=28 April 2017}}</ref> Meanwhile, the YPG also threatened to withdraw from the operation to capture Raqqa, if the United States didn't take measures to stop [[Turkey]]'s attacks against the group.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nrttv.com/en/Details.aspx?Jimare=14156|title=YPG threatens to withdraw from Raqqa ops amid Turkish attacks|date=28 April 2017|publisher=NRT TV|accessdate=28 April 2017}}</ref>\n\n[[File:SDF in Tabqa 1.png|left|thumb|A SDF fighter stands in a destroyed area of [[Al-Thawrah|Tabqa city]].]]\nSDF advanced in Tabqa city again on 30 April. They stated that they had captured six more districts, and that ISIL only controlled the northern part of the city near Tabqa Dam.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-mideast-crisis-syria-tabqa-idUSKBN17W08L|title=U.S.-backed militias claim big advance against IS in Syria's Tabqa|date=30 April 2017|publisher=Reuters|accessdate=30 April 2017|first=Angus|last=McDowall}}</ref> SOHR stated that SDF controlled at least 40% of the city, including more than half of the Old City area.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.aljazeera.com/news/2017/04/kurdish-arab-force-gains-isil-tabqa-170430081216169.html|title=Kurdish-Arab force makes gains against ISIL in Tabqa|date=30 April 2017|publisher=Al-Jazeera|accessdate=30 April 2017}}</ref> Later on the same day, it was reported that the SDF had captured at least 60% of the city.<ref name=\"over half of Tabqa city\">{{cite web|url=https://www.almasdarnews.com/article/isis-defeat-western-raqqa-inevitable-kurdish-troops-seize-half-tabqa-city/|title=ISIS defeat in western Raqqa inevitable as Kurdish troops seize over half of Tabqa city|first=Chris|last=Tomson|date=30 April 2017|publisher=}}</ref> On the next day SDF stated that it had completely captured the Old City area, leaving ISIL in control of only the newer areas of the town alongside the dam. SOHR stated that they controlled about 80% of the city.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-mideast-crisis-syria-raqqa-idUSKBN17X1II|title=U.S.-backed militias oust Islamic State from Syria's Tabqa old city|date=1 May 2017|first=Lisa|last=Barrington|publisher=Reuters|accessdate=1 May 2017}}</ref>\n\nOn 2 May SDF stated that it had captured about 90 percent of the town<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.aljazeera.com/news/2017/05/kurdish-forces-90-percent-syria-tabqa-170502081348954.html|title=Kurdish forces 'take 90 percent' of Syria's Tabqa|date=2 May 2017|author=Diana al-Rifai|publisher=Al-Jazeera|accessdate=2 May 2017}}</ref> amid reports of negotiations between Kurdish fighters and ISIL to allow the latter to withdraw from the remaining areas under its control.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.alaraby.co.uk/english/news/2017/5/2/kurdish-fighters-negotiating-with-is-to-withdraw-from-tabqa|title=Kurdish fighters 'negotiating with IS' to withdraw from Tabqa|date=2 May 2017|publisher=The New Arab|accessdate=2 May 2017}}</ref> By 3 May, SDF had almost captured the whole city except a small northern area and district near the dam.<ref name=AMimpose>{{cite web|url=https://www.almasdarnews.com/article/humiliating-defeat-isis-kurdish-troops-impose-full-control-tabqa-city/|title=Humiliating defeat for ISIS as Kurdish troops impose full control over Tabqa city|date=3 May 2017|publisher=Al-Masdar News|accessdate=4 May 2017}}</ref><ref name=SOHRalmost>{{cite web|url=http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=65729|title=18 days after entering the city\u2026 the Syria Democratic Forces almost completely control al-Tabaqa and ISIS withdraw after negotiations|date=3 May 2017|publisher=SOHR|accessdate=4 May 2017}}</ref> ISIL also carried out counterattacks in and near Tabqa.<ref name=AMimpose/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.laht.com/article.asp?ArticleId=2435686&CategoryId=12395|title=Islamic State Launches Counter-Attacks on US-Backed Kurdish Forces in Syria\n|date=3 May 2017|publisher=The Latin American Herald Tribune|accessdate=4 May 2017}}</ref> It was later reported that a deal had been reached to allow remaining ISIL fighters to withdraw from the city as well as the dam.<ref name=SOHRalmost/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.almasdarnews.com/article/isil-fully-withdraws-tabqa-euphrates-dam-following-deal-kurdish-forces/|title=Humiliating defeat for ISIS as Kurdish troops impose full control over Tabqa city|date=4 May 2017|publisher=Al-Masdar News|accessdate=4 May 2017}}</ref> SDF and its commanders however denied any deal had been reached, adding that clashes were still ongoing against ISIL in a village near Tabqa and the three northern districts of the town including some militants who were hiding among civilians.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rudaw.net/english/middleeast/syria/04052017|title=SDF denies deal to evacuate ISIS in Tabqa, reports intensive clashes|date=4 May 2017|publisher=Rudaw|accessdate=4 May 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://aranews.net/2017/05/syrian-democratic-forces-deny-evacuation-deal-with-isis/|title=Syrian Democratic Forces deny evacuation deal with ISIS|date=4 May 2017|publisher=ARA News|accessdate=5 May 2017}}</ref> Also on 3 May, a new batch of 110 fighters of the Elite Forces graduated after training in [[Al-Hasakah]]. The fighters are scheduled to participate in the Raqqa campaign.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://aletihadpress.com/2017/05/03/%D9%82%D9%88%D8%A7%D8%AA-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%86%D8%AE%D8%A8%D8%A9-%D8%AA%D8%AE%D8%B1%D9%91%D8%AC-%D8%AF%D9%81%D8%B9%D8%A9-%D8%AC%D8%AF%D9%8A%D8%AF%D8%A9-%D9%85%D9%86-%D9%85%D9%82%D8%A7%D8%AA%D9%84%D9%8A/|title=Elite Forces graduated a new batch of fighters to engage in the battle of tenderness|work=Al-Etihad Press|date=3 May 2017}}</ref>\n\n[[File:SDF raise their flag in Tabqa.png|right|thumb|SDF fighters raise their flag in [[Al-Thawrah|Tabqa]].]]\nOn 8 May 2017, 100 Arab fighters from northern Raqqa started training to join the YPG, for the Raqqa offensive, with training set to conclude at the end of the month.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/100-arab-young-men-joined-sdf/#prettyPhoto|title=100 Arab young men joined SDF - ANHA|website=en.hawarnews.com|accessdate=10 July 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170618203607/http://en.hawarnews.com/100-arab-young-men-joined-sdf/#prettyPhoto|archive-date=18 June 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref> Also on 8 May, SDF announced that they had captured the First Quarter district of Tabqa city that connects the three newer districts of the town to the dam.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/idUSKBN1840UT|title=U.S.-backed militias say they made new advance against Islamic State in Tabqa|date=8 May 2017|first=Angus|last=McDowall|publisher=Reuters|accessdate=10 May 2017}}</ref> The advance cutoff the two remaining suburbs under ISIL control from the dam. In addition, SDF also captured the Watani hospital.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://anfenglish.com/news/watani-hospital-west-of-tabqa-cleared-of-isis-19904|title=Watan\u00ee Hospital west of Tabqa cleared of ISIS|date=7 May 2017|publisher=ANF News|accessdate=10 May 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://anfenglish.com/news/connection-severed-between-tabqa-dam-and-three-neighborhoods-19907|title=Connection severed between Tabqa Dam and three neighborhoods|date=8 May 2017|publisher=ANF News|accessdate=10 May 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.almasdarnews.com/article/kurdish-forces-slice-adrift-isis-pocket-western-raqqa/|title=Kurdish forces slice adrift ISIS pocket in western Raqqa|date=8 May 2017|first=Chris|last=Tomson|publisher=Al-Masdar News|accessdate=10 May 2017}}</ref> It was also reported that SDF had captured the village of Sahel al-Khashab.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.abna24.com/news/middle-east/isis-chief-abu-bakr-al-baghdadi-asks-for-help-in-raqqa_828576.html|title=ISIS chief Abu Bakr Al-Baghdadi asks for help in Raqqa|date=8 May 2017|publisher=Ahlul Bayt News Agency|accessdate=10 May 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/sahel-al-khashab-completely-liberated/|title=Sahel al-Khashab completely liberated|date=8 May 2017|publisher=Hawar News Agency|accessdate=10 May 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170611213325/http://en.hawarnews.com/sahel-al-khashab-completely-liberated/|archive-date=11 June 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref> SOHR reported that although some Syrian ISIL fighters had withdrawn under a deal allowing SDF to take control of the whole town, other fighters who were mostly non-Syrian refused to withdraw and were clashing with SDF as well as waging a guerilla-style battle.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=65946|title=After agreeing to withdraw\u2026 Foreigner fighters of the \"Islamic State\" organization refuse to comply and start a guerrilla war in al-Tabaqa city's neighborhoods|date=8 May 2017|publisher=SOHR|accessdate=10 May 2017}}</ref> On 9 May, the SDF made a press statement announcing the relaunch of the fourth phase of the campaign after a 15-day suspension.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://anfenglish.com/news/fourth-phase-of-the-wrath-of-euphrates-relaunched-after-15-days-19954|title=Fourth phase of the Wrath of Euphrates relaunched after 15 days|first=ANF|last=News|website=ANF News}}</ref> The following day, the SDF as well as SOHR announced that the alliance had completely captured the town as well as the dam.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.aljazeera.com/news/2017/05/backed-syrian-forces-fully-capture-tabqa-isil-170510174620917.html|title=US-backed Syrian forces 'fully capture' Tabqa from ISIL|publisher=Al-Jazeera|accessdate=10 May 2017}}</ref><ref name=ArabiyaTabqa>{{cite web|url=http://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2017/05/10/US-backed-forces-seize-Syria-s-Tabqa-nearby-dam-monitor.html|title=US-backed forces seize Syria's Tabqa, dam from ISIS|work=Agence-France Presse|publisher=Al-Arabiya|accessdate=10 May 2017}}</ref>\n\n==== Resumption of Phase Four ====\nThe SDF announced that they had resumed the fourth phase of the campaign on 10 May.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/fourth-stage-of-operation-wrath-of-euphrates-is-resumed/|title=Fourth stage of Operation Wrath of Euphrates is resumed|publisher=Hawar News Agency|accessdate=11 May 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170614081016/http://en.hawarnews.com/fourth-stage-of-operation-wrath-of-euphrates-is-resumed/|archive-date=14 June 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref> On the next day, it was reported that the SDF had captured two to three villages to the north of Raqqa city.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.almasdarnews.com/article/kurdish-forces-capture-three-villages-just-ten-kilometers-north-isis-held-raqqa/|title=Kurdish forces capture three villages just ten kilometers north of ISIS-held Raqqa|first=Chris|last=Tomson|publisher=Al-Masdar News|accessdate=11 May 2017|date=2017-05-11}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://southfront.org/syrian-democratic-forces-took-full-control-tabqa-town-tabqa-dam/|title=Syrian Democratic Forces took full control over Tabqa town and Tabqa Dam|publisher=South Front|accessdate=11 May 2017|date=2017-05-10}}</ref> Later, they captured another village north of Raqqa.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.almasdarnews.com/article/syrian-democratic-forces-inch-closer-self-proclaimed-capital-isis/|title=Syrian Democratic Forces inch closer to the self-proclaimed capital of ISIS|first=Ivan|last=Castro|publisher=Al-Masdar News|accessdate=12 May 2017|date=2017-05-12}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hawarnews.com/%d8%aa%d8%ad%d8%b1%d9%8a%d8%b1-%d9%82%d8%b1%d9%8a%d8%a9-%d8%ae%d8%b1%d8%a8%d8%a9-%d8%ae%d8%a7%d9%86-%d9%88%d8%a5%d8%ad%d8%a8%d8%a7%d8%b7-%d9%87%d8%ac%d9%88%d9%85-%d8%b9%d9%84%d9%89-%d8%a3%d9%85-%d8%aa/|title=\u062a\u062d\u0631\u064a\u0631 \u0642\u0631\u064a\u0629 \u062e\u0631\u0628\u0629 \u062e\u0627\u0646 \u0648\u0625\u062d\u0628\u0627\u0637 \u0647\u062c\u0648\u0645 \u0639\u0644\u0649 \u0623\u0645 \u062a\u0646\u0643|publisher=Hawar News|date=11 May 2017|language=ar}}</ref> An ISIL counter-attack on Tabqa city was meanwhile repelled.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://syriadirect.org/news/the-day-after-us-backed-forces-drive-back-islamic-state-counterattack-after-tabqa-win/|title=The day after: US-backed forces thwart Islamic State counterattack after Tabqa win|publisher=Syria Direct|date=12 May 2017}}</ref> On 12 May, 2 villages in the northern countryside along with a cotton mill were captured. Kurdish news agencies also stated that SDF had captured a local ruling party headquarters as well as prison used by the militants.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.almasdarnews.com/article/syrian-army-kurdish-forces-team-isis-rural-aleppo-raqqa-map-update/|title=Syrian Army, Kurdish forces team up against ISIS in rural Aleppo, Raqqa \u2013 Map update|publisher=Al-Masdar News|date=13 May 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thenational.ae/world/middle-east/syrian-fighters-move-even-closer-to-isils-capital|title=Syrian fighters move even closer to ISIL's 'capital'|agency=Associated Press|publisher=The National|date=13 May 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/el-ensar-village-liberated-from-gangs/|title=El-Ensar village liberated from gangs|publisher=Hawar News|date=12 May 2017|access-date=14 May 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170615211936/http://en.hawarnews.com/el-ensar-village-liberated-from-gangs/|archive-date=15 June 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://anfenglish.com/news/sdf-advances-6-km-towards-the-raqqa-city-19990|title=SDF advances 6 km towards the Raqqa city|publisher=ANF|date=12 May 2017}}</ref> By 14 May, SDF captured three to four villages to the north of Raqqa.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/other-3-villages-north-of-al-raqqa-liberated/|title=Other 3 villages north of al-Raqqa liberated |publisher=Hawar News Agency|date=14 May 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=66415|title=\"Euphrates Wrath\" operation forces continue their offensive for the 3rd consecutive day and advancement in more areas|publisher= SOHR|date=14 May 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.almasdarnews.com/article/kurdish-forces-reach-northern-gates-raqqa-liberating-four-villages/|title=Kurdish forces reach the northern gates of Raqqa after liberating four more villages|publisher= Al-Masdar News|date=14 May 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://southfront.org/us-backed-forces-capture-3-more-villages-from-isis-in-northern-raqqa/|title=U.S.-backed forces capture 3 more villages from ISIS in Northern Raqqa|publisher= South Front|date=14 May 2017}}</ref> About seven to eight villages were captured by SDF in the region till 17 May, along with about 17 hamlets also reported captured.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/two-al-raqqas-villages-17-hamlets-liberated-from-gangs/|title=Two al-Raqqa's villages, 17 hamlets liberated from gangs|publisher=Hawar News Agency|date=15 May 2017|access-date=17 May 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170619000801/http://en.hawarnews.com/two-al-raqqas-villages-17-hamlets-liberated-from-gangs/|archive-date=19 June 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/3-villages-15-hamlets-liberated-from-is-gangs/|title=3 villages, 15 hamlets liberated from IS gangs|publisher= Hawar News Agency|date=16 May 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hawarnews.com/%d8%aa%d8%ad%d8%b1%d9%8a%d8%b1-%d9%82%d8%b1%d9%8a%d8%a9-%d8%a7%d9%84%d8%b1%d8%b4%d9%8a%d8%af/|title=\u062a\u062d\u0631\u064a\u0631 \u0642\u0631\u064a\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u0631\u0634\u064a\u062f|publisher= Hawar News|date=15 May 2017|language=ar}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hawarnews.com/%d8%a7%d9%84%d8%aa%d9%82%d8%af%d9%85-%d8%a8%d8%a7%d8%aa%d8%ac%d8%a7%d9%87-%d9%85%d8%af%d9%8a%d9%86%d8%a9-%d8%a7%d9%84%d8%b1%d9%82%d8%a9-%d9%8a%d8%aa%d9%88%d8%a7%d8%b5%d9%84-%d8%aa%d8%ad%d8%b1%d9%8a/|title=\u0627\u0644\u062a\u0642\u062f\u0645 \u0628\u0627\u062a\u062c\u0627\u0647 \u0645\u062f\u064a\u0646\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u0631\u0642\u0629 \u064a\u062a\u0648\u0627\u0635\u0644: \u062a\u062d\u0631\u064a\u0631 \u0642\u0631\u064a\u0629 \u0648\u0635\u0648\u0627\u0645\u0639 \u0627\u0644\u0642\u0645\u062d|publisher= Hawar News Agency|date=16 May 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.almasdarnews.com/article/kurdish-forces-just-three-kilometers-raqqa-isis-loses-control-key-highway/|title=Kurdish forces just three kilometers from Raqqa as ISIS loses control of key highways|publisher=Al-Masdar News|date=18 May 2017}}</ref>\n\nOn 18 May, SDF captured a village located to the east of Raqqa.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=66657|title=\"Euphrates Wrath\" forces continue their operations to reduce the \"Islamic State\" organization's controlled areas and to take more villages from it in the eastern countryside of Al-Raqqah.|publisher=SOHR|date=18 May 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/hamrat-ghanam-is-liberated-by-sdf/|title=Hamrat Ghanam is liberated by SDF|publisher=Hawar News|date=18 May 2017|access-date=26 May 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170523011217/http://en.hawarnews.com/hamrat-ghanam-is-liberated-by-sdf/|archive-date=23 May 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref> On the next day, two villages along with a farm were captured by the alliance.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ku.hawarnews.com/qsde-gaveke-din-nezi-reqqaye-bu-du-gunden-din-hatin-rizgarkirin/|title=QSD'\u00ea gaveke din n\u00eaz\u00ee Reqqay\u00ea b\u00fb, du gund\u00ean din hatin rizgarkirin|publisher=Hawar News Agency|date=19 May 2017|language=ku|access-date=21 May 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170522212028/http://ku.hawarnews.com/qsde-gaveke-din-nezi-reqqaye-bu-du-gunden-din-hatin-rizgarkirin/|archive-date=22 May 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=66772|title=The forces of the \" Euphrates Wrath \" operation manage to achieve more advances in the eastern countryside of al-Raqqa and documenting the death of their fighters during the battles|publisher=SOHR|date=19 May 2017}}</ref> By 21 May, two villages were captured with SDF advancing within {{convert|2|km|mi}} of the [[Baath Dam]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/al-raqqa-village-liberated-13-mercenaries-killed/|title=Al-Raqqa: village liberated, 13 mercenaries killed|publisher=Hawar News|date=21 May 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/another-step-towards-al-raqqa/|title=Another step towards al-Raqqa|publisher=Hawar News|date=21 May 2017|access-date=26 May 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170705072934/http://en.hawarnews.com/another-step-towards-al-raqqa/|archive-date=5 July 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://southfront.org/syrian-democratic-forces-deploy-closer-isis-self-proclaimed-capital-raqqah/|title=Syrian Democratic Forces deploy closer to ISIS self-proclaimed capital of Raqqah|publisher=South Front|date=21 May 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=67026|title=\"Euphrates Wrath\" operation forces advance west of Al-Raqqah and control new village and get closer to Al-Baath Dam|publisher=SOHR|date=22 May 2017}}</ref> By 23 May, another 2 villages were captured near the dam.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/2-villages-liberated-21-mercenaries-killed/|title=2 villages liberated, 21 mercenaries killed|publisher=Hawar News|date=23 May 2017|access-date=26 May 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170705074456/http://en.hawarnews.com/2-villages-liberated-21-mercenaries-killed/|archive-date=5 July 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://southfront.org/sdf-advancing-against-isis-in-western-raqqah-countryside-map/|title=SDF advancing against ISIS in western Raqqah countryside (Map)|publisher=South Front|date=23 May 2017}}</ref> Another village was captured near the dam later.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.almasdarnews.com/article/kurdish-forces-verge-capturing-baath-dam-amid-new-gains-rural-raqqa/|title=Kurdish forces on the verge of capturing Baath dam amid new gains in rural Raqqa|publisher=Al-Masdar News|date=24 May 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://anfenglish.com/news/sdf-liberates-the-yamamah-village-in-raqqa-operation-20146|title=SDF liberates the Yamamah village in Raqqa operation|publisher=ANF|date=23 May 2017}}</ref> On 24 May, two villages including the town of Hamrat Nasera were captured by the SDF in the western countryside while a village in the eastern countryside was also reported to have been captured.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/wrath-of-euphrates-a-town-and-village-liberated/|title=Wrath of Euphrates: a town and village liberated|publisher=Hawar News|date=24 May 2017|access-date=26 May 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170705072954/http://en.hawarnews.com/wrath-of-euphrates-a-town-and-village-liberated/|archive-date=5 July 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://southfront.org/syrian-democratic-forces-developing-advance-east-and-west-of-raqqa/|title=Syrian Democratic Forces developing advance east and west of Raqqa (Photos, Video)|publisher=South Front|date=24 May 2017}}</ref> On the next day, the SDF captured the strategic Kadiran village to the north of the dam.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/a-village-north-of-al-hurriyah-dam-liberated/|title=A village north of al-Hurriyah Dam liberated|publisher=Hawar News|date=25 May 2017|access-date=26 May 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170628162322/http://en.hawarnews.com/a-village-north-of-al-hurriyah-dam-liberated/|archive-date=28 June 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://southfront.org/us-backed-forces-few-meters-away-from-baath-dam-in-raqqa/|title=US-backed forces few metres away from Baath Dam in Raqqa (Videos, Photos)|publisher=South Front|date=25 May 2017}}</ref> Meanwhile, the Manbij Military Council sent an additional 2,200 fighters.<ref name=\"manbij fm\" /> The SDF stated the next day that more than 1,000 men from the al-Tabqa region had joined it on the day.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/1000-young-men-join-sdf/|title=1,000 young men join SDF|publisher=Hawar News|access-date=2017-05-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170630094052/http://en.hawarnews.com/1000-young-men-join-sdf/|archive-date=2017-06-30|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nFollowing the seizure of six villages on 30 May, the Kurdish-led Syrian Democratic Forces (SDF) continued on the 31st as units were able to take control of Hunaydi village and establish fire control over a section of the M6 highway, a jihadist supply road which runs vertically through ISIS territory in Syria. In addition, ISIL withdrew from the village of al-Assadiah. Effectively, the SDF had then besieged the highly fortified Division 17 military base, located directly north of the provincial capital. Meanwhile, approximately 4,000 ISIS fighters were waiting to fight the SDF in Raqqa.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.almasdarnews.com/article/kurds-reach-gates-raqqa-4000-isis-fighters-gear-apocalyptic-battle/|title=Kurds reach the gates of Raqqa as 4,000 ISIS fighters gear up for apocalyptic battle}}</ref>\n\nOn 2 June, the SDF captured the town of Mansoura after a 3-day battle. Before the SDF captured it, Mansoura was the largest town still under ISIL control west of Raqqa.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-mideast-crisis-syria-raqqa-idUSKBN18T2S6|title=U.S.-backed forces seize Islamic State-held town near Syria's Raqqa: source, monitor|work=Reuters|date=2 June 2017}}</ref> By 4 June, the SDF fully captured [[Baath Dam]].<ref name=baath/>\n\n=== Phase Five: Battle for Raqqa city ===\n{{Main|Battle of Raqqa (2017)}}\n[[File:US fire support for SDF at Raqqa.png|right|thumb|The [[United States Marine Corps]] providing [[fire support]] for the SDF during the [[Battle of Raqqa (2017)|Battle of Raqqa]].]]\n[[File:Battle of Raqqa (2017).svg|thumb|left|Map of the SDF's advances in Raqqa city]]\nOn 6 June 2017, the SDF announced the start of the Battle of Raqqa city. The offensive came from Raqqa's north, east, and west. The SDF attacked the 17th Division base and the Mashlab district in the northern part of the city.<ref name=starts>{{Cite web|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-mideast-crisis-syria-raqqa-idUSKBN18X0LH|title=U.S.-backed Syrian force starts battle to capture Raqqa from Islamic State|work=Reuters|date=6 June 2017}}</ref> The battle was earlier announced by SDF to be the \"fifth and final phase\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/mideast-crisis-syria-raqqa-idINKBN18W29G|title=U.S.-backed anti-IS forces to announce Raqqa assault start date on Tuesday|work=Reuters|date=5 June 2017}}</ref>\n\nOn 24 June, the SDF completely besieged Raqqa city, trapping about 4,000 ISIL militants in the city.<ref name=\"fully encircled\">{{cite web|url=https://www.almasdarnews.com/article/isis-fully-encircled-raqqa-city-latest-kurdish-advances/|title=ISIS fully encircled in Raqqa city after latest Kurdish advances|date=24 June 2017|publisher=|accessdate=10 July 2017}}</ref>\n\nAs of the 28 September, around 50% of Raqqa had been \"totally destroyed\" during the battle.<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://www.middleeasteye.net/news/inside-raqqa-islamic-state-raqqa-slowly-falling-1603909747 |title = Raqqa in ruins: Brutal fight against IS leaves city destroyed}}</ref>\n\nOn 14 October, a group of ISIL fighters and around 400 civilians, reportedly used as [[human shield]]s by ISIS, evacuated from Raqqa under an agreement with the SDF. The next day, the SDF announced the \"final phase\" of the battle, code-named the ''Battle of Martyr [[Adnan Abu Amjad]]'',<ref>{{cite web |url=http://en.hawarnews.com/adnan-abu-amjad-battle-to-liberate-rest-of-al-raqqa-began/ |title=Adnan Abu Amjad battle to liberate rest of al-Raqqa began |access-date=2017-10-15 |publisher=Hawar News Agency|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180120052352/http://en.hawarnews.com/adnan-abu-amjad-battle-to-liberate-rest-of-al-raqqa-began/ |archive-date=2018-01-20 |url-status=dead}}</ref> to capture the remaining ISIL holdouts in 10% of the city.<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://www.aljazeera.com/news/2017/10/evacuation-ends-isil-defeat-syria-raqqa-nears-171015061514918.html |title = Evacuation ends as ISIL defeat in Syria's Raqqa nears &#124; Syria News &#124; al Jazeera}}</ref>\n\nOn 16 October, the SDF reportedly destroyed the last ISIL forces in the al-Andalus and al-Matar neighborhoods,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://en.hawarnews.com/al-andalus-and-al-matar-neighborhoods-liberated/ |title=Al-Andalus and al-Matar neighborhoods liberated |work=[[Hawar News Agency]] |date=16 October 2017 |accessdate=18 October 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180120052654/http://en.hawarnews.com/al-andalus-and-al-matar-neighborhoods-liberated/ |archive-date=20 January 2018 |url-status=dead}}</ref> and finally secured the al-Naim roundabout.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://en.hawarnews.com/raqqas-al-naim-roundabout-liberated-37-isis-members-surrender/ |title=Raqqa's Al Naim roundabout liberated, 37 ISIS members surrender |work=[[Hawar News Agency]] |date=16 October 2017 |accessdate=18 October 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180120052709/http://en.hawarnews.com/raqqas-al-naim-roundabout-liberated-37-isis-members-surrender/ |archive-date=20 January 2018 |url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nOn 17 October, ISIL control in Raqqa officially ended when the SDF captured the National Hospital and the Stadium,<ref name=oct17 /> though a [[clear and hold]] operation was still expected in order to clear out potential remaining pockets of resistance.<ref name=oct17>{{Cite web | url=http://www.dailystar.com.lb/News/Middle-East/2017/Oct-17/422965-us-backed-militias-take-major-raqqa-position-from-daesh-sdf.ashx |title = Daesh defeated in their Syrian capital Raqqa &#124; News , Middle East &#124; THE DAILY STAR}}</ref>\n\nFollowing the end of clearing operations, victory was officially declared by the SDF on 20 October.<ref name=\"SDF declares victory\">{{cite web|url=http://abcnews.go.com/International/us-backed-syrian-force-declares-victory-isis-capital/story?id=50605976|title=US-backed Syrian forces declare victory over ISIS in its former 'capital,' Raqqa|author1=Luis Martinez|author2=Morgan Winsor|date=20 October 2017|accessdate=20 October 2017}}</ref>\n\n== Syrian Army offensive in southern Raqqa ==\n{{Main|Southern Raqqa offensive (June 2017)}}\nOn June 12, the Syrian Arab Army (SAA), led by the [[Tiger Forces]], began an offensive on ISIL positions in the western countryside of Raqqa, south of the town of Maskanah, which it [[Maskanah Plains offensive|recently captured]], toward the Ithriya-Tabqa highway, aiming to secure its main supply route to Aleppo. A [[Hezbollah]]-run media unit reported that government forces advanced 32&nbsp;km south of Maskanah, capturing the villages of Rajm Askar, Bir Inbaj, Zahar Um Baj, Jab Aziz, Jab al-Ghanem, Abu Sousa and Jab Abyadin in the process. A source close to the Tiger Forces said that the SAA had occupied all areas west of the [[Resafa]] oil field. [[Al-Masdar News]] reported that the June 13 advances marked the first time government forces had any presence around SDF-occupied Tabqa in three years.<ref name=\"Reuters\"/><ref name=\"AMN 13 June\">{{cite web | url=https://www.almasdarnews.com/article/syrian-army-kicks-off-raqqa-offensive-big-way-key-town-liberated/ | title=Syrian Army kicks off Raqqa offensive in a big way, key oil field liberated | publisher=Al-Masdar News | date=13 June 2017 | accessdate=13 June 2017 | author=Fadel, Leith}}</ref> On 18 June, a Syrian Air Force [[Sukhoi Su-17|Su-22]] was shot down by a US Navy [[Boeing F/A-18E/F Super Hornet|F-18E]] south of Tabqa; the US military subsequently claimed that the Syrian jet had been intercepted after it had bombed SDF positions.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.military.com/daily-news/2017/06/18/us-navy-fa18e-shoots-down-su22-over-syria.html?ESRC=todayinmil.sm|title=US F/A-18E Shoots Down Syrian Su-22 in Air-to-Air Kill|author=Oriana Pawlyk|work=[[Military.com]]|date=18 May 2017|accessdate=19 June 2017}}</ref> Both the pro-opposition [[Syrian Observatory for Human Rights|SOHR]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=68314|title=A regime warplane was targeted and dropped in the skies of the al-Resafa area|author=|work=[[Syrian Observatory for Human Rights|SOHR]]|date=19 May 2017|accessdate=19 June 2017}}</ref> as well as the pro-SDF [[Hawar News Agency]] denied this, however, stating that the jet had not attacked the SDF. The Syrian government said that their Su-22 had bombed ISIL positions when it was destroyed.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/syrian-regime-a-fighter-downed-by-global-coalition/|title=Syrian regime: a fighter downed by global coalition|work=[[Hawar News Agency]]|date=19 May 2017|accessdate=19 June 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170623021833/http://en.hawarnews.com/syrian-regime-a-fighter-downed-by-global-coalition/|archive-date=23 June 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nOn July 15, the SAA captured the Wahab, al-Fahd, Dbaysan, al-Qseer, Abu al-Qatat and Abu Qatash oil fields, south of Resafa.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-mideast-crisis-iraq-baghdadi-idUSKBN1A20JD | title=Syrian army takes more oil fields from Islamic State in Raqqa and eastern desert | publisher=Reuters | date=15 July 2017 | accessdate=18 July 2017 | author=Al-Khalidi, Suleiman}}</ref> Al-Masdar News reported that the Tiger Forces overran three more fields in the region the following day, including Zamleh Sharqiyah, Bir Zamleh and Al-Khalaa.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.almasdarnews.com/article/three-gas-fields-liberated-syrian-army-brushes-isis-aside-southern-raqqa/ | title=Three gas fields liberated as Syrian Army brushes ISIS aside in southern Raqqa | publisher=Al-Masdar News | date=16 July 2017 | accessdate=18 July 2017 | author=Tomson, Chris}}</ref>\n\n== Administration of captured territory ==\n=== Civil administration ===\n{{See also|Raqqa Internal Security Forces}}\n[[File:Samer Kharkhi.png|right|thumb|Samer Kharkhi, one of the Raqqa Civil Council's leading members]]\n[[File:Raqqa internal security forces with their flag.png|left|thumb|Members of the [[Raqqa Internal Security Forces]] with their flag in [[Ayn Issa]]]]\nOn 14 November, the SDF's civilian sister institution, the [[Syrian Democratic Council]] (SDC), started working on the establishment of a civilian administration to run the city of Raqqa after the expulsion of the Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant. SDC co-chair [[\u00celham Ehmed]] said \"such an administration could provide a good example for democratic change in Raqqa, especially that the city has been for years a de facto capital for the ISIS terrorist group. This accomplishment would be a major change in the overall situation in Syria, and would help the country move towards stability, democratic change. Raqqa will be an example for the whole country.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://aranews.net/2016/11/local-civilian-council-to-run-post-isis-raqqa-kurdish-official/|title=Local civilian council to run post-ISIS Raqqa: Kurdish official|work=[[ARA News]]|date=14 November 2016|access-date=14 November 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170219095058/http://aranews.net/2016/11/local-civilian-council-to-run-post-isis-raqqa-kurdish-official/|archive-date=19 February 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nOn 8 December, Col. John Dorrian, the Operation Inherent Resolve spokesman, stated that \"a governance structure representative of the local population\" similar to that in [[Manbij]] is planned for Raqqa.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hurriyetdailynews.com/us-facilitating-joint-talks-with-turkey-syrian-kurdish-forces-to-ease-tension-.aspx?pageID=238&nID=107109&NewsCatID=358|title=US facilitating joint talks with Turkey, Syrian Kurdish forces to ease tension|work=Hurriyet Daily News|date=9 December 2016}}</ref> On 10 December, Cihan Shekh Ehmed, the spokesman of the SDF-led operation, said that Raqqa would be run by a local elected civilian council after it was liberated.<ref name=\"Secondphase\"/> On 27 March 2017, [[Salih Muslim Muhammad]], co-chairman of the [[Democratic Union Party (Syria)|Democratic Union Party (PYD)]], said that as soon as the SDF had captured the city, \"the people of Raqqa are the ones who [will] take the decision on everything\". If they wanted to do so, Muslim said, they could choose to join the [[Rojava|Democratic Federal System of Northern Syria]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-mideast-crisis-syria-pyd-idUSKBN16Y1B0|title=Syria's Raqqa expected to join Kurdish-led federalism: Kurdish leader|work=Reuters|date=27 March 2017}}</ref> On the same day, the provisional Raqqa Civil Council announced that it had taken over the administration of the eastern countryside.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/al-raqqa-civil-council-undertakes-the-liberated-areas-administration/|title=Al-Raqqa Civil Council undertakes the liberated areas administration|work=[[Hawar News Agency]]|date=27 March 2017|access-date=27 March 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170518013227/http://en.hawarnews.com/al-raqqa-civil-council-undertakes-the-liberated-areas-administration/|archive-date=18 May 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nDuring a meeting in [[Ayn Issa]] on 18 April 2017 attended by tribal chiefs and local dignitaries from Raqqa, SDF announced the official establishment of a civilian council to govern Raqqa city after it is captured. During the meeting of delegates including representatives from [[Syrian people|Arabs]], [[Kurds]] and [[Syrian Turkmen|Turkmen]]; co-chairs Layla Mohammed and Mahmoud Shawakh al-Busran<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://aranews.net/2017/04/kurdish-feminist-appointed-co-head-raqqa-civilian-council/|title=Kurdish feminist appointed as co-head of Raqqa civilian council|author=Wladimir van Wilgenburg|publisher=ARA News|date=20 April 2017}}</ref> were elected and 14 committees were established. SDF stated that a military council to provide security to the city after its capture will be formed soon.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://anfenglish.com/news/raqqa-civilian-assembly-establishment-meeting-kicks-off-19581|title=Raqqa Civilian Assembly Establishment Meeting kicks off|publisher=ANF News|date=18 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://anfenglish.com/news/raqqa-to-be-administered-by-civilian-assembly-after-liberation-19589|title=Raqqa to be administered by Civilian Assembly after liberation|publisher=ANF News|date=18 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/al-raqqas-constituent-congress-a-statement-released-decisions-made/|title=Al-Raqqa's constituent congress: a statement released, decisions made|work=[[Hawar News Agency]]|date=18 April 2017|access-date=18 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170424120052/http://en.hawarnews.com/al-raqqas-constituent-congress-a-statement-released-decisions-made/|archive-date=24 April 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/idUSKBN17K1DF|title=U.S.-allied Syrian groups form civilian council to run Raqqa|first=Ellen|last=Francis|work=Reuters|date=18 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2017/04/18/US-backed-Syria-forces-set-up-post-ISIS-Raqqa-council-.html|title=US-backed Syria forces set up post-ISIS Raqqa council|work=Agence-France Presse|publisher=Al-Arabiya|date=18 April 2017}}</ref> On 20 April, the new civilian council also began to operate in the areas of Tabqa, handling the distribution of food to local villagers.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://anfenglish.com/news/raqqa-civilian-assembly-starts-works-in-liberated-areas-19622|title=Raqqa Civilian Assembly starts works in liberated areas |work=ANF News|date=20 April 2017}}</ref>\n\nOn 15 May 2017, an agreement was made to establish a 'Tabqa Civilian Assembly'. This assembly will be temporary as a broader assembly will be established with councils following the return of residents.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://anfenglish.com/news/tabqa-civilian-assembly-declared-20028|title=Tabqa Civilian Assembly declared|first=ANF|last=News|website=ANF News|accessdate=10 July 2017}}</ref>\n\nOn 17 May 2017, the [[Raqqa Internal Security Forces]] (RISF) were established as new police unit, with the first training course being set up in [[Ayn Issa]]; their purpose is to provide law and order in the areas captured from ISIL during the campaign. As native police, the RISF is supposed to be expanded to at least 3,000 members.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://aranews.net/2017/05/us-led-coalition-trains-raqqa-internal-forces-to-run-post-isis-city/|title=US-led coalition trains Raqqa Internal Forces to run post-ISIS city|author=Wladimir van Wilgenburg|work=[[ARA News]]|date=17 May 2017|access-date=22 May 2017}}</ref>\n\nOn 20 October, SDF declared that Raqqa and its province will decide its own future \"within the framework of a decentralised, federal, democratic Syria\". They pledged to protect Raqqa province from external threats and hand over control to a civil council from the city.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/mideast-crisis-syria-raqqa/raqqa-to-be-part-of-federal-syria-u-s-backed-militia-says-idINKBN1CP16R|title=Raqqa to be part of \"federal Syria\", U.S.-backed militia says|author=Tom Perry|work=Reuters|date=20 October 2017|access-date=23 October 2017}}</ref> In a ceremony on the same day, SDF handed over administration of Raqqa city to the civil council while the 3,000-strong United States-trained police force was tasked with governance and security.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.france24.com/en/20171020-local-officials-tribal-elders-take-over-raqqa-victory-islamic-state-sdf-syria|title=Syria's Raqqa handed over to local officials and tribal elders|work=Associated Press|publisher=France24|date=20 October 2017|access-date=23 October 2017}}</ref>\n\n=== IDP camp and informal settlement ===\nFood, goods and resources have become rare in Raqqa due to clashes, while lives are also at risk from fightings and coalition's bombings.<ref>http://www.reachresourcecentre.info/system/files/resource-documents/reach_syr_ar-raqqa_city_situation_overview_ii_7_july_2017.pdf, from http://www.reachresourcecentre.info/countries/syria</ref> Also, a number of IDP camps and settlement have been set up across northern Syria.<ref>http://www.reachresourcecentre.info/system/files/resource-documents/reach_syr_raqqa_camps_and_sites_profiles_july_2017_v5.pdf, from http://www.reachresourcecentre.info/countries/syria</ref>\n\n=== Tensions and insurgency ===\nOn 25 March 2018, protests erupted in [[Al-Mansurah, Raqqa Governorate|Mansoura]] after a leader of the Bukahmis tribe was arrested by the SDF. Protesters burned tires, and SDF fighters opened fire. The tribal leader was released on the same day. Following the protests, a SDF YPG intelligence officer was killed and his body was dumped on a road near Mansoura. It is unclear if his assassination was related to the protests.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://nedaa-sy.com/en/news/5078|title=Syria's Democratic Militias Release Al-Bukahmis Leader in Raqqa|work=Syria Call|date=26 March 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.dailysabah.com/war-on-terror/2018/03/29/ypg-enraging-locals-in-tal-rifaat-manbij-and-now-in-raqqa |title = YPG enraging locals in Tal Rifaat, Manbij and now in Raqqa}}</ref>\nAfter the conclusion of the campaign, the SDF was faced with a continued [[Eastern Syria Insurgency|insurgency]] by ISIL.\n\n== Gallery ==\n<gallery>\nImage:YPJ sniper Raqqa (November 2016).jpg|A [[YPJ]] sniper during the offensive on 13 November 2016\nImage:SDF technical in northern Raqqa countryside (November 2016).png|A [[Syrian Democratic Forces|SDF]] [[Technical (vehicle)|technical]] in a village captured from [[Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant|ISIL]] on 15 November 2016\nImage:Villagers return to Al-Hisbah after SDF conquest (November 2016).png|Refugees return to their hometown of Al-Hisbah, after the SDF captured it from ISIL.\nImage:SDF technicals in northern Raqqa countryside (December 2016).png|SDF technicals in the northwestern countryside on 12 December 2016\nImage:Tell Abyad Revolutionaries and YPG camp during Raqqa offensive (December 2016).png|Temporary camp of the SDF near Mahmudli on 17 December 2016\nImage:Tell Abyad Revolutionaries and YPG fighters (Raqqa December 2016).png|Fighters of the Tell Abyad Revolutionaries Brigade and the YPG warm themselves at a campfire.\nImage:YPG fighters Raqqa (December 2016).jpg|Kurdish YPG fighters during the offensive on 24 December 2016\nImage:Mahmudli.png|The town of Mahmudli on 4 January 2017, three days after its capture by the SDF\nImage:SDF infantry in Mahmudli.png|SDF fighters in Mahmudli on 4 January 2017\nImage:SDF at Jabar Castle 2.png|SDF fighters at Qal'at Ja'bar on 10 January 2017\nImage:SDF at Jabar Castle 1.png|SDF fighters in front of Qal'at Ja'bar on 10 January 2017\nImage:SDF Guardian Armored Personnel Carrier 2.png|A Kurdish fighter fits a SDF flag on a Guardian [[armored personnel carrier]] supplied by the US.\nImage:SDF MT-LB.png|An [[MT-LB]] of the SDF during the offensive\nImage:YPJ fighters Raqqa (February 2017).jpg|YPJ fighters on 7 February 2017\nImage:Deir Ezzor Military Council fighters.png|[[Syrian Democratic Forces military councils#Deir Ezzor|Deir Ezzor Military Council]] fighters on 9 March 2017\nImage:YPG sniper (Raqqa offensive 2017).jpg|A YPG sniper near the Euphrates\nImage:SDF T-55 near Tabqa Dam.png|A SDF [[T-54/T-55|T-55]] during the offensive\nImage:YPG and YPJ vehicles near Tabqa.png|[[Toyota Hilux]] and other vehicles of the YPG and YPJ 