 October 2017\n|combatant1  = {{flagicon image|Flag of Syrian Democratic Forces.svg}} '''[[Syrian Democratic Forces]]'''<br />{{flagicon image|Flag of Rojava.svg}} [[Self-Defense Forces (Rojava cantons)|Self Defence Forces]] (HXP)<ref name=\"HXP\">{{cite web|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/self-defense-fighters-join-wrath-of-euphrates/|title=Self-defense fighters join Wrath of Euphrates|work=[[Hawar News Agency]]|author=J.O|date=5 February 2017|access-date=5 February 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170206104142/http://en.hawarnews.com/self-defense-fighters-join-wrath-of-euphrates/|archive-date=6 February 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref><br />{{flagicon image|Red and Black Mutualist Flag.png}}{{flagicon image|International Freedom Battalion original banner.svg}} [[Left-wing politics|Leftist]]/[[Anarchism|anarchist]] volunteers{{efn|name=Left|Most leftist foreign volunteers fight as part of the YPG,{{sfnp|Harp|2017|pp=43-49}} though some have also formed independent units, such as the [[Antifascist International Tabur]]{{sfnp|Harp|2017|p=49}} and the [[International Revolutionary People's Guerrilla Forces|IRPGF]], or joined the [[International Freedom Battalion]]. The latter is a larger unit, mostly composed of Kurdish and Turkish communists.<ref name=\"IFB\">{{cite web|url=https://anfenglish.com/kurdistan/raqqa-s-fall-will-bring-the-end-of-erdogan|title='Raqqa's fall will bring the end of Erdo\u011fan'|first=Sinan|last=Deniz|work=ANF News|date=13 November 2016|accessdate=26 January 2017}}</ref>}}<br />\n{{flagicon image|Seal of Combined Joint Task Force \u2013 Operation Inherent Resolve.svg|border=no}} '''[[Combined Joint Task Force \u2013 Operation Inherent Resolve|CJTF\u2013OIR]]'''\n* {{flag|United States}}\n* {{flag|France}}<ref name=\"gains\">{{cite web|url=http://www.voanews.com/a/kurdish-arab-forces-syria-gains-raqqa-province/3646230.html|title=Kurdish-Arab Forces in Syria Make Gains in Raqqa Province|work=[[Voice of America]]|first=Sirwan|last=Kajjo|da