curity in [[Al-Thawrah]])}}<ref name=\"officials\">{{cite web|url=http://aranews.net/2016/12/islamic-state-replaces-syrian-officials-foreign-jihadists-raqqa/|title=Islamic State replaces Syrian officials by foreign jihadists in Raqqa|publisher=[[ARA News]]|first=Haytham|last=Mustafa|date=31 December 2016|accessdate=31 December 2016|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170101091249/http://aranews.net/2016/12/islamic-state-replaces-syrian-officials-foreign-jihadists-raqqa/|archivedate=1 January 2017}}</ref><br />{{flagdeco|Islamic State in Iraq and the Levant}} [[Abu Jandal al-Masri]]<ref name=\"officials\" /><br />{{small|(Chief of Information in Raqqa)}}<br />{{flagdeco|Islamic State in Iraq and the Levant}} Abu Muhammad al-Jazrawi<br />{{small|(Chief of Al-Hisba secret police}}<ref name=\"officials\" /><br />{{flagdeco|Islamic State in Iraq and the Levant}} Mahmoud al-Isawi{{KIA}}<br />{{small|(ISIL propaganda chief)}}<ref name=\"al-Isawi\">{{cite web|title=US airstrike kills ISIS propaganda chief in Raqqa|url=http://aranews.net/2017/01/us-airstrike-kills-isis-propaganda-chief-in-raqqa/|publisher=ARA News|accessdate=7 January 2017}}</ref><br />{{flagdeco|Islamic State in Iraq and the Levant}} Abd al-Basit al-Iraqi{{KIA}}<br />{{small|(ISIL commander of [[Middle East]] external networks)}}<ref name=\"al-Basit\">{{cite web|url=http://www.longwarjournal.org/archives/2016/11/us-led-coalition-killed-emir-of-islamic-states-middle-east-external-networks.php|title=US-led coalition killed emir of Islamic State's 'Middle East external networks'|publisher=The Long War Journal|first=Thomas|last=Joscelyn|date=17 November 2016|accessdate=17 November 2016}}</ref><br />{{flagdeco|Islamic State in Iraq and the Levant}} [[Zainuri Kamaruddin]]{{KIA}}<br />{{small|([[Katibah Nusantara]] commander)}}<ref name=\"channel\">{{cite web|url=http://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/asiapacific/malaysian-is-leader-killed-in-syria-recruited-members-through/3440248.html|title=Three Malaysian ISIS jihadists killed in Raqqa airstrike|publisher=[[Channel NewsAsia]]|first=Amy|last=Chew|date=15 January 2017}}</ref><br />{{flagdeco|Islamic State in Iraq and the Levant}} [[Abu Luqman]]<br />{{small|(ISIL governor of Raqqa)}}{{sfnp|Tabler|2017|pp=2, 3}}<br />''For other ISIL commanders, see [[Order of battle for the Raqqa campaign (2016\u201317)|order of battle]]''\n|units1      = ''See [[Order of battle for the Raqqa campaign (2016\u201317)#Anti-ISIL forces|anti-ISIL forces order of battle]]''\n|units2      = ''See [[Order of battle for the Raqqa campaign (2016\u201317)#Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant|ISIL order of battle]]''\n|strength1   = {{flagicon image|Flag of Syrian Democratic Forces.svg}} 30,000\u201340,000 SDF fighters<ref name=\"batch\">{{cite web|url=https://www.almasdarnews.com/article/kurdish-forces-capture-first-batch-villages-isis-campaign-liberate-raqqa/|title=Kurdish forces capture first batch of villages from ISIS in campaign to liberate Raqqa|first=Chris|last=Tomson|date=6 November 2016|publisher=|accessdate=8 November 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=54042|title=30,000 militants to isolate Raqqa city from its northern countryside|publisher=}}</ref><ref name=\"40,000 fighters\">{{cite web|url=https://www.middleeastmonitor.com/20161104-international-coalition-40000-fighters-prepared-to-isolate-raqqa/|title=International coalition: 40,000 fighters prepared to isolate Raqqa|date=4 November 2016|publisher=}}</ref> {{small|(70% Arab acc. to the SDF)}}<ref name=\"ground\">{{cite web|url=http://aranews.net/2017/02/syrian-democratic-forces-seize-ground-east-raqqa-amid-isis-retreat/|title=Syrian Democratic Forces seize more ground east Raqqa amid ISIS retreat|first=Enwer|last=Omar|publisher=[[ARA News]]|date=12 February 2017|accessdate=12 February 2017}}</ref>\n* {{flagicon image|People's Protection Units Flag.svg|border=no}}{{flagicon image|YPJ_Flag.svg|border=no}} 25,000 [[People's Protection Units|YPG]