ford University Press: 2015: {{ISBN|9780198306429}}\n* ''Skelebones, Level 10'' Illustrated by David Semple : London: Oxford University Press: 2015: {{ISBN|9780198306467}}\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n\n[[Attitude (magazine)|Attitude]] Awards\n*  Winner 2019 - Attitude TV Award\n\n[[British Academy Children's Awards]]\n* Winner 2018 - Pre-School Live Action - Get Well Soon Hospital\n* Winner 2016 - Interactive: Adapted - Get Well Soon Hospital App\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{IMDb name|id=5442964|name=Ranj Singh}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Singh, Ranj}}\n[[Category:1979 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:English television presenters]]\n[[Category:LGBT people from England]]\n[[Category:People from Medway]]\n[[Category:Gay men]]\n[[Category:LGBT broadcasters from the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:LGBT writers from the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:British people of Punjabi descent]]\n\n== Personal life ==\nSingh is [[gay]], having come out at the age of 30 in 2009, he discussed his sexuality in an interview for [[Attitude (magazine)|''Attitude'' magazine]] in 2015 and in 2018 fronted the cover of [[Gay Times]] magazine as part of a [[Gay-sian|gaysian]] celebration of LGBTQ Asians <ref>{{cite web |last1=Connolly |first1=William J |title=Dr Ranj Singh Gaysians cover interview: \u201cAs queer Asians, we have so much to offer ourselves and to the wider world\u201d |url=https://www.gaytimes.co.uk/originals/115425/dr-ranj-singh-gaysians-cover-interview-as-queer-asians-we-have-so-much-to-offer-ourselves-and-to-the-wider-world/ |website=Gay Times |date=20 November 2018}}</ref>. Ranj has been an advocate for LGBTQ rights, especially among minorities, and won the Attitute TV Award in 2019 where he spoke of how \"People from ethnic minorities, people of colour, or LGBTQ people are still at a slight disadvantage\" in the media <ref>{{cite web |last1=Attitude |title=Attitude TV Award: Dr Ranj Singh |url=https://www.attitude.co.uk/article/attitude-tv-award-dr-ranj-singh-1/21978/ |website=Attitude.co.uk |accessdate=12 April 2020 |language=en |date=9 October 2019}}</ref>\n\nRanj was married to a woman after leaving university, but subsequently [[Divorce|divorced]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://attitude.co.uk/article/coming-out-to-my-wife-was-hard-but-coming-out-to-my-family-was-another-level-entirely/10919/|title=STRICTLY'S DR. RANJ SINGH: 'COMING OUT AS GAY TO MY WIFE WAS HARD, BUT TELLING MY FAMILY WAS ANOTHER LEVEL'|work=Attitude|date=5 November 2018}}</ref>. He is a [[tenor]] in a contemporary [[show choir]] called the Adam Street Singers.<ref>{{cite tweet |author=Adam Street Singers|user=adamstsingers|number=1057319843823783936|date=30 October 2018|title=LOVED being in the @RadioTimes this week as part of the article by @DrRanj. We really are so proud of our boy flying the flag - he\u2019s the hardest-working guy we know, and whilst we miss him, PLEASE keep voting to keep him in @bbcstrictly #teamRaja}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n===Television===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|- style=\"background:#b0c4de; text-align:center;\"\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2016\u2013present || ''[[This Morning (TV programme)|This Morning]]'' || Himself || Resident Doctor (57 episodes)\n|-\n| 2020 || ''[[Sport Relief!]]'' || Himself || Special\n|-\n| 2019-present || ''Lorraine (TV programme)|Lorraine'' || Himself || (2 episodes)\n|-\n| 2019-20 || ''[[Would I Lie to You? (game show)|Would I Lie to You?]]'' || Himself || (3 episodes)\n|-\n|2020 || ''[[Celebrity Mastermind]]'' || Himself || Episode 6\n|-\n|2020 || ''[[Catchphrase (British game show|Celebrity Catchphrase]]'' || Himself || Christmas Special\n|-\n|2020 || ''[[The Chase (British game show)|Celebrity Chase]]'' || Himself || Contestant (1 Episode)\n|-\n|2019 || ''[[Antiques Road Trip|Celebrity Antiques Road Trip]]'' || Himself || 1 Episode\n|-\n|2018-19 || ''[[Strictly Come Dancing (series 16)|Strictly Come Dancing]]'' || Hi